    },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do these rules detail the filtering rules required for the control of incoming as well as outgoing accesses?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.4.6"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do these rules detail controls to effect on the network equipment configurations?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do these rules detail controls to effect on the configurations of users stations?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B01-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do these rules define the required management methods to cover anomalies and incidents?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B01-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do these rules impose to send a report to a central authority for any anomaly and incident challenging the security of the Wide-area Network?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B01-11",\n              "index": "11",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a management procedure covering the authorization requests for the binding of any entity to the Wide-area Network and a structure empowered to analyze these requests and provide the corresponding authorization?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B01-12",\n              "index": "12",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a structure empowered to audit the application of the rules and to remove specific rights which are no longer needed or when the conditions are no longer met?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B01-13",\n              "index": "13",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit of the required conditions and application of the rules in each entity authorized to be part of the Wide-area Network?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B01-14",\n              "index": "14",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are reviews of the authorized connections (standard and non-standard) and of their relevance regularly conducted?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.4.7"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0143",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Deny network traffic by default / allow by exception",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall, at managed interfaces, deny network communications traffic by default and allow network communications traffic by exception (i.e., deny all, permit by exception).",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"f2a7b89a-e0c9-4908-8b18-2c718fc5414a\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"f2a7b89a-e0c9-4908-8b18-2c718fc5414a\\":\\"SC-7(5)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This applies to both inbound and outbound network communications traffic. A deny-all, permit-by-exception network communications traffic policy ensures that only those connections which are essential and approved are allowed."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0128",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Only allow certificate authorities for verification of protected sessions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall only allow the installation of [certificate authorities] for verification of the establishment of protected sessions.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"c24e4001-9332-47eb-b03f-63bdd49a9833\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"c24e4001-9332-47eb-b03f-63bdd49a9833\\":\\"SC-23(5)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Reliance on certificate authorities (CAs) for the establishment of secure sessions includes, for example, the use of Secure Socket Layer (SSL) and/or Transport Layer Security (TLS) certificates. These certificates, after verification by the respective certificate authorities, facilitate the establishment of protected sessions between web clients and web servers."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0147",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Restrict incoming communication traffic",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall only allow incoming communications from authorised sources routed to authorised destinations.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"da224a4c-22c7-4d94-8f91-0d19bb5cd0fe\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"da224a4c-22c7-4d94-8f91-0d19bb5cd0fe\\":\\"SC-7(11)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This provides determinations that source and destination address pairs represent authorised/allowed communications. Such determinations can be based on several factors including, for example, the presence of source/destination address pairs in lists of authorised/allowed communications, the absence of address pairs in lists of unauthorised/disallowed pairs, or meeting more general rules for authorised/allowed source/destination pairs."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0169",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use a central user rights and roles management",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use a centralised user rights and roles management system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"2356f631-00ce-409a-bb37-d1afc2a01929\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"2356f631-00ce-409a-bb37-d1afc2a01929\\":\\"TCA_ACCESS_0070\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0163",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Deny not explicitly allowed flows between external systems",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall deny all flows not explicitly allowed with an external system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"5ab1f181-d9ec-4903-bb87-84678046d153\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"5ab1f181-d9ec-4903-bb87-84678046d153\\":\\"TCA_EXT_COM_0030\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "04B02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Authentication of the entity for an incoming access from the Wide-area Network",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "04B02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there, for any access arriving from the Wide-area Network to the local area network, a mechanism controlling the authentication and access control rights of the accessing entity prior to any action?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the authentication mechanism provide a recognized strong level of security?\\r\\nNotably the usage of a simple password will always be a weakness. The only methods recognized as strong, that is to say observable without divulging information, are those based on cryptographic algorithms.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the security equipment that retains and uses reference data (secret elements) to support access authentication use mechanisms which guarantee inviolability and authenticity?\\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanisms used for the creation, modification and storage of reference elements (public keys in particular) must guarantee a level of security comparable to the authentication protocol itself.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the transmission between systems and security equipments of reference data (secret elements, secret or public keys, etc.) use mechanisms which guarantee inviolability and authenticity?\\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanisms used for the transmission of reference elements (public keys in particular) must guarantee a level of security comparable to the authentication protocol itself.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B02-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the management procedure of revoked keys systematically test that the keys have not been revoked?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B02-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the management procedure of revoked keys guarantee that the control systems take in consideration in real time any revocation?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B02-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes that guarantee authentication under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there is an audit at least once a year of the authentication procedures and processes.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0194",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Do not transmit passwords in clear text",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Passwords shall never be transmitted in clear text and their encryption shall be done using appropriate algorithms.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"dd60fb91-c654-4336-bae4-cca490e93ab5\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"dd60fb91-c654-4336-bae4-cca490e93ab5\\":\\"IA-5(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This does not apply when passwords are used to unlock hardware authenticators (e.g., Personal Identity Verification cards). Encrypted representations of passwords include, for example, encrypted versions of passwords and one-way cryptographic hashes of passwords."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0221",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce an unforgeable authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall detect and prevent the use of authentication data that has been copied or forged by any user.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e79e7cc0-7e61-4337-91c9-3628a57c80f2\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e79e7cc0-7e61-4337-91c9-3628a57c80f2\\":\\"12.4\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0174",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Permit \\"emergency\\" actions of unauthenticated user",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall allow some��[unauthenticated-actions] on behalf of the user to be performed before the user is authenticated.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"60abe0d2-4022-486d-a2b5-a5afaf1f18ae\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"60abe0d2-4022-486d-a2b5-a5afaf1f18ae\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "In some cases, several actions before authentication can be defined that permit users to execute several \\"emergency\\" or \\"recovery\\" actions. Such actions could be for example: trigger the password recovery procedure, notify a problem to the appropriate authority."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0354",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use cryptographic bidirectional authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall authenticate devices before establishing local/remote/network connection using a cryptographically based bidirectional authentication.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"808dfd05-b6f6-47c3-a866-2d00d46b7928\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"808dfd05-b6f6-47c3-a866-2d00d46b7928\\":\\"IA-3(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "A local connection is any connection with a device communicating without the use of a network. A network connection is any connection with a device that communicates through a network (e.g., local area or wide area network, Internet). A remote connection is any connection with a device communicating through an external network (e.g., the Internet). Bidirectional authentication provides stronger safeguards to validate the identity of other devices for connections that are of greater risk (e.g., remote connections)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0147",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Restrict incoming communication traffic",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall only allow incoming communications from authorised sources routed to authorised destinations.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"da224a4c-22c7-4d94-8f91-0d19bb5cd0fe\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"da224a4c-22c7-4d94-8f91-0d19bb5cd0fe\\":\\"SC-7(11)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This provides determinations that source and destination address pairs represent authorised/allowed communications. Such determinations can be based on several factors including, for example, the presence of source/destination address pairs in lists of authorised/allowed communications, the absence of address pairs in lists of unauthorised/disallowed pairs, or meeting more general rules for authorised/allowed source/destination pairs."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0121",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use tamperproof access control mechanisms",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use tamperproof access control mechanisms.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"729b71e9-e73e-43a1-a900-e4d1a69fce36\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"729b71e9-e73e-43a1-a900-e4d1a69fce36\\":\\"AC-25\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The tamperproof property of the access control mechanism prevents adversaries from compromising the functioning of the mechanism. This prevents adversaries from bypassing the mechanism and hence violating the security policy."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0191",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Multi-factor authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use multiple-factor authentication for the authentication of users in the system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"8d6e49b2-2296-43bd-958e-7e8ff8a75666\\":\\"ESA\\",\\"a619f297-154b-4319-9ec8-42a5073410f4\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"8d6e49b2-2296-43bd-958e-7e8ff8a75666\\":\\"GASF\\",\\"a619f297-154b-4319-9ec8-42a5073410f4\\":\\"12.4\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "That is, the system shall base authentication on at least two different authentication techniques (e.g. password based + token based)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0190",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Single-factor authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use single-factor authentication for the authentication of users in the system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"37dd9cc6-849d-47d0-91ba-f1ca76fd152e\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"37dd9cc6-849d-47d0-91ba-f1ca76fd152e\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0219",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prohibit the use of cached authenticators after time period",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prohibit the use of cached authenticators after [cache expiration time period].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e559d6c3-4729-4843-a624-7f75423ba602\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e559d6c3-4729-4843-a624-7f75423ba602\\":\\"IA-5(13)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0220",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Ensure strength of secrets",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "When authentication mechanisms are based on secrets, it shall be ensured that the secrets are of appropriate strength.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"3e56bc69-763d-434b-8fae-725f9af3b522\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"3e56bc69-763d-434b-8fae-725f9af3b522\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0130\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The authentication process may rely on a wide range of mechanisms, some of them requiring additional data only known by the user himself.\\nThis personal data are called secrets; it could be dongle, password, etc.\\nNB.: Secrets are not mandatory. Biometric data (eyes prints or fingerprints) could now be used to recognised users."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0175",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "User authentication before any action",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall require each user to be successfully authenticated before allowing any actions on behalf of that user.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"cec8065a-016f-42d2-b7f4-31783668455e\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"cec8065a-016f-42d2-b7f4-31783668455e\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0163",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Deny not explicitly allowed flows between external systems",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall deny all flows not explicitly allowed with an external system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"5ab1f181-d9ec-4903-bb87-84678046d153\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"5ab1f181-d9ec-4903-bb87-84678046d153\\":\\"TCA_EXT_COM_0030\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0343",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Device-to-device identification, authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall uniquely identify and authenticate devices/external systems/separated parts of the system before establishing a local/remote/network connection.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"7e63a97c-6fea-4d4f-94e1-dbed8a7dcb44\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"7e63a97c-6fea-4d4f-94e1-dbed8a7dcb44\\":\\"IA-3\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Devices requiring unique device-to-device identification and authentication may be defined by type, by device, or by a combination of type/device. Information systems typically use either shared known information (e.g., Media Access Control [MAC] or Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol [TCP/IP] addresses) for device identification or organizational authentication solutions (e.g., IEEE 802.1x and Extensible Authentication Protocol [EAP], Radius server with EAP-Transport Layer Security [TLS] authentication, Kerberos) to identify/authenticate devices on local and/or wide area networks.\\n\\nA local connection is any connection with a device communicating without the use of a network. A network connection is any connection with a device that communicates through a network (e.g., local area or wide area network, Internet). A remote connection is any connection with a device communicating through an external network (e.g., the Internet)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "04B03",\n          "index": "3",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Authentication of the entity accessed for an outgoing access across the Wide-area Network",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "04B03-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a mechanism for the authentication of the called entity before any outgoing access from the internal network across the Wide-area Network?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B03-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the authentication mechanism recognized as strong?\\r\\nThe only methods recognized as strong, that is to say observable without divulging information, are those based on cryptographic algorithms.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B03-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the security equipment that retains and uses reference data (secret elements) to support authentication use mechanisms which guarantee inviolability and authenticity?\\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanisms of modification, storage and transmission of reference elements (public keys in particular) must use a level of security comparable to the authentication protocol itself.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B03-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the transmission between equipments of reference data (secret elements) to support authentication use mechanisms which guarantee inviolability and authenticity?\\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanisms of transmission of reference elements (secret elements, public keys, etc.) must guarantee a level of security comparable to the authentication protocol itself.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04B03-05",\n              "index": "5",\n   