e single-factor authentication for the authentication of users in the system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"37dd9cc6-849d-47d0-91ba-f1ca76fd152e\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"37dd9cc6-849d-47d0-91ba-f1ca76fd152e\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0220",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Ensure strength of secrets",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "When authentication mechanisms are based on secrets, it shall be ensured that the secrets are of appropriate strength.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"3e56bc69-763d-434b-8fae-725f9af3b522\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"3e56bc69-763d-434b-8fae-725f9af3b522\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0130\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The authentication process may rely on a wide range of mechanisms, some of them requiring additional data only known by the user himself.\\nThis personal data are called secrets; it could be dongle, password, etc.\\nNB.: Secrets are not mandatory. Biometric data (eyes prints or fingerprints) could now be used to recognised users."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0163",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Deny not explicitly allowed flows between external systems",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall deny all flows not explicitly allowed with an external system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"5ab1f181-d9ec-4903-bb87-84678046d153\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"5ab1f181-d9ec-4903-bb87-84678046d153\\":\\"TCA_EXT_COM_0030\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0343",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Device-to-device identification, authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall uniquely identify and authenticate devices/external systems/separated parts of the system before establishing a local/remote/network connection.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"7e63a97c-6fea-4d4f-94e1-dbed8a7dcb44\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"7e63a97c-6fea-4d4f-94e1-dbed8a7dcb44\\":\\"IA-3\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Devices requiring unique device-to-device identification and authentication may be defined by type, by device, or by a combination of type/device. Information systems typically use either shared known information (e.g., Media Access Control [MAC] or Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol [TCP/IP] addresses) for device identification or organizational authentication solutions (e.g., IEEE 802.1x and Extensible Authentication Protocol [EAP], Radius server with EAP-Transport Layer Security [TLS] authentication, Kerberos) to identify/authenticate devices on local and/or wide area networks.\\n\\nA local connection is any connection with a device communicating without the use of a network. A network connection is any connection with a device that communicates through a network (e.g., local area or wide area network, Internet). A remote connection is any connection with a device communicating through an external network (e.g., the Internet)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        }\n      ],\n      "gasf": [],\n      "answers": {\n        "MEHARI_W": "",\n        "MEHARI_Min": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n        "MEHARI_Max": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n      },\n      "referenceObject": null,\n      "identifier": null,\n      "objType": "Audit",\n      "lockedBy": null\n    },\n    {\n      "category": "04C",\n      "index": "4",\n      "type": "CATEGORY",\n      "value": "Security during data exchanges and communication ",\n      "children": [\n        {\n          "category": "04C01",\n          "index": "1",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Encryption of exchanges on the Wide-area Network\\r\\nEncryption can be effected at layer 2 (encrypting modem ), 3 (IPSEC VPN) or at level 4-5 (SSL) or directly effected by the application (level 6-7, for example encryption before or during transmission), case really treated by domain 09 \\r\\nIt could be systematically on the pipeline (physical or logical) or limited only to certain data flows (as a function of address or type, etc.) it can also be performed on intermediate systems (VPN boxes) or end systems (stations, server) or both.",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "04C01-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have the permanent links and data exchanges which must be protected by encryption solutions been defined and such solutions been implemented on the Wide-area Network?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "10.1.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A10\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Cryptography\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A10.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Cryptographic controls\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"10.1.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Policy on the use of cryptographic controls\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "12.3.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04C01-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the encryption solution offer valid and solid guarantees and has it been approved by the Information Security Officer?  \\r\\nThe sufficient length of the key is one of among many parameters to take into consideration (as a function of the algorithm) . The recommendation of an official organization can be a confidence factor.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04C01-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do the procedure and mechanisms of storage, distribution and exchange of keys and more generally the management of the keys offer solid guarantees which merit confidence and are they approved by the Information Security Officer?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "10.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A10\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Cryptography\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A10.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Cryptographic controls\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"10.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Key management\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "12.3.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04C01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the encryption mechanisms embodied in electronic components which are strictly protected at a physical level against intrusion or change? \\r\\nEncryption mechanisms should be contained within protected enclosures to which it should be impossible to gain a",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04C01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is shutdown or by-pass of the encryption solution immediately detected and signaled to a team available 24 hrs a day capable of triggering an immediate reaction?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04C01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "In the case of inhibition or bypass of the encryption solution or the activation of an unprotected fail-over link of the network, is there a procedure to immediately alert all users?\\r\\nFor example by a warning requiring the user to acknowledge its receipt.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04C01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of all data exchange, encryption systems and associated procedures?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0357",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Define the security layer to be used",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Define if transport layer or message-layer security shall be used.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"1d9ecce3-6d45-4af7-9fe1-bbcb938e9747\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"1d9ecce3-6d45-4af7-9fe1-bbcb938e9747\\":\\"ASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0162",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Mutually authenticate with external systems prior any exchange",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Mutual system authentication, between parts of the system and any external systems, shall occur prior any data exchange.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"43cb6de3-aaae-403b-8515-b861993399a8\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"43cb6de3-aaae-403b-8515-b861993399a8\\":\\"TCA_EXT_COM_0040\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This is particularly important before the identification/authentication of a user."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0105",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Protect information during pre/post transmission handling",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall maintain the confidentiality and integrity of information during preparation for transmission and during reception.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"88cbbda5-6f4f-4234-9880-26f5584fa1b7\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"88cbbda5-6f4f-4234-9880-26f5584fa1b7\\":\\"SC-8(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Information can be either unintentionally or maliciously disclosed or modified during preparation for transmission or during reception including, for example, during aggregation, at protocol transformation points, and during packing/unpacking. These unauthorized disclosures or modifications compromise the confidentiality or integrity of the information."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0118",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Check data flow exchange plausibility",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The plausibility of data exchanged across different levels of security and/or between internal and external areas shall be checked according to the respective definitions of the data flows.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"92c7852f-7f08-4b4a-9610-5530e550184e\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"92c7852f-7f08-4b4a-9610-5530e550184e\\":\\"TCA_EXT_COM_0060\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0362",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Rely on MAC for integrity checks",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Integrity checks shall rely on cryptographic Message Authentication Code (MAC).",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"742a04a0-39b1-443d-a61c-96a88b3d0ef4\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\",\\"2d88fa39-57e7-465c-90bb-f3b25311e29c\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"742a04a0-39b1-443d-a61c-96a88b3d0ef4\\":\\"TCA_EXT_COM_0070\\",\\"2d88fa39-57e7-465c-90bb-f3b25311e29c\\":\\"SI-7(6)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0338",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Securely transmit your keys",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The transmission of sensitive keys shall be ensured over secure channel in accordance with a specified cryptographic key distribution method.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"a305c855-32f2-4782-bb99-ecba431ad57b\\":\\"ESA\\",\\"69bbcb32-7d46-4267-9636-8b7081c62579\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"a305c855-32f2-4782-bb99-ecba431ad57b\\":\\"ASF\\",\\"69bbcb32-7d46-4267-9636-8b7081c62579\\":\\"10.1\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0277",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Communication cryptography",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall protect the confidentiality, integrity and authentication of transmitted information using cryptographic means.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"6697d1a5-a5ed-47dc-9490-3c22aeb1e9f8\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"6697d1a5-a5ed-47dc-9490-3c22aeb1e9f8\\":\\"SC-8\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This applies to both internal and external networks. Organisations relying on commercial providers offering transmission services as commodity services rather than as fully dedicated services (i.e., services which can be highly specialized to individual customer needs), may find it difficult to obtain the necessary assurances regarding the implementation of needed security for transmission confidentiality/integrity. In such situations, organisations determine what types of confidentiality/integrity services are available in standard, commercial telecommunication service packages. If it is infeasible or impractical to obtain the necessary security through appropriate contracting vehicles, organisations implement appropriate compensating security controls or explicitly accept the additional risk."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0340",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Securely access your keys",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall ensure secure access to cryptographic keys.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"fce19c0c-a842-41d8-a3cc-0e387d8d4532\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"fce19c0c-a842-41d8-a3cc-0e387d8d4532\\":\\"10.1\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0164",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce information flow control policies between parts of a system",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall enforce a flow control policy to prevent the disclosure, modification, replay, loss of use of any data transmitted between separated parts of the system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"89f9178f-b582-4365-8292-d2fb29c142db\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"89f9178f-b582-4365-8292-d2fb29c142db\\":\\"TCA_INTER_COM_0010\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "It shall not be possible to bypass these flow control policy."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n         