      {\n              "category": "04C02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do the procedure and mechanisms for storage, distribution and exchange of keys and more generally the management of keys offer a sufficient level of confidence and have they been approved by the Information Security Officer?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04C02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the sealing mechanisms embodied in electronic components which are in turn strictly protected at a physical level against intrusion or change? \\r\\nSealing mechanisms should be contained within protected enclosures to which it should be impossible to gain access. The algorithm is contained within the microprocessor or a microprocessor card which is protected physically and logically.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04C02-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is shutdown or by-pass of the sealing solution immediately detected and signaled to a team available 24 hrs a day capable of triggering an immediate reaction?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04C02-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "In the case of inhibition or bypass of the sealing solution or the activation of an unprotected fail-over link, is there a procedure to immediately alert all users?\\r\\nFor example by a warning requiring the user to actively validate its receipt.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04C02-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of all systems of sealing of the data exchanged and associated procedures?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0162",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Mutually authenticate with external systems prior any exchange",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Mutual system authentication, between parts of the system and any external systems, shall occur prior any data exchange.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"43cb6de3-aaae-403b-8515-b861993399a8\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"43cb6de3-aaae-403b-8515-b861993399a8\\":\\"TCA_EXT_COM_0040\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This is particularly important before the identification/authentication of a user."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0105",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Protect information during pre/post transmission handling",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall maintain the confidentiality and integrity of information during preparation for transmission and during reception.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"88cbbda5-6f4f-4234-9880-26f5584fa1b7\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"88cbbda5-6f4f-4234-9880-26f5584fa1b7\\":\\"SC-8(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Information can be either unintentionally or maliciously disclosed or modified during preparation for transmission or during reception including, for example, during aggregation, at protocol transformation points, and during packing/unpacking. These unauthorized disclosures or modifications compromise the confidentiality or integrity of the information."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0065",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "User state synchrony protocol for distributed systems",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The distributed system shall ensure that the relevant parts of it know the correct status of transmitted data among its different parts, using acknowledgements.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"66d9ce29-eeb6-488b-8256-dd9343ba8f76\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"66d9ce29-eeb6-488b-8256-dd9343ba8f76\\":\\"15.9\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Distributed systems may give rise to greater complexity than monolithic systems through the potential for differences in state between parts of the system, and through delays in communication.\\nIn most cases synchronisation of state between distributed functions involves an exchange protocol.\\n\\nState synchrony protocol establishes the requirement for certain critical functions to use this trusted protocol and�ensures that two distributed parts of the system have synchronised their states after a security-relevant action."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0362",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Rely on MAC for integrity checks",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Integrity checks shall rely on cryptographic Message Authentication Code (MAC).",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"742a04a0-39b1-443d-a61c-96a88b3d0ef4\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\",\\"2d88fa39-57e7-465c-90bb-f3b25311e29c\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"742a04a0-39b1-443d-a61c-96a88b3d0ef4\\":\\"TCA_EXT_COM_0070\\",\\"2d88fa39-57e7-465c-90bb-f3b25311e29c\\":\\"SI-7(6)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0338",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Securely transmit your keys",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The transmission of sensitive keys shall be ensured over secure channel in accordance with a specified cryptographic key distribution method.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"a305c855-32f2-4782-bb99-ecba431ad57b\\":\\"ESA\\",\\"69bbcb32-7d46-4267-9636-8b7081c62579\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"a305c855-32f2-4782-bb99-ecba431ad57b\\":\\"ASF\\",\\"69bbcb32-7d46-4267-9636-8b7081c62579\\":\\"10.1\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0340",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Securely access your keys",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall ensure secure access to cryptographic keys.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"fce19c0c-a842-41d8-a3cc-0e387d8d4532\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"fce19c0c-a842-41d8-a3cc-0e387d8d4532\\":\\"10.1\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0164",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce information flow control policies between parts of a system",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall enforce a flow control policy to prevent the disclosure, modification, replay, loss of use of any data transmitted between separated parts of the system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"89f9178f-b582-4365-8292-d2fb29c142db\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"89f9178f-b582-4365-8292-d2fb29c142db\\":\\"TCA_INTER_COM_0010\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "It shall not be possible to bypass these flow control policy."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        }\n      ],\n      "gasf": [],\n      "answers": {\n        "MEHARI_W": "",\n        "MEHARI_Min": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n        "MEHARI_Max": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n      },\n      "referenceObject": null,\n      "identifier": null,\n      "objType": "Audit",\n      "lockedBy": null\n    },\n    {\n      "category": "04D",\n      "index": "4",\n      "type": "CATEGORY",\n      "value": "Control, Detection and Handling of incidents on the Wide-area Network ",\n      "children": [\n        {\n          "category": "04D01",\n          "index": "1",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Real-time monitoring of the Wide-area Network",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "04D01-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have events or successions of events which might reveal abnormal behavior or illicit action on the Wide-area Network been analyzed and, as a consequence, have specific monitoring points and indicators been established?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1; 16.1.4",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A16\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Information security incident management\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A16.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Management of information security incidents and improvements\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"16.1.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Assessment of and decision on information security events\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D01-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the system equipped with an automatic real time monitoring system in the case of an accumulation of abnormal events (for example unsuccessful connection attempts on non-open ports)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1; 16.1.4",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A16\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Information security incident management\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A16.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Management of information security incidents and improvements\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"16.1.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Assessment of and decision on information security events\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D01-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is use made of a system capable of detecting intrusion and anomalies on the Wide-area Network?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1; 16.1.4",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A16\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Information security incident management\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A16.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Management of information security incidents and improvements\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"16.1.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Assessment of and decision on information security events\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are there one or more applications capable of analyzing the individual anomaly diagnostic data on the Wide-area Network and of triggering an alert to operational personnel?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there within operational personnel a permanent dedicated team or group capable of reacting in the case of a monitoring alert on the Wide-area Network?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "For each case of alert has the expected response from the intervention team been defined and is the availability of the intervention team sufficient to face this expectation?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the parameters defining alarms strictly protected (restricted access rights and strict authentication ) against illicit modification?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the inhibition of an alert system on the Wide-area Network, trigger an alarm with the surveillance team?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D01-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the elements which enable the detection of an anomaly or incident archived (on disk, cassette or optical disk etc.)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protection of log information\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D01-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the procedures for monitoring the Wide-area Network, for the detection of the anomalies and the reactivity of the surveillance team subject to regular audit?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0146",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Detect and audit outgoing threatening communication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall detect and deny outgoing communications traffic posing a threat to external information systems.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"17810fc7-2341-4e1e-ad4a-ca63996fa5a6\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"17810fc7-2341-4e1e-ad4a-ca63996fa5a6\\":\\"SC-7(9)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Detecting outgoing communications traffic from internal actions that may pose threats to external information systems is sometimes termed extrusion detection. Extrusion detection at information system boundaries as part of managed interfaces includes the analysis of incoming and outgoing communications traffic searching for indications of internal threats to the security of external systems. Such threats include, for example, traffic indicative of denial of service attacks and traffic containing malicious code."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0081",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Monitor inbound and outbound communication traffic",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall monitor inbound and outbound communications traffic for unusual or unauthorized activities or conditions.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"7474b658-060f-4281-bc52-6489a3a88972\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"7474b658-060f-4281-bc52-6489a3a88972\\":\\"SI-4(4)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Unusual/unauthorized activities or conditions related to information system inbound and outbound communications traffic include, for example, internal traffic that indicates the presence of malicious code within organizational information systems or propagating among system components, the unauthorized exporting of information, or signalling to external information systems. Evidence of malicious code is used to identify potentially compromised information systems or information system components.\\n\\nThis requirement can be covered using HIDS and/or NIDS (Host or Network Intrusion Detection Systems)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0092",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Take action on audit processing failures",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall be able to take the [appropriate action] when an audit processing failure is detected.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"64d4d890-6df1-4492-84d5-5f59776950a2\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"64d4d890-6df1-4492-84d5-5f59776950a2\\":\\"AU-5\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The followings are examples of action: shut down information system, overwrite oldest audit records, stop generating audit records.\\nOrganisations may choose to define additional actions for different audit processing failures (e.g., by type, by location, by severity, or a combination of such factors). This applies to each audit data storage repository (i.e., distinct information system component where audit records are stored), the total audit storage capacity of organizations (i.e., all audit data storage repositories combined) or both."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0075",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Implement audit functions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Auditing functions shall be implemented and activated throughout the system.��The grades of activation of audit functions shall be adapted to the situation.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"1acf386b-d390-4fc9-804f-badda08fd526\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\",\\"bc15893f-b643-46dc-a512-9d7d04453657\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\",\\"245d894e-2887-4bb2-88cc-66b71c81745e\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"1acf386b-d390-4fc9-804f-badda08fd526\\":\\"A.10.10.1\\",\\"bc15893f-b643-46dc-a512-9d7d04453657\\":\\"AU-12\\",\\"245d894e-2887-4bb2-88cc-66b71c81745e\\":\\"TCA_LOG_GEN_0010\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This requirement ensure that auditing is activated throughout the system to assure that each relevant event is logged. Depending on the type of log and the system state, the auditing functions can be adapted (e.g. verbose mode, minimal audit).\\n\\nThe term \\"system\\" is used here to denote at least\\n- for all physically or logically separated assets and\\n- for all security application interaction across security classification boundaries.\\n\\nFurther involvement of separate applications can be introduced if agreed in the policy.\\nAudits records can be generated from many different information system components. Audited events are events for which audits are to be generated. These events are typically a subset of all events for which the information system is capable of generating audit records."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0095",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Alert on unusual/unauthorised activities",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall alert [incident response personnel (identified by name and/or by role)] when unusual / unauthorised activities are detected.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"d41bafc1-098a-4b5b-9fb0-3ca0de4b9364\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"d41bafc1-098a-4b5b-9fb0-3ca0de4b9364\\":\\"SI-4(5)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Alerts may be generated from a variety of sources, including, for example, audit records or inputs from malicious code protection mechanisms, intrusion detection or prevention mechanisms, or boundary protection devices such as firewalls, gateways, and routers. Alerts can be transmitted, for example, telephonically, by electronic mail messages, or by text messaging. Organisational personnel on the notification list can include, for example, system administrators, mission/business owners, system owners, or information system security officers."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0098",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Write audit trails to write-once media",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall write audit trails to hardware-enforced, write-once media.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e10d9790-203c-4463-a2a3-069b9ea4d9d6\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e10d9790-203c-4463-a2a3-069b9ea4d9d6\\":\\"AU-9(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This applies to the initial generation of audit trails (i.e., the collection of audit records that represents the audit information to be used for detection, analysis, and reporting purposes) and to the backup of those audit trails. It does not apply to the initial generation of audit records prior to being written to an audit trail. Write-once, read-many (WORM) media includes, for example, Compact Disk- Recordable (CD-R) and Digital Video Disk-Recordable (DVD-R). In contrast, the use of switchable write-protection media such as on tape cartridges or Universal Serial Bus (USB) drives results in write-protected, but not write-once, media."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "04D02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Offline analysis of traces, log files and event journals on the Wide-area Network ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "04D02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has detailed analysis been carried out of the events or succession of events on the Wide-area Network which may have had an impact on security (refused connections, re-routings, reconfigurations, changes in performance, access to sensitive data or tools etc.)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are these events recorded as well as the parameters used for their subsequent analysis?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there an application capable of analyzing these records as well as performance measures, of establishing statistics, a dashboard and anomaly diagnostics for examination by a competent team of specialists?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the structure empowered to analyze these summaries (or incidents logs and security related events) required to do so within a fixed and determined period and does it have sufficient availability?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D02-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has the expected response from the surveillance team been defined for each case of alert and are its availability and staffing level sufficient to meet these expectations?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D02-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the parameters defining the elements to record and the analysis to effect strictly protected against unauthorized change (limited rights and strong authentication)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protection of log information\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D02-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is any inhibition of the recording and processing system immediately signaled to the surveillance team?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D02-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the records and summary analysis protected against any destruction or modification?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protection of log information\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D02-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the records and summary analysis kept for a long period?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protection of log information\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D02-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the procedures for recording, processing and analyzing of the records and summaries as well as the availability of the analysis and corrective team subject to regular audit?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0083",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use standardised audit formats",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall produce a system-wide (logical or physical) audit trail composed of audit records in a standardized format.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"ce1b3722-b79e-4fa9-8801-afb30fc20cdd\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"ce1b3722-b79e-4fa9-8801-afb30fc20cdd\\":\\"AU-12(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Audit information that is normalised to common standards promotes interoperability and exchange of such information between dissimilar devices and information systems. This facilitates production of event information that can be more readily analysed and correlated. Standard formats for audit records include, for example, system log records and audit records compliant with Common Event Expressions (CEE). If logging mechanisms within information systems do not conform to standardised formats, systems may convert individual audit records into standardised formats when compiling system-wide audit trails."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0033",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Document relevant logs",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "All relevant logs that need to be analysed for the system shall be described on the CIG.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"73c9985c-dcfe-4fb3-b52a-22b7bdc92cc6\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"73c9985c-dcfe-4fb3-b52a-22b7bdc92cc6\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0076",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Produce audit logs",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Audit logs recording [audit record types] shall be produced and kept for an [agreed period].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"78ac7a48-3942-4371-8e2d-5e24e3c9daf3\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\",\\"5cf0c59f-4d27-464d-a2f6-9c9f2e3baad8\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\",\\"1b9396a8-1f4d-429c-9b40-54eb43cf5a85\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"78ac7a48-3942-4371-8e2d-5e24e3c9daf3\\":\\"A.10.10.1\\",\\"5cf0c59f-4d27-464d-a2f6-9c9f2e3baad8\\":\\"AU-12\\",\\"1b9396a8-1f4d-429c-9b40-54eb43cf5a85\\":\\"TCA_LOG_GEN_0010\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This shall be produced and kept to assist in future investigations and access control monitoring.\\nThe term \\"system\\" is used here to denote at least\\n- for all physically or logically separated assets and\\n- for all security�related applications (e.g. anti-virus software, intrusion detection/prevention software),\\n- for all application interaction across security classification boundaries.\\n\\nFurther involvement of separate applications can be introduced if agreed in the policy.\\nAudits records can be generated from many different information system components. Audited events are events for which audits are to be generated. These events are typically a subset of all events for which the information system is capable of generating audit records."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0100",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Cryptographically protect the integrity of audit trails",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall employ cryptographic mechanisms to protect the integrity of audit information and audit tools.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"80053bf0-c906-47e3-9779-eca784332197\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"80053bf0-c906-47e3-9779-eca784332197\\":\\"AU-9(3)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Cryptographic mechanisms used for protecting the integrity of audit information include, for example, signed hash functions using asymmetric cryptography enabling distribution of the public key to verify the hash information while maintaining the confidentiality of the secret key used to generate the hash."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "04D03",\n          "index": "3",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Management of incidents on the Wide-area Network",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "04D03-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a hot-line charged with taking and recording calls related to the Wide-area Network and to escalate all incidents?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1; 16.1.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A16\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Information security incident management\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A16.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Management of information security incidents and improvements\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"16.1.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Response to information security incidents\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.5"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D03-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is this hot-line team available 24 hours a day?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1; 16.1.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A16\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Information security incident management\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A16.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Management of information security incidents and improvements\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"16.1.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Response to information security incidents\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.5"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "04D03-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a system to support incident management?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1; 16.1.5",\n