	(683, '5', 'MEHARI_LAN', 'QUESTIONNAIRE', '05', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '{\n  "category": "05",\n  "index": "5",\n  "type": "MEHARI_LAN",\n  "questions": [\n    {\n      "category": "05A",\n      "index": "5",\n      "type": "CATEGORY",\n      "value": "Security of the architecture of the local area network",\n      "children": [\n        {\n          "category": "05A01",\n          "index": "1",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Partitioning of the local area network into security domains ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "05A01-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has a partitioning of the local area network been effected in order to separate what is strictly the internal network from the areas which communicate externally (DMZ)?\\r\\nA DMZ, or demilitarized zone, is an exchange zone to the outside, isolated from the internal network (e.g. using a firewall).",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A01-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has the local area network been partitioned into security domains, each requiring a consistent set of security rules, and into zones of confidence within which controls may be specifically adapted?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO1