        "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A13\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Communications security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A13.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Network security management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"13.1.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation in networks\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.4.5"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a complete description of the links and communication equipment in place?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "13.1.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A13\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Communications security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A13.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Network security management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"13.1.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation in networks\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.4.5"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is each domain isolated from the others domains, by using specific security means (filtering router, firewall, etc)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "13.1.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A13\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Communications security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A13.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Network security management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"13.1.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation in networks\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.4.5; 11.4.6"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the security proper to this filtering equipment subject to active maintenance and follow-up by an appropriate expert?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "For each of the domains, has a strictly limited list of authorized inter-domain links, communications and protocols been defined and, by default, are all other protocols shut off (nothing except policy)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.4.6"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A01-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a procedure for the management of inter-domain connection requests and a group in charge of the analysis of these requests, of their authorization and the definition of filtering rules which will be put in place (firewall, service requests, protocols etc.)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A01-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a group in charge of controlling the application of the defined rules and the removal of specific rights when the requirement is no longer needed or the conditions are no longer met?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A01-11",\n              "index": "11",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are any addition to the authorized connection list for a domain and any modification of its parameters logged and audited?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A01-12",\n              "index": "12",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular review of all authorized connections (standard and non-standard) and of their pertinence?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.4.7"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0154",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Employ boundary protection for missions and business functions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Boundary protection mechanisms shall be employed to separate information system components directly supporting missions and/or business functions.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"dd4e6e38-6e66-41eb-8344-ccf3865b09c1\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"dd4e6e38-6e66-41eb-8344-ccf3865b09c1\\":\\"SC-7(21)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Such isolation limits unauthorized information flows among system components and also provides the opportunity to deploy greater levels of protection for selected components. Separating system components with boundary protection mechanisms provides the capability for increased protection of individual components and to more effectively control information flows between those components. This type of enhanced protection limits the potential harm from cyber-attacks and errors. The degree of separation provided varies depending upon the mechanisms chosen. Boundary protection mechanisms include, for example, routers, gateways, and firewalls separating system components into physically separate networks or sub-networks, cross-domain devices separating sub-networks, and encrypting information flows among system components using distinct encryption keys."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0252",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use hardware separation to facilitate process isolation",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall implement underlying hardware separation mechanisms to facilitate process separation.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"4302252b-5e7a-42d8-9f63-a7995ce3dfc3\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"4302252b-5e7a-42d8-9f63-a7995ce3dfc3\\":\\"SC-39(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Hardware-based separation of information system processes is generally less susceptible to compromise than software-based separation, thus providing greater assurance that the separation will be enforced. Underlying hardware separation mechanisms include, for example, hardware memory management."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0041",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Define assumptions on system environment",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The assumptions on system environment shall be aligned to the CIG.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"52ffdf1f-b216-4b44-963c-42ef3dcb8a33\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"52ffdf1f-b216-4b44-963c-42ef3dcb8a33\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "E.g. deployment environment (physical and logical location), network, user access, ..."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0145",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Route outgoing traffic through authenticated proxies",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall route internal communications traffic to external networks through authenticated proxy servers at managed interfaces.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"8f16cb65-4347-4870-95be-5abf3ca85bd1\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"8f16cb65-4347-4870-95be-5abf3ca85bd1\\":\\"SC-7(8)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "External networks are networks outside of organisational control. A proxy server is a server (i.e., information system or application) that acts as an intermediary for clients requesting information system resources (e.g., files, connections, web pages, or services) from other organizational servers. Client requests established through an initial connection to the proxy server are evaluated to manage complexity and to provide additional protection by limiting direct connectivity. Web content filtering devices are one of the most common proxy servers providing access to the Internet. Proxy servers support logging individual Transmission Control Protocol (TCP) sessions and blocking specific Uniform Resource Locators (URLs), domain names, and Internet Protocol (IP) addresses. Web proxies can be configured with organization-defined lists of authorized and unauthorized websites."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0150",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce adherence to protocol formats",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall enforce adherence to protocol formats.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"9b9546d0-4436-4012-ad7c-73979a161c5f\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"9b9546d0-4436-4012-ad7c-73979a161c5f\\":\\"SC-7(17)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Information system components that enforce protocol formats include, for example, deep packet inspection firewalls and XML gateways. Such system components verify adherence to protocol formats/specifications (e.g., IEEE) at the application layer and identify significant vulnerabilities that cannot be detected by devices operating at the network or transport layers."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0159",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Authenticate physically separated parts prior any exchange",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Physically or logically separated parts of the system shall authenticate each other prior any exchange.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e3bb7ed1-699b-4ad6-b96b-4066f8f9821e\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e3bb7ed1-699b-4ad6-b96b-4066f8f9821e\\":\\"TCA_INTER_COM_0050\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0155",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Separate different security domains in separate subnets",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall implement/use separate network addresses (i.e., different subnets) to connect to systems in different security domains.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"0ec5db09-b18d-4fdb-8db4-4558b5784027\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"0ec5db09-b18d-4fdb-8db4-4558b5784027\\":\\"SC-7(22)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Decomposition of information systems into subnets helps to provide the appropriate level of protection for network connections to different security domains containing information with different security categories or classification levels."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0254",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Deploy system/software in an isolated network",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system/software shall be deployed in an isolated network.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"d0f2ffde-73ef-4582-9b29-832d85dc2abc\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"d0f2ffde-73ef-4582-9b29-832d85dc2abc\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0052",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Provide alternative security mechanisms",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Alternative or supplemental security mechanisms shall be employed for satisfying security functions when the primary means of implementing the security function is unavailable or compromised.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"9900f961-ceb7-404c-98af-fe7f92440b14\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"9900f961-ceb7-404c-98af-fe7f92440b14\\":\\"CP-13\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This supports information system resiliency and contingency planning/continuity of operations. To ensure mission/business continuity, organizations can implement alternative or supplemental security mechanisms. These mechanisms may be less effective than the primary mechanisms (e.g., not as easy to use, not as scalable, or not as secure). However, having the capability to readily employ these alternative/supplemental mechanisms enhances overall mission/business continuity that might otherwise be adversely impacted if organizational operations had to be curtailed until the primary means of implementing the functions was restored. Given the cost and level of effort required to provide such alternative capabilities, this control would typically be applied only to critical security capabilities provided by information systems, system components, or information system services. For example, an organization may issue to senior executives and system administrators one-time pads in case multifactor tokens, the organization\'s standard means for secure remote authentication, is compromised."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0153",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Permit to dynamically isolate/segregate system components",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall provide the capability to dynamically isolate/segregate information system components from other components of the system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"bc438381-168b-4d08-ab83-d6fc21441ffa\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"bc438381-168b-4d08-ab83-d6fc21441ffa\\":\\"SC-7(20)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The capability to dynamically isolate or segregate certain internal components of organizational information systems is useful when it is necessary to partition or separate certain components of dubious origin from those components possessing greater trustworthiness. Component isolation reduces the attack surface of organizational information systems. Isolation of selected information system components is also a means of limiting the damage from successful cyber-attacks when those attacks occur."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "05A02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Security of the functioning of the local area network architecture",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has each security domain been analyzed to determine the requirements of continuity of service and, if necessary, has redundancy been incorporated into interconnection points, networking equipment and meshed links?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has a systematic analysis of potential single points of failure been carried out in order to ensure that service equipments (such as energy supply, air conditioning, etc.) do not affect the redundancy planned for network equipment or architecture? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has a control of the average and peak load been carried out for each element of the network and of the compatibility of the network and associated equipment at this load level and is this control regularly repeated?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has this analysis been complemented by a study of network capacity to ensure reliability of communications even in the case of failure of a single link or piece of equipment?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a dynamic measurement of network load and of the load balancing tools?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do network monitoring and reconfiguration tools allow real time corrective action compatible with the requirements of the users?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the architecture of network equipment allow easy adaptation to changes of load levels (clusters, load balancing etc.)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are overload detection and load balancing appliances and devices accessible only by administrators and is their access protected by strengthened access control?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is any inhibition or shutdown of network overload detection and load balancing equipment signaled immediately to the monitoring center or to network administrators?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are regular performance tests of detection and reconfiguration mechanisms carried out?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-11",\n              "index": "11",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are regular audits of the parameterization of detection and reconfiguration systems carried out?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A02-12",\n              "index": "12",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are regular audits carried out of procedures associated with the detection and reconfiguration systems?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0154",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Employ boundary protection for missions and business functions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Boundary protection mechanisms shall be employed to separate information system components directly supporting missions and/or business functions.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"dd4e6e38-6e66-41eb-8344-ccf3865b09c1\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"dd4e6e38-6e66-41eb-8344-ccf3865b09c1\\":\\"SC-7(21)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Such isolation limits unauthorized information flows among system components and also provides the opportunity to deploy greater levels of protection for selected components. Separating system components with boundary protection mechanisms provides the capability for increased protection of individual components and to more effectively control information flows between those components. This type of enhanced protection limits the potential harm from cyber-attacks and errors. The degree of separation provided varies depending upon the mechanisms chosen. Boundary protection mechanisms include, for example, routers, gateways, and firewalls separating system components into physically separate networks or sub-networks, cross-domain devices separating sub-networks, and encrypting information flows among system components using distinct encryption keys."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0051",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Provide alternative communication protocols",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall provide and alternate communication protocol in support of maintaining continuity of operations.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"85e6863e-d22c-4c8d-a187-6d020bf31b3d\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"85e6863e-d22c-4c8d-a187-6d020bf31b3d\\":\\"CP-11\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Alternate communications protocols increase the resilience of information systems. Alternate communications protocols include, for example, switching from Transmission Control Protocol to User Datagram Protocol communications or to a special purpose protocol used in conjunction with the Internet Protocol. Switching communications protocols may affect software applications and therefore, the potential side effects of introducing alternate communications protocols are analysed prior to implementation."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0151",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Fail securely on boundary protection devices",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall fail securely in the event of an operational failure of a boundary protection device.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"c91fa834-a3bc-4377-93be-d01d8b5ed2ca\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"c91fa834-a3bc-4377-93be-d01d8b5ed2ca\\":\\"SC-7(18)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Fail secure is a condition achieved by employing information system mechanisms to ensure that in the event of operational failures of boundary protection devices at managed interfaces (e.g., routers, firewalls, guards, and application gateways residing on protected sub networks commonly referred to as demilitarized zones), information systems do not enter into unsecure states where intended security properties no longer hold. Failures of boundary protection devices cannot lead to, or cause information external to the devices to enter the devices, nor can failures permit unauthorized information releases."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0150",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce adherence to protocol formats",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall enforce adherence to protocol formats.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"9b9546d0-4436-4012-ad7c-73979a161c5f\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"9b9546d0-4436-4012-ad7c-73979a161c5f\\":\\"SC-7(17)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Information system components that enforce protocol formats include, for example, deep packet inspection firewalls and XML gateways. Such system components verify adherence to protocol formats/specifications (e.g., IEEE) at the application layer and identify significant vulnerabilities that cannot be detected by devices operating at the network or transport layers."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0159",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Authenticate physically separated parts prior any exchange",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Physically or logically separated parts of the system shall authenticate each other prior any exchange.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e3bb7ed1-699b-4ad6-b96b-4066f8f9821e\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e3bb7ed1-699b-4ad6-b96b-4066f8f9821e\\":\\"TCA_INTER_COM_0050\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0258",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prevent display of management-related functionalities to non-privileged users",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prevent the presentation of information system management-related functionality at an interface for non-privileged users.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"04da66df-bda0-46bc-a96c-c81933d27273\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"04da66df-bda0-46bc-a96c-c81933d27273\\":\\"SC-2(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This ensures that administration options (e.g., administrator privileges) are not available to general users (including prohibiting the use of the grey-out option commonly used to eliminate accessibility to such information). Such restrictions include, for example, not presenting administration options until users establish sessions with administrator privileges."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0052",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Provide alternative security mechanisms",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Alternative or supplemental security mechanisms shall be employed for satisfying security functions when the primary means of implementing the security function is unavailable or compromised.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"9900f961-ceb7-404c-98af-fe7f92440b14\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"9900f961-ceb7-404c-98af-fe7f92440b14\\":\\"CP-13\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This supports information system resiliency and contingency planning/continuity of operations. To ensure mission/business continuity, organizations can implement alternative or supplemental security mechanisms. These mechanisms may be less effective than the primary mechanisms (e.g., not as easy to use, not as scalable, or not as secure). However, having the capability to readily employ these alternative/supplemental mechanisms enhances overall mission/business continuity that might otherwise be adversely impacted if organizational operations had to be curtailed until the primary means of implementing the functions was restored. Given the cost and level of effort required to provide such alternative capabilities, this control would typically be applied only to critical security capabilities provided by information systems, system components, or information system services. For example, an organization may issue to senior executives and system administrators one-time pads in case multifactor tokens, the organization\'s standard means for secure remote authentication, is compromised."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "05A03",\n          "index": "3",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Organization of the maintenance of local area network equipment",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "05A03-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are all local area network equipments covered by a maintenance contract?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "11.2.4",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A11\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Physical and environmental security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A11.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Equipment\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"11.2.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Equipment maintenance\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "9.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "05A03-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have all equipment, critical to the provision of expected operation and performance of the network, been identified and, for each of them, have the required acceptable and maximum downtime delays been published?",\n              "chi