       "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C01-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have profiles been defined, as part of network operations, corresponding to each type of activity (equipment administration, the administration of security equipment, network management, management of backup medias and contents etc.)?  ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "6.1.2; 9.2.3;  9.2.5; 13.1.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A6\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Organization of information security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A6.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Internal organization\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"6.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation of duties\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of privileged access rights\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A13\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Communications security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A13.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Network security management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"13.1.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Network controls\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.1.3; 10.6.1; 11.2.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "For each profile have the necessary administrative rights been defined? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "6.1.2; 13.1.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A6\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Organization of information security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A6.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Internal organization\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"6.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation of duties\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A13\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Communications security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A13.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Network security management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"13.1.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Network controls\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.1.3; 10.6.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the process of attribution of administrative rights require the formal authorization of management (or the manager responsible for external service providers) at a sufficiently high level?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "6.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A6\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Organization of information security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A6.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Internal organization\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"6.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation of duties\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.1.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the process of attribution of administrative rights effected uniquely in relation to the profile of the holder?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "6.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A6\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Organization of information security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A6.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Internal organization\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"6.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation of duties\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.1.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the process of granting (modification or retraction) of special rights to an individual strictly controlled?\\r\\nA strict control requires a formal recognition of the signature (electronic or not) of the requester, that there be an access control in order to attribute or modify such rights and that any modification of special rights be logged and audited.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.3; 9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of privileged access rights\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a systematic process of removal of administrative rights at the time of departure or role change of staff?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C01-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of all administrative rights attributed ?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0128",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Only allow certificate authorities for verification of protected sessions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall only allow the installation of [certificate authorities] for verification of the establishment of protected sessions.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"c24e4001-9332-47eb-b03f-63bdd49a9833\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"c24e4001-9332-47eb-b03f-63bdd49a9833\\":\\"SC-23(5)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Reliance on certificate authorities (CAs) for the establishment of secure sessions includes, for example, the use of Secure Socket Layer (SSL) and/or Transport Layer Security (TLS) certificates. These certificates, after verification by the respective certificate authorities, facilitate the establishment of protected sessions between web clients and web servers."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0231",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce system access control policies",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall enforce the implementation of the [System Access Control Policy] to system appliances, objects, operation and data.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"824f2261-17da-436d-8a61-47b489684392\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\",\\"d1896fa0-c90f-40a4-ad1b-7f28052048e5\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"824f2261-17da-436d-8a61-47b489684392\\":\\"TCA_ACCESS_0010\\",\\"d1896fa0-c90f-40a4-ad1b-7f28052048e5\\":\\"AC-3\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0169",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use a central user rights and roles management",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use a centralised user rights and roles management system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"2356f631-00ce-409a-bb37-d1afc2a01929\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"2356f631-00ce-409a-bb37-d1afc2a01929\\":\\"TCA_ACCESS_0070\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0030",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Delete inactive accounts",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The contractor shall include the deletion of inactive accounts in the user account management documentation in the [host document].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"de51f0bb-ad01-47e3-b8a7-a5cd3a22ffd6\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"de51f0bb-ad01-47e3-b8a7-a5cd3a22ffd6\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_0020\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The old and inactive accounts should be deleted.\\nThis prevents illicit use of accounts by other users."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0264",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Restrict security attributes modification",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Modification of security attributes shall only be possible by specific, well-defined roles.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"b0f230da-0b0b-41b2-aac8-3ea2c049317f\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\",\\"ce3c8f56-af3d-4daf-bdb2-8202eae3b95a\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"b0f230da-0b0b-41b2-aac8-3ea2c049317f\\":\\"TCA_SEC_MNGT_0020\\",\\"ce3c8f56-af3d-4daf-bdb2-8202eae3b95a\\":\\"TCA_SEC_MNGT_0010\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Security attributes are all data that are used to configure the security features of the system."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0127",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Session unique identifiers",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall generate a unique session identifier for each session with [randomness requirements] and recognizes only session identifiers that are system-generated.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"54a61643-d0fe-4c0c-aecc-e9d6060b8022\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"54a61643-d0fe-4c0c-aecc-e9d6060b8022\\":\\"SC-23(3)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This curtails the ability of adversaries from reusing previously valid session IDs. Employing the concept of randomness in the generation of unique session identifiers helps to protect against brute-force attacks to determine future session identifiers."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0355",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Employ secure name/address resolution services",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall request and perform data origin authentication and data integrity verification on the name/address resolution responses that the system receives from authoritative sources.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"25ebe765-3d91-4658-8f37-56794ce81206\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\",\\"f9fe6b47-1b92-48cf-9ace-3be7d3ed08b6\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"25ebe765-3d91-4658-8f37-56794ce81206\\":\\"SC-21\\",\\"f9fe6b47-1b92-48cf-9ace-3be7d3ed08b6\\":\\"SC-20\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Each client of name resolution services either performs this validation on its own, or has authenticated channels to trusted validation providers. Information systems that provide name and address resolution services for local clients include, for example, recursive resolving or caching domain name system (DNS) servers. DNS client resolvers either perform validation of DNSSEC signatures, or clients use authenticated channels to recursive resolvers that perform such validations. Information systems that use technologies other than the DNS to map between host/service names and network addresses provide other means to enable clients to verify the authenticity and integrity of response data."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0258",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prevent display of management-related functionalities to non-privileged users",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prevent the presentation of information system management-related functionality at an interface for non-privileged users.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"04da66df-bda0-46bc-a96c-c81933d27273\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"04da66df-bda0-46bc-a96c-c81933d27273\\":\\"SC-2(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This ensures that administration options (e.g., administrator privileges) are not available to general users (including prohibiting the use of the grey-out option commonly used to eliminate accessibility to such information). Such restrictions include, for example, not presenting administration options until users establish sessions with administrator privileges."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "06C02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Authentication of administrators and operational personnel  ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "06C02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the process of authentication of network administrators or holders of administrative rights considered to be secure?\\r\\nAn authentication protocol is considered secure if it is not susceptible to being broken by a listening device on the network or rendered inoperable by specialists tools (in particular password crack tools). Such security usually uses cryptographic methods.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the rules, for instance in the case of passwords, considered to be very strict?\\r\\nStrict rules impose the use of tested non-trivial passwords and the use of a mixture of different types of character of a reasonable length (ten or more characters). It is desirable that such rules be decided or agreed upon by the CISO.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is a strong authentication used for the connection of administrators to the supervision system as well as for the connection of the supervision system to network equipments?\\r\\nIf the administrator connects to a hypervisor (such as HP OpenView, IBM TIVOLI, CA Unicenter, BMC Patrol or Bull OpenMaster) with secure authentication and effective access control, an equivalent level of security is needed for the objects that are managed (avoiding for example visible passwords, default public and community groups, access via telnet or simple SQL) in order to avoid malicious direct action on the equipment.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a consistent control of the administrator`s rights, of its context, and of the suitability of this context with the requested access, as per formal rules of access control?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C02-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are authentication parameters under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the list of people able to change authentication rules, the identifiers themselves and the rules for monitoring connection attempts be strictly limited, that there be a reinforced access control in order to be able to modify these rights and that any modification of these rights be logged and audited and that there be a general audit at least once a year of all authentication parameters.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C02-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are there processes that guarantee authentication under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there is an audit at least once a year of the authentication procedures and processes.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C02-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit of existing profiles having administrative rights?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C02-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit of the procedures for granting profiles and the security parameters protecting the profiles and the rights?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0354",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use cryptographic bidirectional authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall authenticate devices before establishing local/remote/network connection using a cryptographically based bidirectional authentication.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"808dfd05-b6f6-47c3-a866-2d00d46b7928\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"808dfd05-b6f6-47c3-a866-2d00d46b7928\\":\\"IA-3(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "A local connection is any connection with a device communicating without the use of a network. A network connection is any connection with a device that communicates through a network (e.g., local area or wide area network, Internet). A remote connection is any connection with a device communicating through an external network (e.g., the Internet). Bidirectional authentication provides stronger safeguards to validate the identity of other devices for connections that are of greater risk (e.g., remote connections)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "06C03",\n          "index": "3",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Surveillance of administrative actions on the network ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "06C03-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has a detailed analysis been carried out of the operations performed with administrative rights which may potentially have an impact on network security (configuration of security systems, access to sensitive information, usage of sensitive tools, download or modification of administrative tools etc.)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.3; 13.1.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Administrator and operator logs\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A13\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Communications security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A13.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Network security management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"13.1.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Network controls\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.4; 10.6.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "06C03-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are all these events recorded on a log file as well as all parameters required for their subsequent analysis?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_IS