	(902, '6', 'Security of operations procedures ', 'CATEGORY', '06A', '06', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(903, '1', 'Security in the relationship with operational personnel (employees, suppliers or service providers)', 'CATEGORY', '06A01', '06A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(904, '1', 'Is there a security policy specifically aimed at operational network personnel covering all the aspects of information security (confidentiality of information, service and information availability, integrity of information and configurations, trace ability, etc. )?  ', 'QUESTION', '06A01-01', '06A01', '4', '1', '', 'E1', '', '', NULL),
	(905, '2', 'Is operational network personnel required to sign contract clauses of adherence to that security policy (no matter their status: permanent or temporary staff, students, etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '06A01-02', '06A01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(906, '3', 'Do these clauses make clear that the obligation to respect security applies to all information no matter what the medium is (paper, magnetic, optical, etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '06A01-03', '06A01', '2', '2', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(907, '4', 'Do these clauses make clear, if necessary and legally possible, that the obligation to respect the security policy applies without limitation in time? \r\nThis applies, in particular, to the clauses concerning confidentiality, they may (and often must) continue after the end of the contract linking (directly or indirectly) the employee or  service provider or partner to the company', 'QUESTION', '06A01-04', '06A01', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(908, '5', 'Do these clauses make clear that the personnel has an obligation not to tolerate any action contrary to security from other people?', 'QUESTION', '06A01-05', '06A01', '4', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(909, '6', 'Does the signature of these clauses represent a formal commitment?\r\nIn order to achieve a formal commitment, the personnel should explicitly state that his/her signature implies having understood and accepted the security policy', 'QUESTION', '06A01-06', '06A01', '4', '3', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(910, '7', 'Are these same clauses obligatory for contractors working on network operations?\r\nPractically, the contractors should ensure that their personnel sign individually and explicitly under the same conditions than internal staff.', 'QUESTION', '06A01-07', '06A01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(911, '8', 'Is there a mandatory and well adapted training course aimed at network operations personnel?', 'QUESTION', '06A01-08', '06A01', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(912, '9', 'Are the confidentiality agreements, signed by personnel, securely kept (at least in a locked cupboard )?  ', 'QUESTION', '06A01-09', '06A01', '2', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(913, '10', 'Are the confidentiality agreements, signed by external contractors, securely kept (at least in a locked cupboard )?  ', 'QUESTION', '06A01-10', '06A01', '2', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(914, '11', 'Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of the effective application of the signature procedure by  operational personnel (directly employed by the company or indirectly through a service company)?', 'QUESTION', '06A01-11', '06A01', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(915, '2', 'Control of the implementation or upgrade of software or hardware ', 'CATEGORY', '06A02', '06A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(916, '1', 'Is there a control procedure for change decisions, equipment and system evolutions (registration, planning, formal approbation, communication to all concerned individuals, etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-01', '06A02', '2', '2', '', 'E1', '12.1.2', '10.1.2', NULL),
	(917, '2', 'Are the change decisions based on an analysis of the capacity of the new equipment and systems in ensuring the required load taking into account the evolution of foreseeable requests?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-02', '06A02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.3', '10.3.1', NULL),
	(918, '3', 'Do the installations take into account physical protection (protected access, no direct external view to equipments, absence of physical threats, climate conditions, protection against thunderbolts, protection against dust, etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-03', '06A02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '11.2.1', '9.2.1', NULL),
	(919, '4', 'Is there a definite review, involving Information Security Office personnel, of the potential risks related to functional changes associated to each new or revised network software or equipment?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-04', '06A02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.5.1; 14.2.9', '12.4.1; 10.3.2', NULL),
	(920, '5', 'Does this review contain an analysis of the risks that may arise from these functional changes?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-05', '06A02', '2', '2', '', 'E2', '12.5.1; 14.2.9', '12.4.1; 10.3.2', NULL),
	(921, '6', 'Has operational staff received specific formal training in risk analysis?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-06', '06A02', '1', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(922, '7', 'Does operational staff obtain appropriate advice when needed?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-07', '06A02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(923, '8', 'Are security measures, to be implemented to counter any new risks identified, subject to formal review and control before start of production?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-08', '06A02', '4', '', '', 'E2', '14.2.9', '10.3.2', NULL),
	(924, '9', 'Are security parameters and configuration rules (removal of all generic accounts, changing of generic passwords, closure of all ports not specifically requested and authorized, access control and authentication parameters, control of routing tables etc.) detailed and kept up to date and are they reviewed before any start of production of a new version?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-09', '06A02', '4', '', '', 'E2', '14.2.9', '11.4.4; 10.3.2', NULL),
	(925, '10', 'Are the security parameters and configuration rules controlled before any new version is installed and operated? ', 'QUESTION', '06A02-10', '06A02', '4', '', '', 'E2', '14.2.9', '11.4.4; 10.3.2', NULL),
	(926, '11', 'Is it considered the possible impact over the continuity plans due the system changes?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-11', '06A02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '14.2.9', '10.3.2', NULL),
	(927, '12', 'Are any exemptions from the prior risk analysis and control of security parameters subject to strict procedures requiring the signature of a senior manager?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-12', '06A02', '4', '', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(928, '13', 'Is the start of production of new equipment or software only possible by operational staff?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-13', '06A02', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '12.5.1', '12.4.1; 6.1.4', NULL),
	(929, '14', 'Is the start of production of new equipment or software only possible following a defined validation and authorization process?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-14', '06A02', '2', '3', '', 'E3', '12.5.1', '12.4.1; 6.1.4', NULL),
	(930, '15', 'Are all the control procedures related to start of production subject to regular audit?', 'QUESTION', '06A02-15', '06A02', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(931, '3', 'Control of maintenance operations ', 'CATEGORY', '06A03', '06A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(932, '1', 'Is it kept a trace of all maintenance operations?', 'QUESTION', '06A03-01', '06A03', '1', '', '', 'E2', '11.2.4', '9.2.4', NULL),
	(933, '2', 'Are all maintenance operations required to terminate with a systematic verification of all security parameters (as defined at the start of production)?  ', 'QUESTION', '06A03-02', '06A03', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(934, '3', 'Are all maintenance operations required to terminate with a systematic verification of security log files parameters (events to be recorded, context of events to be recorded, duration of retention, etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '06A03-03', '06A03', '4', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(935, '4', 'Are all maintenance operations required to terminate with a systematic verification of administration control parameters (necessary profile, authentication type, removal of standard logins, etc.)?  ', 'QUESTION', '06A03-04', '06A03', '4', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(936, '5', 'Is a formal exemption, signed by a responsible manager, required if the above mentioned procedures are not observed? ', 'QUESTION', '06A03-05', '06A03', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '14.2.9', NULL),
	(937, '6', 'Is the totality of start of production (after maintenance) control procedures regularly audited?', 'QUESTION', '06A03-06', '06A03', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '14.2.9', NULL),
	(938, '4', 'Control of Remote Maintenance ', 'CATEGORY', '06A04', '06A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(939, '1', 'In the case of remote maintenance, is there a secure authentication procedure of the remote maintenance center?', 'QUESTION', '06A04-01', '06A04', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '11.4.4', NULL),
	(940, '2', 'In the case of remote maintenance is there a secure authentication procedure for maintenance personnel? ', 'QUESTION', '06A04-02', '06A04', '4', '', '2', 'E2', '', '11.4.4', NULL),
	(941, '3', 'Is there a set of procedures covering the attribution of access rights for a new maintenance operative, the revocation of rights and the attribution of rights in emergency situations? ', 'QUESTION', '06A04-03', '06A04', '2', '', '', 'E3', '', '11.4.4', NULL),
	(942, '4', 'Have the procedures and protocols for the exchange and storage of secret data etc., been approved by the Information Security Officer or a specialized organization? ', 'QUESTION', '06A04-04', '06A04', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(943, '5', 'Does the usage of the remote maintenance line require the prior agreement (for each usage) of operational personnel (following the provider`s request specifying the nature, date and time of the intervention )?  ', 'QUESTION', '06A04-05', '06A04', '4', '', '', 'E2', '', '11.4.4', NULL),
	(944, '6', 'Is the equipment allocated for remote maintenance protected against inhibition or modification of access conditions, resulting in the triggering of an alarm? ', 'QUESTION', '06A04-06', '06A04', '2', '2', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(945, '7', 'Are all the control procedures for remote maintenance regularly audited?', 'QUESTION', '06A04-07', '06A04', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(946, '5', 'Management of Operating Procedures for Network Operation', 'CATEGORY', '06A05', '06A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(947, '1', 'Do the network operating  procedure result from the study of the overall cases to be covered by said procedure (normal operating cases and incidents)?', 'QUESTION', '06A05-01', '06A05', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.1', '10.1.1', NULL),
	(948, '2', 'Are the operating procedures documented and kept up to date?', 'QUESTION', '06A05-02', '06A05', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.1', '10.1.1', NULL),
	(949, '3', 'Are these operating procedures readily available upon request by any accredited individual?', 'QUESTION', '06A05-03', '06A05', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.1; 15.2.1', '10.1.1', NULL),
	(950, '4', 'Does the Management approve changes to procedures ?', 'QUESTION', '06A05-04', '06A05', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.1; 15.2.1', '10.1.1', NULL),
	(951, '5', 'Are these procedures protected from unauthorized alterations?', 'QUESTION', '06A05-05', '06A05', '2', '', '', 'R1', '15.2.1', '', NULL),
	(952, '6', 'Are the operating procedures audited regularly for authenticity and relevance?', 'QUESTION', '06A05-06', '06A05', '2', '', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(953, '6', 'Management of service providers relating to networks', 'CATEGORY', '06A06', '06A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(954, '1', 'Is it ensured regularly that the network security services allocated to suppliers or service providers are efficiently implemented and maintained by them?', 'QUESTION', '06A06-01', '06A06', '4', '', '', 'C1', '12.6.1', '10.2.1', NULL),
	(955, '2', 'Is it ensured that the above suppliers have efficiently prepared the appropriate arrangements to ensure that the services are provided as agreed?', 'QUESTION', '06A06-02', '06A06', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.6.1', '10.2.1', NULL),
	(956, '3', 'Is the respect of the security provisions by the suppliers or service providers under control and regularly reviewed?', 'QUESTION', '06A06-03', '06A06', '4', '', '', 'E1', '12.6.1', '10.2.2', NULL),
	(957, '4', 'Is it ensured that the suppliers report and document any security incident concerning information or networks?', 'QUESTION', '06A06-04', '06A06', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.6.1', '10.2.2', NULL),
	(958, '5', 'Is there a regular review of these incidents or malfunctions with the concerned suppliers?', 'QUESTION', '06A06-05', '06A06', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.6.1', '10.2.2', NULL),
	(959, '6', 'Are any changes in the contract relationship (e.g. Mandatory duties, service levels) analyzed for impact on resulting potential risks?', 'QUESTION', '06A06-06', '06A06', '2', '', '', 'E3', '15.2.2', '10.2.3', NULL),
	(960, '7', 'Taking into account the confidentiality during maintenance operations on network equipment.', 'CATEGORY', '06A07', '06A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(961, '1', 'Is there a procedure describing in detail the operations to execute before conducting maintenance thus avoiding their access to critical data (encryption keys, network protection, equipment security configuration, etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '06A07-01', '06A07', '4', '', '', 'E2', '11.2.4; 11.2.7', '9.2.6; 9.2.4', NULL),
	(962, '2', 'Is there a procedure or a contractual provision regarding the maintenance personnel (internal and external) specifying that any support containing sensitive information must be wiped out before its disposal?', 'QUESTION', '06A07-02', '06A07', '4', '', '', 'E2', '11.2.4', '9.2.4', NULL),
	(963, '3', 'Is there a systems` integrity verification procedure after a maintenance is conducted (no spyware, no Trojan horse, etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '06A07-03', '06A07', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(964, '4', 'Is a formal exemption, signed by a responsible manager, required if the above mentioned procedures are not observed? ', 'QUESTION', '06A07-04', '06A07', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(965, '5', 'Are the above procedures regularly audited?', 'QUESTION', '06A07-05', '06A07', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(966, '8', 'Contract Management of Network Services', 'CATEGORY', '06A08', '06A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(967, '1', 'Have service levels been identified for each network service?\r\nService levels apply not only to the services rendered to users, but also the security features required and the commitments of each party involved. ', 'QUESTION', '06A08-01', '06A08', '4', '', '', 'E1', '13.1.2', '10.6.2', NULL),
	(968, '2', 'Have these service levels been included in a contractual agreement  (whatever the services are ensured internally or by an external provider)?', 'QUESTION', '06A08-02', '06A08', '4', '', '', 'E2', '13.1.2', '10.6.2', NULL),
	(969, '3', 'Does Management control the application of corresponding measures?', 'QUESTION', '06A08-03', '06A08', '2', '', '', 'C1', '13.1.2', '10.6.2', NULL),
	(970, '6', 'Parameters setting and control of hardware and software configurations', 'CATEGORY', '06B', '06', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(971, '1', 'Network equipment customizing and compliance control of configurations', 'CATEGORY', '06B01', '06B', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(972, '1', 'Is there a document or set of documents or an operational procedure detailing all security parameters for network equipment? which is derived from the network protection policy and determined filtering rules?\r\nSuch a document must result from the network protection policy and describe the filtering rules decided. It should also state the reference versions of the  systems so it is possible to check the status of the updates.', 'QUESTION', '06B01-01', '06B01', '4', '2', '', 'E1', '', '', NULL),
	(973, '2', 'Does this document (or documents) require the removal of all generic or by default accounts and does it detail the list of such accounts?  ', 'QUESTION', '06B01-02', '06B01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(974, '3', 'Does this document or procedure impose a synchronization feature, based on a reliable time reference?', 'QUESTION', '06B01-03', '06B01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.4', '10.10.6', NULL),
	(975, '4', 'Are these parameters set and updated regularly in line with latest information and in cooperation with expert authorities (specialized audits, subscription to a service center, regular consultation with CERTs, etc.)?\r\nCERT : Computer Emergency Response Team.', 'QUESTION', '06B01-04', '06B01', '2', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(976, '5', 'Are these referenced documents (or copies of installed parameters considered as references) protected, by secure sealing methods, against untimely or illicit alteration?  ', 'QUESTION', '06B01-05', '06B01', '2', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(977, '6', 'Is the integrity of system configurations regularly tested against the configuration theoretically expected (at least weekly if not each time  systems are activated)?', 'QUESTION', '06B01-06', '06B01', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '18.2.3', '15.2.2', NULL),
	(978, '7', 'Are regular audits carried out of the list of security parameters specified?', 'QUESTION', '06B01-07', '06B01', '2', '', '', 'R1', '12.1.4; 18.2.3', '10.1.4; 15.2.2', NULL),
	(979, '8', 'Are regular audits carried out of the exception or escalation procedures in case of difficulties?', 'QUESTION', '06B01-08', '06B01', '2', '', '', 'C1', '12.1.4; 18.2.3', '10.1.4; 15.2.2', NULL),
	(980, '9', 'Are the development and test systems separated from the operational systems?', 'QUESTION', '06B01-09', '06B01', '1', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.4', '10.1.4', NULL),
	(981, '2', 'Control of the network access configurations of  user equipment', 'CATEGORY', '06B02', '06B', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(982, '1', 'Is there a document detailing all parameters to check on user workstations related to external connections capability (modem, WiFi, etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '06B02-01', '06B02', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(983, '2', 'Is this document regularly updated in line with the latest information and in cooperation with expert authorities (specialized audits, subscription to a service center, regular consultation with CERTs, etc.)?   ', 'QUESTION', '06B02-02', '06B02', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(984, '3', 'Is this reference document protected against all unauthorized] or illicit modification by strong security methods (digital signature)?  ', 'QUESTION', '06B02-03', '06B02', '4', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(985, '4', 'Is the configuration of network equipment of user workstations checked systematically for compliance against this reference document?', 'QUESTION', '06B02-04', '06B02', '2', '3', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(986, '5', 'Is this control effected systematically, at each connection to the network? ', 'QUESTION', '06B02-05', '06B02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(987, '6', 'Are there automatic routines which systematically analyze the use of the telephone network for data transmission? ', 'QUESTION', '06B02-06', '06B02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(988, '7', 'Are there automatic routines which test for the presence of non declared wireless network (WiFi) access points?  ', 'QUESTION', '06B02-07', '06B02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(989, '8', 'Are user workstations protected against the possibility of installing systems software and of modifying configurations? ', 'QUESTION', '06B02-08', '06B02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(990, '9', 'Is there a regular audit of the user configuration reference document and is the configuration control procedure regularly executed? ', 'QUESTION', '06B02-09', '06B02', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(991, '6', 'Control of administrative rights ', 'CATEGORY', '06C', '06', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(992, '1', 'Control of special access rights to network equipment ', 'CATEGORY', '06C01', '06C', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(993, '1', 'Has a management policy for privileged access rights on the network equipment been established, based on prior analysis of the security requirements and business stakes?', 'QUESTION', '06C01-01', '06C01', '2', '', '', 'E1', '9.1.1', '11.1.1', NULL),
	(994, '2', 'Is this policy documented, regularly reviewed, and approved by the affected managers?', 'QUESTION', '06C01-02', '06C01', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(995, '3', 'Have profiles been defined, as part of network operations, corresponding to each type of activity (equipment administration, the administration of security equipment, network management, management of backup medias and contents etc.)?  ', 'QUESTION', '06C01-03', '06C01', '1', '', '', 'E1', '6.1.2; 9.2.3;  9.2.5; 13.1.1', '10.1.3; 10.6.1; 11.2.2', NULL),
	(996, '4', 'For each profile have the necessary administrative rights been defined? ', 'QUESTION', '06C01-04', '06C01', '4', '2', '', 'E1', '6.1.2; 13.1.1', '10.1.3; 10.6.1', NULL),
	(997, '5', 'Does the process of attribution of administrative rights require the formal authorization of management (or the manager responsible for external service providers) at a sufficiently high level?', 'QUESTION', '06C01-05', '06C01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '6.1.2', '10.1.3', NULL),
	(998, '6', 'Does the process of attribution of administrative rights effected uniquely in relation to the profile of the holder?', 'QUESTION', '06C01-06', '06C01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '6.1.2', '10.1.3', NULL),
	(999, '7', 'Is the process of granting (modification or retraction) of special rights to an individual strictly controlled?\r\nA strict control requires a formal recognition of the signature (electronic or not) of the requester, that there be an access control in order to attribute or modify such rights and that any modification of special rights be logged and audited.', 'QUESTION', '06C01-07', '06C01', '4', '2', '3', 'R1', '9.2.3; 9.2.5', '11.2.2', NULL),
	(1000, '8', 'Is there a systematic process of removal of administrative rights at the time of departure or role change of staff?', 'QUESTION', '06C01-08', '06C01', '4', '3', '', 'E2', '9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1001, '9', 'Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of all administrative rights attributed ?', 'QUESTION', '06C01-09', '06C01', '1', '2', '', 'C1', '9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1002, '2', 'Authentication of administrators and operational personnel  ', 'CATEGORY', '06C02', '06C', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1003, '1', 'Is the process of authentication of network administrators or holders of administrative rights considered to be secure?\r\nAn authentication protocol is considered secure if it is not susceptible to being broken by a listening device on the network or rendered inoperable by specialists tools (in particular password crack tools). Such security usually uses cryptographic methods.', 'QUESTION', '06C02-01', '06C02', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1004, '2', 'Are the rules, for instance in the case of passwords, considered to be very strict?\r\nStrict rules impose the use of tested non-trivial passwords and the use of a mixture of different types of character of a reasonable length (ten or more characters). It is desirable that such rules be decided or agreed upon by the CISO.', 'QUESTION', '06C02-02', '06C02', '2', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1005, '3', 'Is a strong authentication used for the connection of administrators to the supervision system as well as for the connection of the supervision system to network equipments?\r\nIf the administrator connects to a hypervisor (such as HP OpenView, IBM TIVOLI, CA Unicenter, BMC Patrol or Bull OpenMaster) with secure authentication and effective access control, an equivalent level of security is needed for the objects that are managed (avoiding for example visible passwords, default public and community groups, access via telnet or simple SQL) in order to avoid malicious direct action on the equipment.', 'QUESTION', '06C02-03', '06C02', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1006, '4', 'Is there a consistent control of the administrator`s rights, of its context, and of the suitability of this context with the requested access, as per formal rules of access control?', 'QUESTION', '06C02-04', '06C02', '4', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1007, '5', 'Are authentication parameters under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the list of people able to change authentication rules, the identifiers themselves and the rules for monitoring connection attempts be strictly limited, that there be a reinforced access control in order to be able to modify these rights and that any modification of these rights be logged and audited and that there be a general audit at least once a year of all authentication parameters.', 'QUESTION', '06C02-05', '06C02', '4', '2', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1008, '6', 'Are there processes that guarantee authentication under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there is an audit at least once a year of the authentication procedures and processes.', 'QUESTION', '06C02-06', '06C02', '4', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1009, '7', 'Is there a regular audit of existing profiles having administrative rights?', 'QUESTION', '06C02-07', '06C02', '4', '3', '', 'C1', '9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1010, '8', 'Is there a regular audit of the procedures for granting profiles and the security parameters protecting the profiles and the rights?', 'QUESTION', '06C02-08', '06C02', '4', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1011, '3', 'Surveillance of administrative actions on the network ', 'CATEGORY', '06C03', '06C', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1012, '1', 'Has a detailed analysis been carried out of the operations performed with administrative rights which may potentially have an impact on network security (configuration of security systems, access to sensitive information, usage of sensitive tools, download or modification of administrative tools etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '06C03-01', '06C03', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.3; 13.1.1', '10.10.4; 10.6.1', NULL),
	(1013, '2', 'Are all these events recorded on a log file as well as all parameters required for their subsequent analysis?', 'QUESTION', '06C03-02', '06C03', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.3; 13.1.1', '10.10.4; 10.6.1', NULL),
	(1014, '3', 'Is there a system which enables the detection of the modification or deletion of a past record and to immediately trigger an alarm to a manager? ', 'QUESTION', '06C03-03', '06C03', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '12.4.3', '10.10.4', NULL),
	(1015, '4', 'Is there a summary of these records which enables management to detect abnormal behavior?', 'QUESTION', '06C03-04', '06C03', '4', '', '3', 'E3', '12.4.3', '10.10.4', NULL),
	(1016, '5', 'Is there a system which enables the detection of any modification of recording parameters and to immediately trigger an alarm to a manager? ', 'QUESTION', '06C03-05', '06C03', '4', '2', '', 'R1', '12.4.3', '10.10.4', NULL),
	(1017, '6', 'Does any inhibition of the recording system and processing of logged events trigger an alarm to a manager? ', 'QUESTION', '06C03-06', '06C03', '4', '3', '', 'E3', '12.4.3', '10.10.4', NULL),
	(1018, '7', 'Are all records or summary analysis protected against destruction or modification?', 'QUESTION', '06C03-07', '06C03', '2', '', '', 'R1', '12.4.3', '10.10.4', NULL),
	(1019, '8', 'Are all records or summary analysis kept for a long period?', 'QUESTION', '06C03-08', '06C03', '2', '', '', 'R1', '', '10.10.4', NULL),
	(1020, '9', 'Are the procedures for recording and analyzing operations executed with administrative rights regularly audited? ', 'QUESTION', '06C03-09', '06C03', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1021, '4', 'Control of networking operational tools and utilities ', 'CATEGORY', '06C04', '06C', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1022, '1', 'Is there an exhaustive inventory of the sensitive networking tools or utilities (administration of rights, configuration management, backups, copies, hot system restarts etc.) allowed for each type of operational staff profile?', 'QUESTION', '06C04-01', '06C04', '4', '', '', 'E1', '', '', NULL),
	(1023, '2', 'Can the tools or sensitive utilities only be used by the holders of the corresponding profiles following a secure and individual authentication (authentication token, smart card etc.)?  ', 'QUESTION', '06C04-02', '06C04', '2', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1024, '3', 'Is it forbidden to add or create tools or utilities without formal authorization?', 'QUESTION', '06C04-03', '06C04', '2', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1025, '4', 'Is this forbidding rule regularly enforced by an automatic procedure which may trigger an alert to a manager? ', 'QUESTION', '06C04-04', '06C04', '2', '2', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1026, '5', 'Do the rights attributed to operational teams prohibit them from modifying operational tools and utilities or at the very least is there a control of any such modification with triggering of an alert to a manager? ', 'QUESTION', '06C04-05', '06C04', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1027, '6', 'Are the attribution of profiles and the implementation of the security measures mentioned above regularly audited?', 'QUESTION', '06C04-06', '06C04', '2', '2', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1028, '6', 'Audit and Network Control Procedures', 'CATEGORY', '06D', '06', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1029, '1', 'Audit Control Operation ', 'CATEGORY', '06D01', '06D', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1030, '1', 'Has the management established the requirements and procedures to follow during the audits conducted on the networks?', 'QUESTION', '06D01-01', '06D01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.7.1', '15.3.1', NULL),
	(1031, '2', 'Are the rules related to network audits, relevant procedures and associated responsibilities defined and documented?\r\nThe limits to be determined concern the type of access to the equipment, the controls and authorized processing, the deletion of sensitive data obtained, the flagging of certain operations, ... and the empowerment of the individuals conducting the audits. ', 'QUESTION', '06D01-02', '06D01', '3', '', '', 'E2', '12.7.1', '15.3.1', NULL),
	(1032, '3', 'Are the auditors independent of the concerned activities?', 'QUESTION', '06D01-03', '06D01', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.7.1', '15.3.1', NULL),
	(1033, '4', 'Are the audit operations conducted for critical data recorded?', 'QUESTION', '06D01-04', '06D01', '2', '', '', 'E3', '12.7.1', '15.3.1', NULL),
	(1034, '5', 'Are the possible actions of the auditors well delimited? \r\nSuch limitations are recommended in the case of external auditors.', 'QUESTION', '06D01-05', '06D01', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '15.3.2', NULL),
	(1035, '2', 'Protection of Tools and Audit Results', 'CATEGORY', '06D02', '06D', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1036, '1', 'Are the audit tools protected to avoid any unauthorized or abusive use?\r\nThis applies particularly to intrusion testing and vulnerability assessments.', 'QUESTION', '06D02-01', '06D02', '3', '', '', 'E2', '', '15.3.2', NULL),
	(1037, '2', 'Are the audit results protected against any modification or disclosure?', 'QUESTION', '06D02-02', '06D02', '3', '', '', 'E2', '', '15.3.2', NULL),
	(1038, '3', 'Is the use of audit tools and results strictly limited?\r\nSuch limitations are recommended in the case of external auditors.', 'QUESTION', '06D02-03', '06D02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '15.3.2', NULL),
	(1039, '7', 'MEHARI_SecurityAndArchitecture', 'QUESTIONNAIRE', '07', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '{\n  "category": "07",\n  "index": "7",\n  "type": "MEHARI_SecurityAndArchitecture",\n  "questions": [\n    {\n      "category": "07A",\n      "index": "7",\n      "type": "CATEGORY",\n      "value": "Control of access to systems ",\n      "children": [\n        {\n          "category": "07A01",\n          "index": "1",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Management of access profiles (rights and privileges granted by functional profile) ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "07A01-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has a management policy for access rights to the systems been established, built from an analysis of the security requirements based on the business stakes?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.1.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Business requirements of access control\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.1.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Access control policy\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.1.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A01-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is access to the various parts of the information system (applications, data bases, systems, equipments, etc) defined in terms of job profiles which regroup roles or functions within the organization (profiles define access rights which are available to holders of the profile)?\\r\\nNote: in certain circumstances the notion of profile may be replaced by the notion of group.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.3; 9.2.5; 9.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of privileged access rights\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Information access restriction\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A01-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is it possible to adjust the access rights attributed to a given profile, based on the nature of the connection and equipment used (location, link, network, protocol, encryption, etc) and on the classification of the resources accessed?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do the profiles also allow definition of working time limits (daily hours and periods in the working calendar, weekends, holidays etc.)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.6"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have these profiles and the access rights attributed to the different profiles, as a function of context, been approved by the information owners and the Information Security Officer?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.6"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the process of definition and management of rights attributed to profiles under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the list of people able to change rights attributed to profiles be strictly limited and that the implementation of these rights into tables be strictly secure during transmission and storage and that there exists a reinforced access control in order to be able to modify these rights and that any modification of these rights be logged and audited.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is it possible to review at any time, the complete list of profiles and of the rights attributed to each profile?  ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit at least once a year of all rights attributed to each profile and the profile management procedures?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0376",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Assign the lowest privilege role by default",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall assign the least privileged role to a user by default when no other indication is available (e.g. explicit choice made by the user).",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"395bf167-fb65-49f5-918c-897f83e85a0e\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"395bf167-fb65-49f5-918c-897f83e85a0e\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "For example, on a linux system, a user be a regular user but also an administrator of the machine. When that user logs in, he should not be automatically assigned all privileges when he doesn\'t actually need to oeprate as root on the machine. Therefore, in that example, he should only be assigned to the \\"regular user\\" role by default, until he makes an explicit action to obtain the root privileges."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0124",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Permit to deny unauthorised session establishments",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall be able to deny session establishment based on one or a combination of the following:\\n- The location of the user terminal,\\n- Time of day and day of week\\n- User ID",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"cf463274-5a3d-4ba0-a963-402f176b27f0\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"cf463274-5a3d-4ba0-a963-402f176b27f0\\":\\"TCA_SYS_ACC_0090\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0032",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Only grant access to a subset of user accounts",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The contractor shall include the whitelist of users authorized to access the various systems in the user account management documentation in the [host document].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"99d3b62a-fd17-436d-8cb4-f918be1622e4\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"99d3b62a-fd17-436d-8cb4-f918be1622e4\\":\\"TCA_OS_BIOS_0160\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "When OS services are based on user accounts, only the required subset of users shall be granted access.\\nThis requirement means that the common rule should be to prevent users to use services like FTP. Access should be granted only on a case-by-case basis"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0231",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce system access control policies",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall enforce the implementation of the [System Access Control Policy] to system appliances, objects, operation and data.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"824f2261-17da-436d-8a61-47b489684392\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\",\\"d1896fa0-c90f-40a4-ad1b-7f28052048e5\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"824f2261-17da-436d-8a61-47b489684392\\":\\"TCA_ACCESS_0010\\",\\"d1896fa0-c90f-40a4-ad1b-7f28052048e5\\":\\"AC-3\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0169",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use a central user rights and roles management",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use a centralised user rights and roles management system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"2356f631-00ce-409a-bb37-d1afc2a01929\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"2356f631-00ce-409a-bb37-d1afc2a01929\\":\\"TCA_ACCESS_0070\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "07A02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Management of access authorizations and privileges (granting, delegation, revocation)",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "07A02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the procedure of granting access authorization require the formal approval of line management (at a sufficiently high level)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"User access provisioning\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are authorizations granted to named individuals only as a function of their profile?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"User access provisioning\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the procedure for granting (or changing or revoking) authorization to an individual (either directly or via his profile) strictly controlled?\\r\\nA strict control requires a formal recognition of the signature (electronic or otherwise) of the requester, that the implementation of the profile attributed to users in the form of tables is highly secure during transmission and storage and that there be a reinforced access control over the modification of such records and that any modification of records be logged and audited.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.2; 9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"User access provisioning\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a systematic process of updating the table of access authorizations at the time of departure of personnel (either internal or external)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.2; 9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"User access provisioning\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A02-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a systematic process of updating the table of access authorizations at the time of change of function?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.2; 9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"User access provisioning\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A02-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a strictly controlled process (as above) which allows to delegate his/her own authorizations, in part or in whole, to a person of choice for a determined period (in case of absence)?\\r\\nIn this case, the delegated rights must no longer be authorized to the person who has delegated them during this time. The owner however, must have the possibility of taking them back, by which process he or she effectively ends the delegation.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"User access provisioning\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A02-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is it possible to control at any time, for all users, the rights, authorizations and privileges in force?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"User access provisioning\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A02-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of  the profiles and authorizations granted to all users and of the procedures for management of attributed profiles?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0030",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Delete inactive accounts",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The contractor shall include the deletion of inactive accounts in the user account management documentation in the [host document].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"de51f0bb-ad01-47e3-b8a7-a5cd3a22ffd6\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"de51f0bb-ad01-47e3-b8a7-a5cd3a22ffd6\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_0020\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The old and inactive accounts should be deleted.\\nThis prevents illicit use of accounts by other users."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "07A03",\n          "index": "3",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Authentication of the access requester (user or entity)",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the process of distribution or modification of the user credentials guarantee that only the holder of the identifier can have access to them (initial communication is confidential, password change is under the exclusive control of the user, etc.)?  ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.4; 9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of secret authentication information of users\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the process of definition or modification of user credentials respect a set of rules which ensures their intrinsic validity?\\r\\nIn the case of passwords: sufficient length (8 characters or more), obligatory mixture of types of characters, frequent change (less than once a month), impossibility of reusing an old password, non-trivial word test using a dictionary, banning of standard systems, first names, anagrams of user name, dates etc. In the case of certificates and authentications based on cryptographic mechanisms: generation process evaluated or publicly recognized, keys of a sufficient length etc.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.4; 9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of secret authentication information of users\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.3; 11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the process of presenting a user password guarantee its trustworthiness?\\r\\nThe usage of a password will always be a weak point. The only process which does not divulge observable information consists of either introducing an object containing a secret (smart card), or entering a code which changes at every moment (token card type SecureId) or using a biometric characteristic.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.4; 9.4.2;  9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of secret authentication information of users\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.1; 11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the logon process secured?\\r\\nA secure logon should not give any information before the process is satisfactorily executed, not display the authenticators` password, display date and time of last connection, display eventual connection attempts that have failed, etc. ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.4; 9.4.2;  9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of secret authentication information of users\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.1; 11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do the mechanisms for retention and usage of credentials by the user (or by the equipment representing the user) or by the target systems guarantee trustworthiness and authenticity of these credentials?\\r\\nPasswords must be stored encrypted and a preliminary access control must be made before being accessible to the user.\\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must propose solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.4; 9.4.2;  9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of secret authentication information of users\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.1; 11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do the mechanisms used for the transmission of the credentials between the user and target equipments guarantee trustworthiness and authenticity of these credentials?\\r\\nTransmission of a password must be encrypted or use an algorithm which introduces a variable at each transmission.\\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must propose solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.2;  9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.1; 11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "In the case of multiple incorrect authentication attempts, is there an automatic process which temporarily invalidates the identifier used or, possibly, the user workstation itself, or which slows down the authentication process so as to inhibit any automatic routine from connecting?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.2;  9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.1; 11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the procedure for the replacement of a lost or mislaid user credential (password, token card) allow the instant deactivation of the old credential?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.4",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of secret authentication information of users\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the procedure for the replacement of a lost or mislaid user credential (password, token card) allow an effective control of the requester`s identity?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.4",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of secret authentication information of users\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are authentication parameters under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the list of people allowed to change the definition rules of credentials, the credentials themselves, the rules of surveillance of connection attempts etc., be strictly limited and that there exists a reinforced access control to effect these modifications, that these modifications be logged and audited and that there exists a regular general audit at least once a year of all authentication parameters.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A03-11",\n              "index": "11",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes that ensure authentication under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (close with a seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of authentication procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect intrusion attempts and the processes which respond to these intrusion attempts).",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0186",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Display minimal information with monitoring exception",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Only identification and authentication data fields required for log-on purposes shall be displayed except for network services/applications running under the Monitoring System role:\\nFor these, it shall be allowed to display/output the respective monitoring information as well.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"9252c245-2b2c-4c6c-b547-aa4c6beb54ca\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"9252c245-2b2c-4c6c-b547-aa4c6beb54ca\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0080\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0194",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Do not transmit passwords in clear text",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Passwords shall never be transmitted in clear text and their encryption shall be done using appropriate algorithms.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"dd60fb91-c654-4336-bae4-cca490e93ab5\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"dd60fb91-c654-4336-bae4-cca490e93ab5\\":\\"IA-5(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This does not apply when passwords are used to unlock hardware authenticators (e.g., Personal Identity Verification cards). Encrypted representations of passwords include, for example, encrypted versions of passwords and one-way cryptographic hashes of passwords."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0339",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Periodically change your keys",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall enforce change of cryptographic keys at a [defined-key-change-interval].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"30f6672d-5f5c-4e3a-876f-452e7561c967\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"30f6672d-5f5c-4e3a-876f-452e7561c967\\":\\"ASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The appropriate key management can be done via a PKI."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0187",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Detect unsuccessful log-in tentative",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall detect when a number of unsuccessful authentication attempts related to a user since the last successful authentication occurred. The number of unsuccessful authentication attempts shall be configurable.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"01544988-edb2-4b68-9013-aa92128223f3\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"01544988-edb2-4b68-9013-aa92128223f3\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0030\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This prevents an attacker to scan all possible passwords for breaking the access control mechanism. They are mandatory to protect from attacks driven by people around authorised user."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0352",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Validate certification paths",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall validate certificates by constructing a certification path with status information to an accepted trust anchor.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"1dfba2de-063f-4ac7-b4f6-75b76353754c\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"1dfba2de-063f-4ac7-b4f6-75b76353754c\\":\\"IA-5(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Status information for certification paths includes, for example, certificate revocation lists or certificate status protocol responses."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0203",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Token based authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use authentication tokens to authenticate users.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"1d04f0b3-1353-44b6-93a5-6bf484148ab3\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\",\\"9c23d21f-d2dc-4f4f-866b-89cea98c1474\\":\\"ESA\\",\\"4b904608-dc4a-4226-b631-2d167d134c20\\":\\"NIST-FIPS-190\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"1d04f0b3-1353-44b6-93a5-6bf484148ab3\\":\\"IA-5(11)\\",\\"9c23d21f-d2dc-4f4f-866b-89cea98c1474\\":\\"GASF\\",\\"4b904608-dc4a-4226-b631-2d167d134c20\\":\\"Section 4\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The identity of a human user can be proven by requiring the user to demonstrate possession of a physical object which is unique to that user, or to a group of users. Objects used for this it purpose are known as authentication tokens. Since the uniqueness of the information stored on an authentication token is responsible for proving the identity of its bearer to the host system, the information must be protected against duplication or theft. Advanced tokens usually contain a microprocessor and semiconductor memory, and support sophisticated authentication protocols which provide a high level of security.\\n\\nFrom a security standpoint, the strength of token based authentication lies in the fact that the device containing the information which verifies the identity of the user is portable. Therefore, the authentication information can be kept in the user\'s possession. The greatest threat to the security of this type of system is the possibility that an attacker could steal a valid token in order to pose as an authorized user. A sophisticated attacker might also be able to counterfeit a token. These threats can be reduced by requiring the user to submit a password or PIN when the token is used for authentication. There should be a limit to the number of consecutive incorrect PIN submissions. Without the password, a stolen or counterfeited token would not allow an attacker to gain access to the system. This can significantly increase the level of assurance since a user\'s identity is verified based on something the user knows in addition to possession of the token. Compromise of one user\'s token should only compromise that user, not the entire system. Use of tokens with cryptographic capabilities can contribute greatly to the security of an authentication system. In addition, the use of passwords or PINs in combination with authentication tokens is recommended for applications where this approach is practical.\\n\\nThe type of authentication token selected for a particular application will depend on a number of factors."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0349",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Digital signature based authentication (PKI)",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use PKI-based authentication and validate certificates by constructing a certification path with status information to an accepted trust anchor",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"b5eee7db-52af-4163-90d0-20a95051ab0e\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"b5eee7db-52af-4163-90d0-20a95051ab0e\\":\\"IA-5(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Devices requiring unique device-to-device identification and authentication may be defined by type, by device, or by a combination of type/device. Information systems typically use either shared known information (e.g., Media Access Control [MAC] or Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol [TCP/IP] addresses) for device identification or organizational authentication solutions (e.g., IEEE 802.1x and Extensible Authentication Protocol [EAP], Radius server with EAP-Transport Layer Security [TLS] authentication, Kerberos) to identify/authenticate devices on local and/or wide area networks.\\n\\nA local connection is any connection with a device communicating without the use of a network. A network connection is any connection with a device that communicates through a network (e.g., local area or wide area network, Internet). A remote connection is any connection with a device communicating through an external network (e.g., the Internet)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0214",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Biometric based authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use a biometric authentication system/method to authenticate users.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"f40a5b48-f001-4aab-8b27-57542f65c93a\\":\\"ESA\\",\\"6851ef0c-2d17-41e8-8d7f-7ffbfd851e14\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"f40a5b48-f001-4aab-8b27-57542f65c93a\\":\\"GASF\\",\\"6851ef0c-2d17-41e8-8d7f-7ffbfd851e14\\":\\"IA-5(12)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Certain physical features of the human body are relatively unique from individual to individual. Facial photographs and fingerprints have long been used for personal identification, particularly by law enforcement agencies. Biometric authentication is the measurement of a unique biological feature used to verify the claimed identity of an individual through automated means. The biometric authentication mechanism will strive to measure a unique biological feature to the degree that only one person may be authenticated as a specific user. The biological feature may be based on a physiological or behavioural characteristic. The physiological characteristics measure a physical feature such as a fingerprint or face. The behavioural characteristics measure your reaction or response such as your signature or voice. The most used biometrics are fingerprint, retinal and voice authentication devices.\\nReferences: FIPS Publication 201"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0182",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Display last unsuccessful session",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Upon successful session establishment, the system shall display to the user the date, time and location of the last unsuccessful attempt of session establishment and the number of unsuccessful attempts since the last successful session establishment.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"abb68bfc-ea6d-4a3e-be48-493afb3471d9\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"abb68bfc-ea6d-4a3e-be48-493afb3471d9\\":\\"TCA_SYS_ACC_0070\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0178",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce user deactivation after failed attempts",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "When the [number of unsuccessful authentication attempts] has been reached or exceeded, the system shall disable the access to the user for a certain time. This time shall be configurable.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"acbf0298-6ac3-459d-ae73-d3cf673f898a\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\",\\"71f95adf-ef1c-49eb-a5ef-94a6fceebe15\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"acbf0298-6ac3-459d-ae73-d3cf673f898a\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0040\\",\\"71f95adf-ef1c-49eb-a5ef-94a6fceebe15\\":\\"AC-7\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This is prevents an attacker to scan all possible passwords for breaking the access control mechanism. They are mandatory to protect from attacks driven by people around authorised user.\\nThis control applies regardless of whether the logon occurs via a local or network connection. Due to the potential for denial of service, automatic lockouts initiated by information systems are usually temporary and automatically release after a predetermined time period established by organizations. If a delay algorithm is selected, organizations may choose to employ different algorithms for different information system components based on the capabilities of those components. Responses to unsuccessful login attempts may be implemented at both the operating system and the application levels."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0134",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce a lockout after failed log-in attempts",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "A�[shut out time delay] shall be enforced after a configurable [number of failed log-in attempts] before allowing a further log-in attempt.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"2db5bb16-9299-4006-88fd-22efa4fcd03d\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\",\\"1c9f2eaf-b03e-4573-82dd-ed6cbc751a49\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"2db5bb16-9299-4006-88fd-22efa4fcd03d\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0190\\",\\"1c9f2eaf-b03e-4573-82dd-ed6cbc751a49\\":\\"AC-7\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Due to the potential for denial of service, automatic lockouts initiated by information systems are usually temporary and automatically release after a predetermined time period established by organizations. If a delay algorithm is selected, organizations may choose to employ different algorithms for different information system components based on the capabilities of those components. Responses to unsuccessful logon attempts may be implemented at both the operating system and the application levels.\\n\\nFor missions where availability is critical, the values ( [number of failed log-in attempts] and the�[shut out time delay]) can be set to soften the impact of this requirment (e.g set a high number of allowed attempts and a short shut out time delay)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0195",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Follow password guidelines",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Passwords shall follow the definitions in the \\"ESACERT Security Guidelines ? Recommendations for Password usage\\" password best practices.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"1bf91337-b304-4a26-a1df-0ba258521b3c\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"1bf91337-b304-4a26-a1df-0ba258521b3c\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0144\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0185",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Display minimal information",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Only identification and authentication data fields required for log-on purposes shall be displayed for all roles and users.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"b51ce4b0-a6fb-4b27-90de-55341ebd54e4\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"b51ce4b0-a6fb-4b27-90de-55341ebd54e4\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0050\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0220",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Ensure strength of secrets",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "When authentication mechanisms are based on secrets, it shall be ensured that the secrets are of appropriate strength.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"3e56bc69-763d-434b-8fae-725f9af3b522\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"3e56bc69-763d-434b-8fae-725f9af3b522\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0130\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The authentication process may rely on a wide range of mechanisms, some of them requiring additional data only known by the user himself.\\nThis personal data are called secrets; it could be dongle, password, etc.\\nNB.: Secrets are not mandatory. Biometric data (eyes prints or fingerprints) could now be used to recognised users."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0202",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Store password securely",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Passwords stored by the system shall be stored using a secure one-way encryption algorithm.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e02509db-87a1-448b-bc94-8d8b24f86670\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e02509db-87a1-448b-bc94-8d8b24f86670\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0100\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This shall apply to online storage as well as to any kind of offline storage (e.g. on access control media).\\nNote that if passwords, pin codes and the like are stored on media, the media are considered part of the system.\\nAs an example, assuming that the authentication process relies on a password-based solution, the system shall store the passwords of the users encrypted."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0183",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Display last successful session",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Upon successful session establishment, the system shall display to the user the date, time and location of the last successful session establishment.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"08c0f152-6af7-4e7a-adbd-5b202207b52e\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\",\\"4f2d5f01-7b5a-4013-a0e4-012300969598\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"08c0f152-6af7-4e7a-adbd-5b202207b52e\\":\\"AC-9(2)\\",\\"4f2d5f01-7b5a-4013-a0e4-012300969598\\":\\"TCA_SYS_ACC_0060\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This is intended to cover both traditional logons to information systems and accesses to systems that occur in other types of architectural configurations (e.g., service oriented architectures)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "07A04",\n          "index": "4",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Access filtering and management of associations ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "07A04-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does any access to a system require the use of an identifier recognized by the system?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A04-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a direct or indirect correspondence between any identifier and a real physical person?\\r\\nIn the case where an application calls another or executes a system call, it may be that the application does not transfer to the target system the identifier which originally made the request. The link between the call, the identifier and the user himself must remain traceable after the fact.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A04-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have all generic or by-default accounts been deleted?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A04-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the acceptance of the identifier by the system systematically subject to authentication?\\r\\nSystematic authentication requires that the process be implemented for all subsystems (Remote process monitors, database management systems, batch processes, etc.), for all application requests and for all access routes, including ports reserved for remote maintenance.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A04-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "May the authentication process be renewed during an open session for those transactions considered to be sensitive?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A04-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there an automatic invalidation of the user session in the absence of traffic after a defined duration, thus requiring user re-identification and re-authentication?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.5"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A04-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a systematic control, based upon definite access rules, of the profile of the requester, of the association context and of the appropriateness of that profile and context for the access requested?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A04-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the parameters for the definition and management of access filtering rules under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the list of persons allowed to change the security parameters for access filtering be extremely limited, and that there be a reinforced access control in order to be able to effect such modification and that any modification be logged and audited.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A04-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes that guarantee access filtering under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (close with a seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of access filtering procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect intrusion attempts and the processes which respond to these intrusion attempts).",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A04-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are regular tests carried out to attempt to break into the information system and are there detailed technical audits run by specialists?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0111",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Perform self-test",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "A suite of self-tests shall be run (e.g. during initial start-up, periodically during normal operation, at the request of the authorised user) to demonstrate the correct operation of itself.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"ae0bf421-a5e3-44a7-9810-5212a694522c\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"ae0bf421-a5e3-44a7-9810-5212a694522c\\":\\"15.14\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Actions should be taken as the result of self-testing.\\nThe corruption of security data, functions (including the one performing tests) should be also detected"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0353",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Map the authenticated identity to the account",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall map the authenticated identity to the account of the individual.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"ac60c56b-0a65-41ae-9e41-150be664da2e\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"ac60c56b-0a65-41ae-9e41-150be664da2e\\":\\"IA-5(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0130",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Automatically lock session after inactivity",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The information system shall prevent further access to the system by initiating a session lock after a�[period of inactivity].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"88260c9d-3c8a-4d60-9d4d-9abf29fc15c6\\":\\"NIST\\",\\"b458b2f7-c61f-4edc-b206-121878c2a35b\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\",\\"711a1452-d532-4496-aa98-0a5b815f5e1e\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"88260c9d-3c8a-4d60-9d4d-9abf29fc15c6\\":\\"AC-11\\",\\"b458b2f7-c61f-4edc-b206-121878c2a35b\\":\\"A.11.5.5\\",\\"711a1452-d532-4496-aa98-0a5b815f5e1e\\":\\"TCA_SYS_ACC_0040\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Session locks are temporary actions taken when users stop work and move away from the immediate vicinity of information systems but do not want to log out because of the temporary nature of their absences. Session locks are implemented where session activities can be determined. This is typically at the operating system level, but can also be at the application level. Session locks are not an acceptable substitute for logging out of information systems, for example, if organizations require users to log out at the end of workdays."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0391",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use human identification challenges",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use challenge-response tests to idendify whether or not the user is human.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"5611e9d8-c5fc-4bfa-9459-e819b347ca4e\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"5611e9d8-c5fc-4bfa-9459-e819b347ca4e\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This applies mostly for services available to web users. Challenge-response systems, widely known as CAPTCHAs (Completely Automated Public Turing test to tell Computers and Humans Apart), permit to restrict the use of automatic scripts for specific features (e.g. browsing, registering)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0137",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Invalidate session identifiers at logout",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall invalidate session identifiers upon user logout or other session terminations",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"8181ce4e-3b25-453c-8181-f72b3471e9c9\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"8181ce4e-3b25-453c-8181-f72b3471e9c9\\":\\"SC-23(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This curtails the ability of adversaries from capturing and continuing to employ previously valid session IDs."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0222",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Re-authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall re-authenticate the user under [specific conditions].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"8bc9f6a5-d728-4138-8cc5-6d9520fd94c0\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"8bc9f6a5-d728-4138-8cc5-6d9520fd94c0\\":\\"12.4\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0136",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Terminate network connection after session or timeout",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall terminate the network connection associated with a communication session at the end of the session or after a defined [time period of inactivity].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"d1c6c318-9128-43d2-a55f-4dda3242bb6e\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\",\\"fea1d5ef-7acf-4823-9a8e-8d6876e68692\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"d1c6c318-9128-43d2-a55f-4dda3242bb6e\\":\\"A.11.5.6\\",\\"fea1d5ef-7acf-4823-9a8e-8d6876e68692\\":\\"SC-10\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This applies to both internal and external networks. Terminating network connections associated with communications sessions include, for example, de-allocating associated TCP/IP address/port pairs at the operating system level, or de-allocating networking assignments at the application level if multiple application sessions are using a single, operating system-level network connection. Time periods of inactivity may be established by organisations and include, for example, time periods by type of network access or for specific network accesses."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0383",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prevent display of default banner",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prevent the display of applications\' and servers\' default banner.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"0329ae85-3eb9-4a40-8063-a45b2e1b6fa1\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"0329ae85-3eb9-4a40-8063-a45b2e1b6fa1\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Most default banners reveal relevant information on the server and application\\nIndeed, one of the first tasks when conducting an application penetration test is to try to identify the version of the server and the application to pentest. The reason for that is that it allows the tester to discover all the well-known vulnerabilities that are affecting the server and the application.\\nThis process is called application fingerprinting."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "07A05",\n          "index": "5",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Authentication of the server for access to sensitive servers",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "07A05-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a possibility to declare servers as sensitive and, as such, requiring an authentication of the server accessed?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A05-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a mechanism of authentication of the server called before access to a sensitive server from the internal network?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A05-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the authentication mechanism of the accessed servers provide a recognized strong level of security?\\r\\nNotably the usage of a simple password will always be a weakness. The only methods recognized as strong, that is observable without divulging information, are those based on cryptographic algorithms.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A05-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do the security equipment that retain credentials (e.g. passwords, calling number, etc.) use mechanisms which guarantee their impregnability and authenticity?\\r\\nPasswords must be stored encrypted and a preliminary control of the user must be made before usage.\\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A05-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the transmission of credentials (e.g. passwords, calling address, etc.) between calling user equipment and authentication systems use mechanisms which guarantee their impregnability and authenticity?\\r\\nTransmission of a password must be encrypted or use an algorithm which introduces a variable at each transmission. \\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A05-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the revoked keys management procedure guarantee that the control systems take into consideration in real time any revocation of keys?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A05-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the revoked keys management procedure guarantee that the control systems systematically test that the keys used have not been revoked?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07A05-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes that guarantee the authentication of the accessed entities under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there is an audit at least once a year of the authentication procedures and processes.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0194",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Do not transmit passwords in clear text",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Passwords shall never be transmitted in clear text and their encryption shall be done using appropriate algorithms.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"dd60fb91-c654-4336-bae4-cca490e93ab5\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"dd60fb91-c654-4336-bae4-cca490e93ab5\\":\\"IA-5(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This does not apply when passwords are used to unlock hardware authenticators (e.g., Personal Identity Verification cards). Encrypted representations of passwords include, for example, encrypted versions of passwords and one-way cryptographic hashes of passwords."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0191",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Multi-factor authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use multiple-factor authentication for the authentication of users in the system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"8d6e49b2-2296-43bd-958e-7e8ff8a75666\\":\\"ESA\\",\\"a619f297-154b-4319-9ec8-42a5073410f4\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"8d6e49b2-2296-43bd-958e-7e8ff8a75666\\":\\"GASF\\",\\"a619f297-154b-4319-9ec8-42a5073410f4\\":\\"12.4\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "That is, the system shall base authentication on at least two different authentication techniques (e.g. password based + token based)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0190",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Single-factor authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use single-factor authentication for the authentication of users in the system.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"37dd9cc6-849d-47d0-91ba-f1ca76fd152e\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"37dd9cc6-849d-47d0-91ba-f1ca76fd152e\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0356",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Provide trusted communications path between users and sensitive security function",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall establish a trusted communications path between the user and the sensitive security functions of the system (e.g. system authentication and re-authentication).",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"5ce11876-5ee6-494d-96c4-e88530f89180\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"5ce11876-5ee6-494d-96c4-e88530f89180\\":\\"SC-11\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Trusted paths are mechanisms by which users (through input devices) can communicate directly with security functions of information systems with the requisite assurance to support information security policies. The mechanisms can be activated only by users or the security functions of organizational information systems. User responses via trusted paths are protected from modifications by or disclosure to untrusted applications. Organizations employ trusted paths for high-assurance connections between security functions of information systems and users (e.g., during system logons). Enforcement of trusted communications paths is typically provided via an implementation that meets the reference monitor concept."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0219",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prohibit the use of cached authenticators after time period",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prohibit the use of cached authenticators after [cache expiration time period].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e559d6c3-4729-4843-a624-7f75423ba602\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e559d6c3-4729-4843-a624-7f75423ba602\\":\\"IA-5(13)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        }\n      ],\n      "gasf": [],\n      "answers": {\n        "MEHARI_W": "",\n        "MEHARI_Min": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n        "MEHARI_Max": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n      },\n      "referenceObject": null,\n      "identifier": null,\n      "objType": "Audit",\n      "lockedBy": null\n    },\n    {\n      "category": "07B",\n      "index": "7",\n      "type": "CATEGORY",\n      "value": "Containment of environments ",\n      "children": [\n        {\n          "category": "07B01",\n          "index": "1",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Control of access to residual data",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "07B01-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has a detailed analysis been carried out for each type of system to identify residual data files, their storage areas and access paths to such files and storage areas?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07B01-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have storage systems (and medias) been identified which once stored sensitive information and which have been re-affected to other usages? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07B01-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the system use an access rights control mechanism which prohibits user access to the contents of resources which have been freed up by another process (areas of memory, temporary resources )?  ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07B01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the tools which enable access to sensitive remnant data or temporary files reserved only for the use of systems operators and does access to those tools require a secure authentication?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07B01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are there procedures of physical erasure of residual files (in main memory or for storage media)?  ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07B01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are these procedures implemented systematically and automatically by the relevant systems each time a logical resource is freed? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07B01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the invalidation of such procedures alerted to an operational IT manager?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07B01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a procedure which guarantees that sensitive information contained on discarded media will be protected until the destruction of the supporting media?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "8.3.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A8\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Asset management\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A8.3\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Media handling\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"8.3.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Disposal of media\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.7.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07B01-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are all security procedures and parameters protecting access to residual data subject to regular audit?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0356",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Provide trusted communications path between users and sensitive security function",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall establish a trusted communications path between the user and the sensitive security functions of the system (e.g. system authentication and re-authentication).",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"5ce11876-5ee6-494d-96c4-e88530f89180\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"5ce11876-5ee6-494d-96c4-e88530f89180\\":\\"SC-11\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Trusted paths are mechanisms by which users (through input devices) can communicate directly with security functions of information systems with the requisite assurance to support information security policies. The mechanisms can be activated only by users or the security functions of organizational information systems. User responses via trusted paths are protected from modifications by or disclosure to untrusted applications. Organizations employ trusted paths for high-assurance connections between security functions of information systems and users (e.g., during system logons). Enforcement of trusted communications paths is typically provided via an implementation that meets the reference monitor concept."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        }\n      ],\n      "gasf": [],\n      "answers": {\n        "MEHARI_W": "",\n        "MEHARI_Min": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n        "MEHARI_Max": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n      },\n      "referenceObject": null,\n      "identifier": null,\n      "objType": "Audit",\n      "lockedBy": null\n    },\n    {\n      "category": "07C",\n      "index": "7",\n      "type": "CATEGORY",\n      "value": "Management and saving of logs ",\n      "children": [\n        {\n          "category": "07C01",\n          "index": "1",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Recording access to sensitive resources ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "07C01-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has a specific analysis been carried out to determine which access requests and related parameters will be logged?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C01-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is a tool or control application used which is able to log accesses to sensitive resources (applications, files, databases, etc.)?  ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C01-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the rules, specifying which accesses to log and retain, formalized?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have the rules, specifying which accesses to log and retain, been approved by the information owners or the Information Security Officer?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do the rules which specify which accesses will be logged include the necessary elements to carry out a subsequent investigation in the case of anomaly?\\r\\nThese rules should specify for each type of access (system, database management system, etc. ) the fundamental elements to record; for example user ID, the service or application requested, date and time, the point from where the access was requested if known etc.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have these rules been validated by Legal Department (particularly for logs containing personal data)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are all these records archived (on disk, cassettes, optical disk, etc.) and conserved for a long period in such a way as to not be modifiable?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1; 12.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protection of log information\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.1; 10.10.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the parameters for definition and management of recording connections (login) and called applications under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the list of persons allowed  to change the definition parameters and the management of the recording rules for the logins and called applications be strictly limited and that there exist a reinforced access control to effect these modifications and that these modifications be logged and audited.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protection of log information\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C01-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes which ensure the recording of connections and called applications under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used for recording has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (closed with seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of recording procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect modification attempts and the processes which respond to these modification attempts).",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0087",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Ensure system wide/time correlated audit trails",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall compile audit records from the all system components/parts into a, centralized, system-wide (logical or physical) audit trail that is time correlated within [level of tolerance for relationship between time stamps of individual records in the audit trail].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"b6cdc917-e03d-4020-a313-ef0d3286cc8f\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"b6cdc917-e03d-4020-a313-ef0d3286cc8f\\":\\"AU-12(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The compilation of audit records implies the format adaptation and time correlation of the logs (i.e. to match the centralized log format and time value) and the forwarding of those records into a centralized log processing facility for log correlation.\\nAudit trails are time-correlated if the time stamps in the individual audit records can be reliably related to the time stamps in other audit records to achieve a time ordering of the records within organizational tolerances."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0075",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Implement audit functions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Auditing functions shall be implemented and activated throughout the system.��The grades of activation of audit functions shall be adapted to the situation.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"1acf386b-d390-4fc9-804f-badda08fd526\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\",\\"bc15893f-b643-46dc-a512-9d7d04453657\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\",\\"245d894e-2887-4bb2-88cc-66b71c81745e\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"1acf386b-d390-4fc9-804f-badda08fd526\\":\\"A.10.10.1\\",\\"bc15893f-b643-46dc-a512-9d7d04453657\\":\\"AU-12\\",\\"245d894e-2887-4bb2-88cc-66b71c81745e\\":\\"TCA_LOG_GEN_0010\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This requirement ensure that auditing is activated throughout the system to assure that each relevant event is logged. Depending on the type of log and the system state, the auditing functions can be adapted (e.g. verbose mode, minimal audit).\\n\\nThe term \\"system\\" is used here to denote at least\\n- for all physically or logically separated assets and\\n- for all security application interaction across security classification boundaries.\\n\\nFurther involvement of separate applications can be introduced if agreed in the policy.\\nAudits records can be generated from many different information system components. Audited events are events for which audits are to be generated. These events are typically a subset of all events for which the information system is capable of generating audit records."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0076",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Produce audit logs",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Audit logs recording [audit record types] shall be produced and kept for an [agreed period].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"78ac7a48-3942-4371-8e2d-5e24e3c9daf3\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\",\\"5cf0c59f-4d27-464d-a2f6-9c9f2e3baad8\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\",\\"1b9396a8-1f4d-429c-9b40-54eb43cf5a85\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"78ac7a48-3942-4371-8e2d-5e24e3c9daf3\\":\\"A.10.10.1\\",\\"5cf0c59f-4d27-464d-a2f6-9c9f2e3baad8\\":\\"AU-12\\",\\"1b9396a8-1f4d-429c-9b40-54eb43cf5a85\\":\\"TCA_LOG_GEN_0010\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This shall be produced and kept to assist in future investigations and access control monitoring.\\nThe term \\"system\\" is used here to denote at least\\n- for all physically or logically separated assets and\\n- for all security�related applications (e.g. anti-virus software, intrusion detection/prevention software),\\n- for all application interaction across security classification boundaries.\\n\\nFurther involvement of separate applications can be introduced if agreed in the policy.\\nAudits records can be generated from many different information system components. Audited events are events for which audits are to be generated. These events are typically a subset of all events for which the information system is capable of generating audit records."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0098",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Write audit trails to write-once media",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall write audit trails to hardware-enforced, write-once media.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e10d9790-203c-4463-a2a3-069b9ea4d9d6\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e10d9790-203c-4463-a2a3-069b9ea4d9d6\\":\\"AU-9(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This applies to the initial generation of audit trails (i.e., the collection of audit records that represents the audit information to be used for detection, analysis, and reporting purposes) and to the backup of those audit trails. It does not apply to the initial generation of audit records prior to being written to an audit trail. Write-once, read-many (WORM) media includes, for example, Compact Disk- Recordable (CD-R) and Digital Video Disk-Recordable (DVD-R). In contrast, the use of switchable write-protection media such as on tape cartridges or Universal Serial Bus (USB) drives results in write-protected, but not write-once, media."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "07C02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Recording privileged system calls ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "07C02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has a specific analysis been carried out of privileged system calls to log and of parameters related to these calls which should be recorded?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is use made of a tool or control application which is able to record privileged system calls (tools which require special access rights, access to security files, administration of security parameters etc.)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have the rules specifying the privileged system calls to be logged been formalized?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have the rules specifying the privileged system calls to be logged been approved by the information owners or the Information Security Officer?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C02-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do the rules specifying the accesses to privileged system calls to be logged include the relevant elements needed for subsequent investigation in the case of anomaly?\\r\\nThe rules must specify for each type of system call (create, read, update or delete) the basic elements to record, for example, the nature of the event, the user identifier, the systems services required, date and time etc.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C02-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have these rules been validated by Legal Department (particularly for logs containing personal data)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C02-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are all these records archived (on disk, cassettes, optical disk, etc.) and conserved for a long period in such a way as to not be falsifiable?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.1; 12.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Event logging\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protection of log information\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.3; 10.10.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C02-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the parameters for definition and management of the rules for recording privileged system calls under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the list of persons allowed to change the recording parameters be strictly limited and that there exists a reinforced access control to effect these modifications and that these modifications be logged and audited.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protection of log information\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.10.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07C02-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes which ensure the recording of privileged system calls under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used for recording has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (closed with seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of recording procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect modification attempts and the processes which respond to these modification attempts).",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0087",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Ensure system wide/time correlated audit trails",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall compile audit records from the all system components/parts into a, centralized, system-wide (logical or physical) audit trail that is time correlated within [level of tolerance for relationship between time stamps of individual records in the audit trail].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"b6cdc917-e03d-4020-a313-ef0d3286cc8f\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"b6cdc917-e03d-4020-a313-ef0d3286cc8f\\":\\"AU-12(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The compilation of audit records implies the format adaptation and time correlation of the logs (i.e. to match the centralized log format and time value) and the forwarding of those records into a centralized log processing facility for log correlation.\\nAudit trails are time-correlated if the time stamps in the individual audit records can be reliably related to the time stamps in other audit records to achieve a time ordering of the records within organizational tolerances."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0076",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Produce audit logs",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Audit logs recording [audit record types] shall be produced and kept for an [agreed period].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"78ac7a48-3942-4371-8e2d-5e24e3c9daf3\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\",\\"5cf0c59f-4d27-464d-a2f6-9c9f2e3baad8\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\",\\"1b9396a8-1f4d-429c-9b40-54eb43cf5a85\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"78ac7a48-3942-4371-8e2d-5e24e3c9daf3\\":\\"A.10.10.1\\",\\"5cf0c59f-4d27-464d-a2f6-9c9f2e3baad8\\":\\"AU-12\\",\\"1b9396a8-1f4d-429c-9b40-54eb43cf5a85\\":\\"TCA_LOG_GEN_0010\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This shall be produced and kept to assist in future investigations and access control monitoring.\\nThe term \\"system\\" is used here to denote at least\\n- for all physically or logically separated assets and\\n- for all security�related applications (e.g. anti-virus software, intrusion detection/prevention software),\\n- for all application interaction across security classification boundaries.\\n\\nFurther involvement of separate applications can be introduced if agreed in the policy.\\nAudits records can be generated from many different information system components. Audited events are events for which audits are to be generated. These events are typically a subset of all events for which the information system is capable of generating audit records."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0098",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Write audit trails to write-once media",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall write audit trails to hardware-enforced, write-once media.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e10d9790-203c-4463-a2a3-069b9ea4d9d6\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e10d9790-203c-4463-a2a3-069b9ea4d9d6\\":\\"AU-9(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This applies to the initial generation of audit trails (i.e., the collection of audit records that represents the audit information to be used for detection, analysis, and reporting purposes) and to the backup of those audit trails. It does not apply to the initial generation of audit records prior to being written to an audit trail. Write-once, read-many (WORM) media includes, for example, Compact Disk- Recordable (CD-R) and Digital Video Disk-Recordable (DVD-R). In contrast, the use of switchable write-protection media such as on tape cartridges or Universal Serial Bus (USB) drives results in write-protected, but not write-once, media."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        }\n      ],\n      "gasf": [],\n      "answers": {\n        "MEHARI_W": "",\n        "MEHARI_Min": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n        "MEHARI_Max": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n      },\n      "referenceObject": null,\n      "identifier": null,\n      "objType": "Audit",\n      "lockedBy": null\n    },\n    {\n      "category": "07D",\n      "index": "7",\n      "type": "CATEGORY",\n      "value": "Security of the architecture",\n      "children": [\n        {\n          "category": "07D01",\n          "index": "1",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Service continuity of the architecture and of its components",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "07D01-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has an analysis been carried out of the various shared equipment and systems (apart from the architecture of the applications but including general peripheral systems such as backup systems and robots, print servers and centralized printing equipment) in order to highlight the needs of service continuity?\\r\\nAn in depth analysis assumes that a list of failure scenarios has been established and that the consequences of such events have been analyzed.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07D01-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has this analysis allowed to detail the minimum performance levels that must be maintained for each system and have these performance levels been accepted by users or information owners?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07D01-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has the appropriate level of architectural redundancy been determined (e.g. clusters or disk replication ) for the servers or equipment concerned? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07D01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the architecture and its implementation guarantee that the minimum performance levels will be exceeded in the case of an incident of failure?\\r\\nSuch a guarantee supposes that either fail safe systems are entirely automatic or that sufficient detection systems and staff are in place so as to manually reconfigure them.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07D01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there an assurance in this case that secondary equipment (power supply, air-conditioning, etc. ) does not introduce any additional risk and does not eliminate redundancy envisaged for the systems architecture or equipment?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07D01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does any shutdown or inhibition of redundant equipment or system devoted to detecting the need for human intervention or for automatic reconfiguration trigger an alarm to an operational manager? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07D01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are regular tests made to demonstrate that security equipment is able to guarantee minimum performance levels required in the case of an incident or failure? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0058",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Fail in a known state",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall fail to a [known-state] for [defined types of failures] preserving [defined system state information] in failure.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"5ca74366-8324-455b-8511-41a50a586085\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"5ca74366-8324-455b-8511-41a50a586085\\":\\"SC-24\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Failure in a known state addresses security concerns in accordance with the mission/business needs of organizations. Failure in a known secure state helps to prevent the loss of confidentiality, integrity, or availability of information in the event of failures of organizational information systems or system components. Failure in a known safe state helps to prevent systems from failing to a state that may cause injury to individuals or destruction to property. Preserving information system state information facilitates system restart and return to the operational mode of organizations with less disruption of mission/business processes."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0092",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Take action on audit processing failures",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall be able to take the [appropriate action] when an audit processing failure is detected.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"64d4d890-6df1-4492-84d5-5f59776950a2\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"64d4d890-6df1-4492-84d5-5f59776950a2\\":\\"AU-5\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The followings are examples of action: shut down information system, overwrite oldest audit records, stop generating audit records.\\nOrganisations may choose to define additional actions for different audit processing failures (e.g., by type, by location, by severity, or a combination of such factors). This applies to each audit data storage repository (i.e., distinct information system component where audit records are stored), the total audit storage capacity of organizations (i.e., all audit data storage repositories combined) or both."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0054",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Provide a safe mode",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall provide a safe mode in which the system enters under certain [agreed critical conditions].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"dc1acd19-70e9-42bd-bfac-1bf5065d0fde\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"dc1acd19-70e9-42bd-bfac-1bf5065d0fde\\":\\"CP-12\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "For information systems supporting critical missions/business functions including, for example, military operations and weapons systems, civilian space operations, nuclear power plant operations, and air traffic control operations (especially real-time operational environments), organizations may choose to identify certain conditions under which those systems revert to a pre-defined safe mode of operation. The safe mode of operation, which can be activated automatically or manually, restricts the types of activities or operations information systems could execute when those conditions are encountered. Restriction include, for example, allowing only certain functions that could be carried out under�limited power or with reduced communications bandwidth.\\n\\nSuch such safe modes are be a prevention approach to maintain the system\'s availability, e.g. by limiting the modification ablities (e.g. read only for some parts), by limiting the possible interactions, by limiting the power, by reducing the communication bandwidth, thereby ensuring the system\'s persistence during the time of the critical event."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0055",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "System restore",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall be able to restore after a crash of failure.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"4abf78c0-8744-45c4-b3d7-7ca48f55e9c6\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"4abf78c0-8744-45c4-b3d7-7ca48f55e9c6\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0052",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Provide alternative security mechanisms",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Alternative or supplemental security mechanisms shall be employed for satisfying security functions when the primary means of implementing the security function is unavailable or compromised.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"9900f961-ceb7-404c-98af-fe7f92440b14\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"9900f961-ceb7-404c-98af-fe7f92440b14\\":\\"CP-13\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This supports information system resiliency and contingency planning/continuity of operations. To ensure mission/business continuity, organizations can implement alternative or supplemental security mechanisms. These mechanisms may be less effective than the primary mechanisms (e.g., not as easy to use, not as scalable, or not as secure). However, having the capability to readily employ these alternative/supplemental mechanisms enhances overall mission/business continuity that might otherwise be adversely impacted if organizational operations had to be curtailed until the primary means of implementing the functions was restored. Given the cost and level of effort required to provide such alternative capabilities, this control would typically be applied only to critical security capabilities provided by information systems, system components, or information system services. For example, an organization may issue to senior executives and system administrators one-time pads in case multifactor tokens, the organization\'s standard means for secure remote authentication, is compromised."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "07D02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Isolation of Sensitive Systems",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "07D02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has the systems` sensitivity been analyzed (based on the applications and data processed) including peripheral systems or robots used for storage or archiving, print servers or central printing equipment, etc.) to highlight their security requirements?\\r\\nA thorough analysis implies the establishment of a list of incident scenarios (A, I, C), for which all foreseeable consequences were analyzed.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.6.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07D02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Did this analysis allow to formalize minimum requirements for each system and were these minimum requirements accepted by the users (information owner)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.6.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "07D02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have appropriate isolation measures (physical and logical) been determined for these servers and equipment?\\r\\nThese measures may impose to use different data centers for sensitive servers or applications from other servers.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.6.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0253",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Critical and sensitive system segregation",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Critial and sensitive systems shall have a dedicated environment isolated for the other systems",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"c6ecece5-babc-4de1-ac93-3b62ff7d5096\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"c6ecece5-babc-4de1-ac93-3b62ff7d5096\\":\\"A.11.6.2\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        }\n      ],\n      "gasf": [],\n      "answers": {\n        "MEHARI_W": "",\n        "MEHARI_Min": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n        "MEHARI_Max": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n      },\n      "referenceObject": null,\n      "identifier": null,\n      "objType": "Audit",\n      "lockedBy": null\n    }\n  ],\n  "identifier": null,\n  "objType": "Audit",\n  "lockedBy": null\n}'),
	(1040, '7', 'Control of access to systems ', 'CATEGORY', '07A', '07', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1041, '1', 'Management of access profiles (rights and privileges granted by functional profile) ', 'CATEGORY', '07A01', '07A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1042, '1', 'Has a management policy for access rights to the systems been established, built from an analysis of the security requirements based on the business stakes?', 'QUESTION', '07A01-01', '07A01', '2', '', '', 'E1', '9.1.1', '11.1.1', NULL),
	(1043, '2', 'Is access to the various parts of the information system (applications, data bases, systems, equipments, etc) defined in terms of job profiles which regroup roles or functions within the organization (profiles define access rights which are available to holders of the profile)?\r\nNote: in certain circumstances the notion of profile may be replaced by the notion of group.', 'QUESTION', '07A01-02', '07A01', '4', '2', '', 'E1', '9.2.3; 9.2.5; 9.4.1', '11.2.2', NULL),
	(1044, '3', 'Is it possible to adjust the access rights attributed to a given profile, based on the nature of the connection and equipment used (location, link, network, protocol, encryption, etc) and on the classification of the resources accessed?', 'QUESTION', '07A01-03', '07A01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1045, '4', 'Do the profiles also allow definition of working time limits (daily hours and periods in the working calendar, weekends, holidays etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '07A01-04', '07A01', '2', '', '', 'E3', '9.4.2', '11.5.6', NULL),
	(1046, '5', 'Have these profiles and the access rights attributed to the different profiles, as a function of context, been approved by the information owners and the Information Security Officer?', 'QUESTION', '07A01-05', '07A01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '9.4.2', '11.5.6', NULL),
	(1047, '6', 'Is the process of definition and management of rights attributed to profiles under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the list of people able to change rights attributed to profiles be strictly limited and that the implementation of these rights into tables be strictly secure during transmission and storage and that there exists a reinforced access control in order to be able to modify these rights and that any modification of these rights be logged and audited.', 'QUESTION', '07A01-06', '07A01', '4', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1048, '7', 'Is it possible to review at any time, the complete list of profiles and of the rights attributed to each profile?  ', 'QUESTION', '07A01-07', '07A01', '2', '2', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1049, '8', 'Is there a regular audit at least once a year of all rights attributed to each profile and the profile management procedures?', 'QUESTION', '07A01-08', '07A01', '4', '2', '', 'C1', '9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1050, '2', 'Management of access authorizations and privileges (granting, delegation, revocation)', 'CATEGORY', '07A02', '07A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1051, '1', 'Does the procedure of granting access authorization require the formal approval of line management (at a sufficiently high level)?', 'QUESTION', '07A02-01', '07A02', '4', '2', '', 'E1', '9.2.2', '', NULL),
	(1052, '2', 'Are authorizations granted to named individuals only as a function of their profile?', 'QUESTION', '07A02-02', '07A02', '2', '', '', 'E1', '9.2.2', '', NULL),
	(1053, '3', 'Is the procedure for granting (or changing or revoking) authorization to an individual (either directly or via his profile) strictly controlled?\r\nA strict control requires a formal recognition of the signature (electronic or otherwise) of the requester, that the implementation of the profile attributed to users in the form of tables is highly secure during transmission and storage and that there be a reinforced access control over the modification of such records and that any modification of records be logged and audited.', 'QUESTION', '07A02-03', '07A02', '4', '2', '3', 'E2', '9.2.2; 9.2.5', '11.2.2', NULL),
	(1054, '4', 'Is there a systematic process of updating the table of access authorizations at the time of departure of personnel (either internal or external)?', 'QUESTION', '07A02-04', '07A02', '4', '3', '', 'E2', '9.2.2; 9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1055, '5', 'Is there a systematic process of updating the table of access authorizations at the time of change of function?', 'QUESTION', '07A02-05', '07A02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '9.2.2; 9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1056, '6', 'Is there a strictly controlled process (as above) which allows to delegate his/her own authorizations, in part or in whole, to a person of choice for a determined period (in case of absence)?\r\nIn this case, the delegated rights must no longer be authorized to the person who has delegated them during this time. The owner however, must have the possibility of taking them back, by which process he or she effectively ends the delegation.', 'QUESTION', '07A02-06', '07A02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '9.2.2', '', NULL),
	(1057, '7', 'Is it possible to control at any time, for all users, the rights, authorizations and privileges in force?', 'QUESTION', '07A02-07', '07A02', '2', '', '', 'C1', '9.2.2', '', NULL),
	(1058, '8', 'Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of  the profiles and authorizations granted to all users and of the procedures for management of attributed profiles?', 'QUESTION', '07A02-08', '07A02', '1', '2', '', 'C1', '9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1059, '3', 'Authentication of the access requester (user or entity)', 'CATEGORY', '07A03', '07A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1060, '1', 'Does the process of distribution or modification of the user credentials guarantee that only the holder of the identifier can have access to them (initial communication is confidential, password change is under the exclusive control of the user, etc.)?  ', 'QUESTION', '07A03-01', '07A03', '2', '1', '', 'E1', '9.2.4; 9.4.3', '11.5.3', NULL),
	(1061, '2', 'Does the process of definition or modification of user credentials respect a set of rules which ensures their intrinsic validity?\r\nIn the case of passwords: sufficient length (8 characters or more), obligatory mixture of types of characters, frequent change (less than once a month), impossibility of reusing an old password, non-trivial word test using a dictionary, banning of standard systems, first names, anagrams of user name, dates etc. In the case of certificates and authentications based on cryptographic mechanisms: generation process evaluated or publicly recognized, keys of a sufficient length etc.', 'QUESTION', '07A03-02', '07A03', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '9.2.4; 9.4.3', '11.2.3; 11.5.3', NULL),
	(1062, '3', 'Does the process of presenting a user password guarantee its trustworthiness?\r\nThe usage of a password will always be a weak point. The only process which does not divulge observable information consists of either introducing an object containing a secret (smart card), or entering a code which changes at every moment (token card type SecureId) or using a biometric characteristic.', 'QUESTION', '07A03-03', '07A03', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '9.2.4; 9.4.2;  9.4.3', '11.5.1; 11.5.3', NULL),
	(1063, '4', 'Is the logon process secured?\r\nA secure logon should not give any information before the process is satisfactorily executed, not display the authenticators` password, display date and time of last connection, display eventual connection attempts that have failed, etc. ', 'QUESTION', '07A03-04', '07A03', '1', '', '', 'E3', '9.2.4; 9.4.2;  9.4.3', '11.5.1; 11.5.3', NULL),
	(1064, '5', 'Do the mechanisms for retention and usage of credentials by the user (or by the equipment representing the user) or by the target systems guarantee trustworthiness and authenticity of these credentials?\r\nPasswords must be stored encrypted and a preliminary access control must be made before being accessible to the user.\r\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must propose solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.', 'QUESTION', '07A03-05', '07A03', '2', '2', '3', 'E2', '9.2.4; 9.4.2;  9.4.3', '11.5.1; 11.5.3', NULL),
	(1065, '6', 'Do the mechanisms used for the transmission of the credentials between the user and target equipments guarantee trustworthiness and authenticity of these credentials?\r\nTransmission of a password must be encrypted or use an algorithm which introduces a variable at each transmission.\r\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must propose solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.', 'QUESTION', '07A03-06', '07A03', '2', '2', '3', 'E3', '9.4.2;  9.4.3', '11.5.1; 11.5.3', NULL),
	(1066, '7', 'In the case of multiple incorrect authentication attempts, is there an automatic process which temporarily invalidates the identifier used or, possibly, the user workstation itself, or which slows down the authentication process so as to inhibit any automatic routine from connecting?', 'QUESTION', '07A03-07', '07A03', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '9.4.2;  9.4.3', '11.5.1; 11.5.3', NULL),
	(1067, '8', 'Does the procedure for the replacement of a lost or mislaid user credential (password, token card) allow the instant deactivation of the old credential?', 'QUESTION', '07A03-08', '07A03', '2', '2', '', 'E2', '9.2.4', '11.5.3', NULL),
	(1068, '9', 'Does the procedure for the replacement of a lost or mislaid user credential (password, token card) allow an effective control of the requester`s identity?', 'QUESTION', '07A03-09', '07A03', '2', '2', '', 'E3', '9.2.4', '11.5.3', NULL),
	(1069, '10', 'Are authentication parameters under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the list of people allowed to change the definition rules of credentials, the credentials themselves, the rules of surveillance of connection attempts etc., be strictly limited and that there exists a reinforced access control to effect these modifications, that these modifications be logged and audited and that there exists a regular general audit at least once a year of all authentication parameters.', 'QUESTION', '07A03-10', '07A03', '4', '2', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1070, '11', 'Are the processes that ensure authentication under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (close with a seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of authentication procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect intrusion attempts and the processes which respond to these intrusion attempts).', 'QUESTION', '07A03-11', '07A03', '4', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1071, '4', 'Access filtering and management of associations ', 'CATEGORY', '07A04', '07A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1072, '1', 'Does any access to a system require the use of an identifier recognized by the system?', 'QUESTION', '07A04-01', '07A04', '1', '2', '', 'E1', '', '11.5.2', NULL),
	(1073, '2', 'Is there a direct or indirect correspondence between any identifier and a real physical person?\r\nIn the case where an application calls another or executes a system call, it may be that the application does not transfer to the target system the identifier which originally made the request. The link between the call, the identifier and the user himself must remain traceable after the fact.', 'QUESTION', '07A04-02', '07A04', '4', '2', '', 'E1', '', '11.5.2', NULL),
	(1074, '3', 'Have all generic or by-default accounts been deleted?', 'QUESTION', '07A04-03', '07A04', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '11.5.2', NULL),
	(1075, '4', 'Is the acceptance of the identifier by the system systematically subject to authentication?\r\nSystematic authentication requires that the process be implemented for all subsystems (Remote process monitors, database management systems, batch processes, etc.), for all application requests and for all access routes, including ports reserved for remote maintenance.', 'QUESTION', '07A04-04', '07A04', '2', '2', '', 'E2', '9.4.2', '11.5.2', NULL),
	(1076, '5', 'May the authentication process be renewed during an open session for those transactions considered to be sensitive?', 'QUESTION', '07A04-05', '07A04', '4', '', '', 'E3', '9.4.2', '', NULL),
	(1077, '6', 'Is there an automatic invalidation of the user session in the absence of traffic after a defined duration, thus requiring user re-identification and re-authentication?', 'QUESTION', '07A04-06', '07A04', '4', '', '', 'E3', '9.4.2', '11.5.5', NULL),
	(1078, '7', 'Is there a systematic control, based upon definite access rules, of the profile of the requester, of the association context and of the appropriateness of that profile and context for the access requested?', 'QUESTION', '07A04-07', '07A04', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1079, '8', 'Are the parameters for the definition and management of access filtering rules under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the list of persons allowed to change the security parameters for access filtering be extremely limited, and that there be a reinforced access control in order to be able to effect such modification and that any modification be logged and audited.', 'QUESTION', '07A04-08', '07A04', '4', '2', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1080, '9', 'Are the processes that guarantee access filtering under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (close with a seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of access filtering procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect intrusion attempts and the processes which respond to these intrusion attempts).', 'QUESTION', '07A04-09', '07A04', '4', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1081, '10', 'Are regular tests carried out to attempt to break into the information system and are there detailed technical audits run by specialists?', 'QUESTION', '07A04-10', '07A04', '2', '3', '', 'R2', '', '', NULL),
	(1082, '5', 'Authentication of the server for access to sensitive servers', 'CATEGORY', '07A05', '07A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1083, '1', 'Is there a possibility to declare servers as sensitive and, as such, requiring an authentication of the server accessed?', 'QUESTION', '07A05-01', '07A05', '4', '1', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1084, '2', 'Is there a mechanism of authentication of the server called before access to a sensitive server from the internal network?', 'QUESTION', '07A05-02', '07A05', '4', '1', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1085, '3', 'Does the authentication mechanism of the accessed servers provide a recognized strong level of security?\r\nNotably the usage of a simple password will always be a weakness. The only methods recognized as strong, that is observable without divulging information, are those based on cryptographic algorithms.', 'QUESTION', '07A05-03', '07A05', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1086, '4', 'Do the security equipment that retain credentials (e.g. passwords, calling number, etc.) use mechanisms which guarantee their impregnability and authenticity?\r\nPasswords must be stored encrypted and a preliminary control of the user must be made before usage.\r\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.', 'QUESTION', '07A05-04', '07A05', '4', '3', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1087, '5', 'Does the transmission of credentials (e.g. passwords, calling address, etc.) between calling user equipment and authentication systems use mechanisms which guarantee their impregnability and authenticity?\r\nTransmission of a password must be encrypted or use an algorithm which introduces a variable at each transmission. \r\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.', 'QUESTION', '07A05-05', '07A05', '4', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1088, '6', 'Does the revoked keys management procedure guarantee that the control systems take into consideration in real time any revocation of keys?', 'QUESTION', '07A05-06', '07A05', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1089, '7', 'Does the revoked keys management procedure guarantee that the control systems systematically test that the keys used have not been revoked?', 'QUESTION', '07A05-07', '07A05', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1090, '8', 'Are the processes that guarantee the authentication of the accessed entities under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there is an audit at least once a year of the authentication procedures and processes.', 'QUESTION', '07A05-08', '07A05', '4', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1091, '7', 'Containment of environments ', 'CATEGORY', '07B', '07', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1092, '1', 'Control of access to residual data', 'CATEGORY', '07B01', '07B', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1093, '1', 'Has a detailed analysis been carried out for each type of system to identify residual data files, their storage areas and access paths to such files and storage areas?', 'QUESTION', '07B01-01', '07B01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1094, '2', 'Have storage systems (and medias) been identified which once stored sensitive information and which have been re-affected to other usages? ', 'QUESTION', '07B01-02', '07B01', '4', '', '', 'E1', '', '', NULL),
	(1095, '3', 'Does the system use an access rights control mechanism which prohibits user access to the contents of resources which have been freed up by another process (areas of memory, temporary resources )?  ', 'QUESTION', '07B01-03', '07B01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1096, '4', 'Are the tools which enable access to sensitive remnant data or temporary files reserved only for the use of systems operators and does access to those tools require a secure authentication?', 'QUESTION', '07B01-04', '07B01', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1097, '5', 'Are there procedures of physical erasure of residual files (in main memory or for storage media)?  ', 'QUESTION', '07B01-05', '07B01', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1098, '6', 'Are these procedures implemented systematically and automatically by the relevant systems each time a logical resource is freed? ', 'QUESTION', '07B01-06', '07B01', '4', '3', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1099, '7', 'Is the invalidation of such procedures alerted to an operational IT manager?', 'QUESTION', '07B01-07', '07B01', '4', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1100, '8', 'Is there a procedure which guarantees that sensitive information contained on discarded media will be protected until the destruction of the supporting media?', 'QUESTION', '07B01-08', '07B01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '8.3.2', '10.7.2', NULL),
	(1101, '9', 'Are all security procedures and parameters protecting access to residual data subject to regular audit?', 'QUESTION', '07B01-09', '07B01', '4', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1102, '7', 'Management and saving of logs ', 'CATEGORY', '07C', '07', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1103, '1', 'Recording access to sensitive resources ', 'CATEGORY', '07C01', '07C', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1104, '1', 'Has a specific analysis been carried out to determine which access requests and related parameters will be logged?', 'QUESTION', '07C01-01', '07C01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.1', '10.10.2', NULL),
	(1105, '2', 'Is a tool or control application used which is able to log accesses to sensitive resources (applications, files, databases, etc.)?  ', 'QUESTION', '07C01-02', '07C01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.1', '10.10.2', NULL),
	(1106, '3', 'Are the rules, specifying which accesses to log and retain, formalized?', 'QUESTION', '07C01-03', '07C01', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1107, '4', 'Have the rules, specifying which accesses to log and retain, been approved by the information owners or the Information Security Officer?', 'QUESTION', '07C01-04', '07C01', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1108, '5', 'Do the rules which specify which accesses will be logged include the necessary elements to carry out a subsequent investigation in the case of anomaly?\r\nThese rules should specify for each type of access (system, database management system, etc. ) the fundamental elements to record; for example user ID, the service or application requested, date and time, the point from where the access was requested if known etc.', 'QUESTION', '07C01-05', '07C01', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.1', '10.10.1', NULL),
	(1109, '6', 'Have these rules been validated by Legal Department (particularly for logs containing personal data)?', 'QUESTION', '07C01-06', '07C01', '2', '2', '', 'E3', '12.4.1', '10.10.1', NULL),
	(1110, '7', 'Are all these records archived (on disk, cassettes, optical disk, etc.) and conserved for a long period in such a way as to not be modifiable?', 'QUESTION', '07C01-07', '07C01', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.1; 12.4.2', '10.10.1; 10.10.3', NULL),
	(1111, '8', 'Are the parameters for definition and management of recording connections (login) and called applications under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the list of persons allowed  to change the definition parameters and the management of the recording rules for the logins and called applications be strictly limited and that there exist a reinforced access control to effect these modifications and that these modifications be logged and audited.', 'QUESTION', '07C01-08', '07C01', '4', '2', '', 'R1', '12.4.2', '10.10.3', NULL),
	(1112, '9', 'Are the processes which ensure the recording of connections and called applications under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the software used for recording has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (closed with seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of recording procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect modification attempts and the processes which respond to these modification attempts).', 'QUESTION', '07C01-09', '07C01', '4', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1113, '2', 'Recording privileged system calls ', 'CATEGORY', '07C02', '07C', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1114, '1', 'Has a specific analysis been carried out of privileged system calls to log and of parameters related to these calls which should be recorded?', 'QUESTION', '07C02-01', '07C02', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.1', '10.10.2', NULL),
	(1115, '2', 'Is use made of a tool or control application which is able to record privileged system calls (tools which require special access rights, access to security files, administration of security parameters etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '07C02-02', '07C02', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.1', '10.10.2', NULL),
	(1116, '3', 'Have the rules specifying the privileged system calls to be logged been formalized?', 'QUESTION', '07C02-03', '07C02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1117, '4', 'Have the rules specifying the privileged system calls to be logged been approved by the information owners or the Information Security Officer?', 'QUESTION', '07C02-04', '07C02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1118, '5', 'Do the rules specifying the accesses to privileged system calls to be logged include the relevant elements needed for subsequent investigation in the case of anomaly?\r\nThe rules must specify for each type of system call (create, read, update or delete) the basic elements to record, for example, the nature of the event, the user identifier, the systems services required, date and time etc.', 'QUESTION', '07C02-05', '07C02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.1', '10.10.1', NULL),
	(1119, '6', 'Have these rules been validated by Legal Department (particularly for logs containing personal data)?', 'QUESTION', '07C02-06', '07C02', '2', '2', '', 'E3', '12.4.1', '10.10.1', NULL),
	(1120, '7', 'Are all these records archived (on disk, cassettes, optical disk, etc.) and conserved for a long period in such a way as to not be falsifiable?', 'QUESTION', '07C02-07', '07C02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.4.1; 12.4.2', '10.10.3; 10.10.1', NULL),
	(1121, '8', 'Are the parameters for definition and management of the rules for recording privileged system calls under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the list of persons allowed to change the recording parameters be strictly limited and that there exists a reinforced access control to effect these modifications and that these modifications be logged and audited.', 'QUESTION', '07C02-08', '07C02', '4', '2', '', 'R1', '12.4.2', '10.10.3', NULL),
	(1122, '9', 'Are the processes which ensure the recording of privileged system calls under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the software used for recording has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (closed with seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of recording procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect modification attempts and the processes which respond to these modification attempts).', 'QUESTION', '07C02-09', '07C02', '4', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1123, '7', 'Security of the architecture', 'CATEGORY', '07D', '07', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1124, '1', 'Service continuity of the architecture and of its components', 'CATEGORY', '07D01', '07D', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1125, '1', 'Has an analysis been carried out of the various shared equipment and systems (apart from the architecture of the applications but including general peripheral systems such as backup systems and robots, print servers and centralized printing equipment) in order to highlight the needs of service continuity?\r\nAn in depth analysis assumes that a list of failure scenarios has been established and that the consequences of such events have been analyzed.', 'QUESTION', '07D01-01', '07D01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1126, '2', 'Has this analysis allowed to detail the minimum performance levels that must be maintained for each system and have these performance levels been accepted by users or information owners?', 'QUESTION', '07D01-02', '07D01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1127, '3', 'Has the appropriate level of architectural redundancy been determined (e.g. clusters or disk replication ) for the servers or equipment concerned? ', 'QUESTION', '07D01-03', '07D01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1128, '4', 'Does the architecture and its implementation guarantee that the minimum performance levels will be exceeded in the case of an incident of failure?\r\nSuch a guarantee supposes that either fail safe systems are entirely automatic or that sufficient detection systems and staff are in place so as to manually reconfigure them.', 'QUESTION', '07D01-04', '07D01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1129, '5', 'Is there an assurance in this case that secondary equipment (power supply, air-conditioning, etc. ) does not introduce any additional risk and does not eliminate redundancy envisaged for the systems architecture or equipment?', 'QUESTION', '07D01-05', '07D01', '2', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1130, '6', 'Does any shutdown or inhibition of redundant equipment or system devoted to detecting the need for human intervention or for automatic reconfiguration trigger an alarm to an operational manager? ', 'QUESTION', '07D01-06', '07D01', '2', '', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1131, '7', 'Are regular tests made to demonstrate that security equipment is able to guarantee minimum performance levels required in the case of an incident or failure? ', 'QUESTION', '07D01-07', '07D01', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1132, '2', 'Isolation of Sensitive Systems', 'CATEGORY', '07D02', '07D', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1133, '1', 'Has the systems` sensitivity been analyzed (based on the applications and data processed) including peripheral systems or robots used for storage or archiving, print servers or central printing equipment, etc.) to highlight their security requirements?\r\nA thorough analysis implies the establishment of a list of incident scenarios (A, I, C), for which all foreseeable consequences were analyzed.', 'QUESTION', '07D02-01', '07D02', '3', '', '', 'E2', '', '11.6.2', NULL),
	(1134, '2', 'Did this analysis allow to formalize minimum requirements for each system and were these minimum requirements accepted by the users (information owner)?', 'QUESTION', '07D02-02', '07D02', '3', '', '', 'E2', '', '11.6.2', NULL),
	(1135, '3', 'Have appropriate isolation measures (physical and logical) been determined for these servers and equipment?\r\nThese measures may impose to use different data centers for sensitive servers or applications from other servers.', 'QUESTION', '07D02-03', '07D02', '3', '', '', 'E2', '', '11.6.2', NULL);
INSERT INTO `ASSAUDIT_DEFAULT` (`ID`, `IX`, `AVALUE`, `ATYPE`, `CATEGORY`, `PARENT`, `VW`, `VMAX`, `VMIN`, `VTYPE`, `VISO13`, `VISO5`, `QUESTIONNAIRE_JSON`) VALUES
	(1136, '8', 'MEHARI_ITProductionEnvironment', 'QUESTIONNAIRE', '08', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '{\n  "category": "08",\n  "index": "8",\n  "type": "MEHARI_ITProductionEnvironment",\n  "questions": [\n    {\n      "category": "08A",\n      "index": "8",\n      "type": "CATEGORY",\n      "value": "Security of operational procedures ",\n      "children": [\n        {\n          "category": "08A01",\n          "index": "1",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Consideration of security in relation with operational personnel (permanent and temporary staff)",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a security policy, specifically aimed at operations personnel, related to information systems?\\r\\nThis policy should cover the requirements for the protection of information as well as the protection of physical assets and processes and mention the forbidden behaviors",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "11.2.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A11\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Physical and environmental security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A11.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Equipment\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"11.2.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Equipment siting and protection\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "9.2.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is information systems operations personnel required to sign contract clauses of adherence to that security policy (no matter their status: permanent or temporary staff, students, etc.)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do these clauses make clear that the obligation to respect that security policy applies to information at large (whichever the support : paper, magnetic, optical, etc.)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do these clauses make clear, if necessary and legally possible, that the obligation to respect the security policy applies without limitation in time?\\r\\nThis applies, in particular, to the clauses concerning confidentiality, they may (and often must) continue after the end of the contract linking (directly or indirectly) the employee or  service provider or partner to the company",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do these clauses make clear that the personnel has an obligation not to tolerate any action contrary to security from other people?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the signature of these clauses represent a formal commitment?\\r\\nIn order to achieve a formal commitment, the personnel should explicitly state that his/her signature implies having understood and accepted the security policy",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are these same clauses obligatory for contractors working on systems operations?\\r\\nPractically, the contractors should ensure that their personnel sign individually and explicitly under the same conditions than internal staff. ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a mandatory and well adapted training course aimed at systems operation personnel?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the security policy compliance agreements, signed by personnel, securely kept (at least in a locked cupboard )?  ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the security policy compliance agreements, signed by external contractors, securely kept (at least in a locked cupboard )?  ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A01-11",\n              "index": "11",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of the effective application of the signature procedure by  operational personnel (directly employed by the company or indirectly through a service company) ?  ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0149",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prevent discovery of components/devices",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prevent the discovery of specific system components composing a managed interface.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"a31b61c3-86e2-4ff9-87b1-0acd1297b701\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"a31b61c3-86e2-4ff9-87b1-0acd1297b701\\":\\"SC-7(16)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This protects network addresses of information system components that are part of managed interfaces from discovery through common tools and techniques used to identify devices on networks. Network addresses are not available for discovery (e.g., network address not published or entered in domain name systems), requiring prior knowledge for access. Another obfuscation technique is to periodically change network addresses."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "08A02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Control of the operational tools and utilities",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "08A02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have different profiles been defined for the systems operation staff (administration and management of configurations, administration of security equipment, monitoring, audit and investigation)? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.6.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.6\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Technical vulnerability management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.6.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Restrictions on software installation\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are all members of systems operation staff attributed with one of these profiles? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.6.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.6\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Technical vulnerability management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.6.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Restrictions on software installation\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have all the sensitive system tools and utilities (rights administration, configuration management, backups, copies, hot restarts, etc.) been exhaustively audited and listed for each profile?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": " 9.4.4; 12.6.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Use of privileged utility programs\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.6\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Technical vulnerability management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.6.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Restrictions on software installation\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is it possible only for holders of a certain profile to use the corresponding tools and utilities subsequent to proper strong authentication (smart card or token card)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": " 9.4.4; 12.6.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Use of privileged utility programs\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.6\\",\\"Object