ESTION",\n              "value": "Is the start of  production of new versions of systems or applications possible by the use of a defined validation and authorization process? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.5.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.5\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Control of operational software\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"12.5.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Installation of software on operational systems\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "12.4.1; 6.1.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08A03-16",\n              "index": "16",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the start of production control procedures regularly audited?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0071",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Authenticate code prior to installation",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall implement cryptographic mechanisms to authenticate software prior to installation.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"ff5cb8d1-2a1a-424f-a367-6a8154f6c890\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"ff5cb8d1-2a1a-424f-a367-6a8154f6c890\\":\\"SI-7(15)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Cryptographic authentication includes, for example, verifying that software or firmware components have been digitally signed using certificates recognized and approved by organizations. Code signing is an effective method to protect against malicious code.\\nAuthentication of code relies on the availability ceritificates (e.g. Message Authentication Codes), which permit to verify, by comparing the certificate with the calculated signature,�the integrity and origin of the software."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0028",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Define access hardening steps",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The contractor shall document the specific hardening steps taken to restrict access to the target system/software.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"4bbd48da-c47a-4ba2-8f7b-583ee47663ef\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"4bbd48da-c47a-4ba2-8f7b-583ee47663ef\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0012",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Establish change management procedures",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "A change management, configuration control, review and release process shall be established for releasing any change to software.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"f4777615-a477-4729-81e0-8c12813b4446\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"f4777615-a477-4729-81e0-8c12813b4446\\":\\"TCA_NON_FUNC_0040\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This should be documented in the Software Management Plan."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0267",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Remove default installations",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "No servers with default installation configuration shall be used.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0062",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Protect against denial of service",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall protect against or limit the effects of denial of service attacks by employing security safeguards.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e8df5ca1-bcf6-41a6-8fc6-7cd2a35ec6c8\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e8df5ca1-bcf6-41a6-8fc6-7cd2a35ec6c8\\":\\"SC-5\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "A variety of technologies exist to limit, or in some cases, eliminate the effects of denial of service attacks. For example, boundary protection devices can filter certain types of packets to protect information system components on internal organizational networks from being directly affected by denial of service attacks. Employing increased capacity and bandwidth combined with service redundancy may also reduce the susceptibility to denial of service attacks."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0383",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prevent display of default banner",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prevent the display of applications\' and servers\' default banner.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"0329ae85-3eb9-4a40-8063-a45b2e1b6fa1\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"0329ae85-3eb9-4a40-8063-a45b2e1b6fa1\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Most default banners reveal relevant information on the server and application\\nIndeed, one of the first tasks when conducting an application penetration test is to try to identify the version of the server and the application to pentest. The reason for that is that it allows the tester to discover all the well-known vulnerabilities that are affecting the server and the application.\\nThis process is called application fingerprinting."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\