ion theoretically expected?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "18.2.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A18\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Compliance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A18.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Information security reviews\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"18.2.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Technical compliance review\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "15.2.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08B01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are regular audits carried out of the  compliance to the specifications for security parameters?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "18.2.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A18\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Compliance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A18.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Information security reviews\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"18.2.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Technical compliance review\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "15.2.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08B01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are regular audits carried out of the exception and escalation procedures in the case of difficulty or installation problems?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "18.2.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A18\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Compliance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A18.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Information security reviews\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"18.2.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Technical compliance review\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "15.2.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "08B01-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the development and test environments separated from the operational environments?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0028",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Define access hardening steps",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The contractor shall document the specific hardening steps taken to restrict access to the target system/software.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"4bbd48da-c47a-4ba2-8f7b-583ee47663ef\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"4bbd48da-c47a-4ba2-8f7b-583ee47663ef\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0267",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Remove default installations",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "No servers with default installation configuration shall be used.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0268",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Synchronise internal clocks",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall synchronise its internal clock with the [authoritative time source] every [update frequency].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"057ea763-6b84-43dd-abf0-c4d9dbb575b9\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"057ea763-6b84-43dd-abf0-c4d9dbb575b9\\":\\"AU-8(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This provides uniformity of time stamps for information systems with multiple system clocks and systems connected over a network."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0251",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Isolate processing threads",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall maintain a separate execution domain for each thread when multi-threaded processing is used.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"bd96bdab-df03-4d98-b170-69197a4a00aa\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"bd96bdab-df03-4d98-b170-69197a4a00aa\\":\\"SC-39(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0031",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Disable default accounts",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The contractor shall include the deactivation of default accounts in the user account management documentation in the [host document].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"2026547a-1547-4627-9ad2-214bd95d4179\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"2026547a-1547-4627-9ad2-214bd95d4179\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_0030\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Default or standard accounts / account names (e.g. Guest) shall be disabled.\\nThese accounts are an easy target even for not-too-experienced attackers."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0144",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prevent split tunnelling with remote devices",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall, in conjunction with a remote device, prevent the device from simultaneously establishing non-remote connections with the system and communicating via some other connection to resources in external networks.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"d0e681f0-cc9c-4ec8-9896-3fd75645a00c\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"d0e681f0-cc9c-4ec8-9896-3fd75645a00c\\":\\"SC-7(7)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This is implemented within remote devices (e.g., notebook computers) through configuration settings to disable split tunnelling in those devices, and by preventing those configuration settings from being readily configurable by users. This control enhancement is implemented within the information system by the detection of split tunnelling (or of configuration settings that allow split tunnelling) in the remote device, and by prohibiting the connection if the remote device is using split tunnelling. Split tunnelling might be desirable by remote users to communicate with local information system resources such as printers/file servers. However, split tunnelling would in effect allow unauthorized external connections, making the system more vulnerable to attack and to exfiltration of organizational information. The use of VPNs for remote connections, when adequately provisioned with appropriate security controls, may provide the organization with sufficient assurance that it can effectively treat such connections as non-remote connections from the confidentiality and integrity perspective. VPNs thus provide a means for allowing non-remote communications paths from remote devices. The use of an adequately provisioned VPN does not eliminate the need for preventing split tunnelling."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0026",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Implement ESA compliant system",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall be compliant with ESA Network Security Policy.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"15df59e9-8c56-41de-b318-7648dcade033\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"15df59e9-8c56-41de-b318-7648dcade033\\":\\"ASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0383",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prevent display of default banner",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prevent the display of applications\' and servers\' default banner.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"0329ae85-3eb9-4a40-8063-a45b2e1b6fa1\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"0329ae85-3eb9-4a40-8063-a45b2e1b6fa1\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Most default banners reveal relevant information on the server and application\\nIndeed, one of the first tasks when conducting an application penetration test is to try to identify the version of the server and the application to pentest. The reason for that is that it allows the tester to discover all the well-known vulnerabilities that are affecting the server and the application.\\nThis process is called application fingerprinting."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0262",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce secure default values for security functions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall enforce the secure default values for security functions.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"7dc47a64-56f1-48b4-8421-253f9776e193\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"7dc47a64-56f1-48b4-8421-253f9776e193\\":\\"TCA_SEC_MNGT_0080\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The default values for security function shall reflect the best possible security. In other words, when configurable, the value chosen as default values should always reflect the strongest security available.\\nFor example if a web application has the option between using http and https, the default value should be https. Downgrading to http is then left as advised choice and to the responsibility of the configuring user."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "08B02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Conformity control of operational software configurations (including packages)",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "08B02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "