ription": "The system shall able to detect when the limit of storage capacity is reached.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"b0538019-cc81-4f96-86e4-94d1bee727cd\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"b0538019-cc81-4f96-86e4-94d1bee727cd\\":\\"AU-5(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Organisations may have multiple audit data storage repositories distributed across multiple information system components, with each repository having different storage volume capacities."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0252",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use hardware separation to facilitate process isolation",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall implement underlying hardware separation mechanisms to facilitate process separation.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"4302252b-5e7a-42d8-9f63-a7995ce3dfc3\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"4302252b-5e7a-42d8-9f63-a7995ce3dfc3\\":\\"SC-39(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Hardware-based separation of information system processes is generally less susceptible to compromise than software-based separation, thus providing greater assurance that the separation will be enforced. Underlying hardware separation mechanisms include, for example, hardware memory management."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0368",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use strong encryption for data stored on the disk",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Only strong encryption and decryption algorithms shall be used for the data stored on disks : custom cryptographic algorithms shall not be implemented.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"67513586-1c4f-4286-bbce-656760a9538a\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"67513586-1c4f-4286-bbce-656760a9538a\\":\\"ASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Use approved public key cryptographic algorithms like RSA, AES.\\nUse strong algorithms asSHA256 or better.\\nGenerate strong cryptographic keys with minimum of 128bit key length and use strong random number generators for defining key."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0245",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Implement hardware separation mechanisms for security function isolation",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use underlying hardware separation mechanisms to implement security function isolation.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"1422c4a8-d6d6-40b7-9105-d551da932176\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"1422c4a8-d6d6-40b7-9105-d551da932176\\":\\"SC-3(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Underlying hardware separation mechanisms include, for example, hardware ring architectures, commonly implemented within microprocessors, and hardware-enforced address segmentation used to support logically distinct storage objects with separate attributes (i.e., readable, writeable)."\n              },\n              "r