	(1513, '9', 'MEHARI_ApplicationSecurity', 'QUESTIONNAIRE', '09', '', '', '', '', '', '', '', '{\n  "category": "09",\n  "index": "9",\n  "type": "MEHARI_ApplicationSecurity",\n  "questions": [\n    {\n      "category": "09A",\n      "index": "9",\n      "type": "CATEGORY",\n      "value": "Application access control ",\n      "children": [\n        {\n          "category": "09A01",\n          "index": "1",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Management of application data access profiles ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "09A01-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has a management policy for access rights to data and information been established, built from an analysis of the security requirements based on the business stakes?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.1.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Business requirements of access control\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.1.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Access control policy\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.1.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A01-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is access to applications and associated data defined in terms of job profiles which regroup roles or functions within the organization (a profile defines access rights available  to holders of the profile)?\\r\\nNote: in certain circumstances the notion of profile may be replaced by the notion of group.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.3; 9.2.5; 9.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of privileged access rights\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Information access restriction\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.2; 11.6.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A01-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is it possible to adjust the access rights (that establish rights attributed to a given profile), variable parameters based on the connection context such as the origin of the request or network paths used, or depending on protection means used (protocol, encryption, etc) and on the classification of the resources accessed?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do the access profiles also allow definition of working time limits and periods in the working calendar (daily hours, weekends, holidays etc.)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.6"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have these profiles and the access rights attributed to the different profiles been approved by the information owners and/or the Information Security Officer?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes of definition and management of rights attributed to profiles under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the list of people allowed to change rights attributed to profiles be strictly limited and that the implementation of these rights (e.g. into tables) be strictly secure and that there exist a reinforced access control for any modification of these rights and that any modification be logged and audited.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is it possible to review at any time the list of profiles and the rights attributed to each profile?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of the totality of rights attributed to each profile and the profile management procedures?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0032",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Only grant access to a subset of user accounts",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The contractor shall include the whitelist of users authorized to access the various systems in the user account management documentation in the [host document].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"99d3b62a-fd17-436d-8cb4-f918be1622e4\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"99d3b62a-fd17-436d-8cb4-f918be1622e4\\":\\"TCA_OS_BIOS_0160\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "When OS services are based on user accounts, only the required subset of users shall be granted access.\\nThis requirement means that the common rule should be to prevent users to use services like FTP. Access should be granted only on a case-by-case basis"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0231",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce system access control policies",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall enforce the implementation of the [System Access Control Policy] to system appliances, objects, operation and data.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"824f2261-17da-436d-8a61-47b489684392\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\",\\"d1896fa0-c90f-40a4-ad1b-7f28052048e5\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"824f2261-17da-436d-8a61-47b489684392\\":\\"TCA_ACCESS_0010\\",\\"d1896fa0-c90f-40a4-ad1b-7f28052048e5\\":\\"AC-3\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "09A02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Management of access authorizations to application data (granting, delegation, revocation) ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "09A02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the procedure of granting access authorization to applications require the formal authorization of line management  (at a sufficiently senior level)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Information access restriction\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.6.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are authorizations granted to named individuals and only as a function of their profile?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.6.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the procedure for granting (or modification or revocation) of access rights (directly or via a profile) strictly controlled?\\r\\nA strict control requires a formal recognition of the signature (electronic or otherwise) of the requester, that the implementation of the profile attributed to users in the form of tables is highly secure and that there be a reinforced access control over the modification of such records and that any modification of records be logged and audited.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of privileged access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a systematic process of updating the table of access rights at the time of departure of personnel (internal or external personnel)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A02-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a systematic process of updating the table of access rights at the time of change of function?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A02-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a strictly controlled process (see below) which allows rights to be delegated, in part or in whole, to a person of choice for a determined period (in case of absence)?\\r\\nIn this case, the delegated rights must no longer be available to the person who has delegated them during this time. The latter however, must have the possibility of taking them back, by which process he or she effectively ends the delegation.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A02-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is it possible to control at any time, for all users, the rights, authorizations and privileges in force?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A02-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of the profiles and authorizations granted to all personnel and the procedures for management of attributed profiles?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0030",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Delete inactive accounts",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The contractor shall include the deletion of inactive accounts in the user account management documentation in the [host document].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"de51f0bb-ad01-47e3-b8a7-a5cd3a22ffd6\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"de51f0bb-ad01-47e3-b8a7-a5cd3a22ffd6\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_0020\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The old and inactive accounts should be deleted.\\nThis prevents illicit use of accounts by other users."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "09A03",\n          "index": "3",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Authentication of the access requester",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "09A03-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the process of distribution or modification of the user credentials guarantee that only the holder of the identifier has access (initial communication is confidential, password change is under the exclusive control of the user, etc.)?  ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": " 9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A03-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the process of creation or modification of a user credentials respect a set of rules which ensures its intrinsic validity?\\r\\nIn the case of passwords: sufficient length (8 characters or more), obligatory mixture of types of characters, frequent change (less than once a month), impossibility of reusing an old password, non-trivial word test using a dictionary, banning of standard systems, first names, anagrams of user name, dates etc.\\r\\nIn the case of certificates or use made of cryptographic mechanisms for authentication: a generation process evaluated or publicly recognized, encryption keys of a sufficient length etc.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": " 9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.3; 11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A03-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the presentation of his credentials by the user guarantee their inviolability?\\r\\nTyping a password will always be a weak point. The only processes whose observation does not divulge information consist either of introducing an object containing a secret (smart card), or using a code which changes at every moment (token card) or using a means of which contains some biometric characteristic.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": " 9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A03-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a guarantee that the credentials, used for authentication, will remain inviolable and authentic while kept or presented by the user or by the user agent?\\r\\nPasswords must be stored encrypted and a preliminary access control must be made before usage. \\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic processing, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a reference organization.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": " 9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A03-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a guarantee that the credentials, used for authentication, will remain inviolable and authentic while transmitted between the user and the target systems?\\r\\nTransmission of a password must be encrypted or use an algorithm which introduces a variable at each transmission. \\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic processing, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a reference organization.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": " 9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A03-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "In the case of multiple incorrect authentication attempts, is there a process which automatically invalidates the user identifier, even the user workstation itself, or a slowing of the authentication process (aimed at preventing connection from an automatic routine)?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": " 9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A03-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the procedure for the replacement of lost or mislaid user authentication means (password, token card) allow for the instant deactivation of the user account?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": " 9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A03-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the procedure for the replacement of lost or mislaid user authentication means (password, token card) allow for an effective control of the requester`s identity?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": " 9.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Password management system\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A03-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are authentication parameters under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that people able to change the definition rules of credentials, the credentials themselves, rules of surveillance of connection attempts etc., be strictly limited and that there exists a reinforced access control to effect these modifications, that these modifications be logged and audited and that a general audit be run at least once a year of all authentication parameters.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A03-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes that guarantee authentication under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of authentication procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect violations attempts and the processes which respond to these violation attempts).",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0194",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Do not transmit passwords in clear text",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Passwords shall never be transmitted in clear text and their encryption shall be done using appropriate algorithms.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"dd60fb91-c654-4336-bae4-cca490e93ab5\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"dd60fb91-c654-4336-bae4-cca490e93ab5\\":\\"IA-5(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This does not apply when passwords are used to unlock hardware authenticators (e.g., Personal Identity Verification cards). Encrypted representations of passwords include, for example, encrypted versions of passwords and one-way cryptographic hashes of passwords."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0111",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Perform self-test",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "A suite of self-tests shall be run (e.g. during initial start-up, periodically during normal operation, at the request of the authorised user) to demonstrate the correct operation of itself.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"ae0bf421-a5e3-44a7-9810-5212a694522c\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"ae0bf421-a5e3-44a7-9810-5212a694522c\\":\\"15.14\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Actions should be taken as the result of self-testing.\\nThe corruption of security data, functions (including the one performing tests) should be also detected"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0339",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Periodically change your keys",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall enforce change of cryptographic keys at a [defined-key-change-interval].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"30f6672d-5f5c-4e3a-876f-452e7561c967\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"30f6672d-5f5c-4e3a-876f-452e7561c967\\":\\"ASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The appropriate key management can be done via a PKI."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0187",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Detect unsuccessful log-in tentative",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall detect when a number of unsuccessful authentication attempts related to a user since the last successful authentication occurred. The number of unsuccessful authentication attempts shall be configurable.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"01544988-edb2-4b68-9013-aa92128223f3\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"01544988-edb2-4b68-9013-aa92128223f3\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0030\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This prevents an attacker to scan all possible passwords for breaking the access control mechanism. They are mandatory to protect from attacks driven by people around authorised user."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0221",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce an unforgeable authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall detect and prevent the use of authentication data that has been copied or forged by any user.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"e79e7cc0-7e61-4337-91c9-3628a57c80f2\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"e79e7cc0-7e61-4337-91c9-3628a57c80f2\\":\\"12.4\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0352",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Validate certification paths",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall validate certificates by constructing a certification path with status information to an accepted trust anchor.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"1dfba2de-063f-4ac7-b4f6-75b76353754c\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"1dfba2de-063f-4ac7-b4f6-75b76353754c\\":\\"IA-5(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Status information for certification paths includes, for example, certificate revocation lists or certificate status protocol responses."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0203",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Token based authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use authentication tokens to authenticate users.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"1d04f0b3-1353-44b6-93a5-6bf484148ab3\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\",\\"9c23d21f-d2dc-4f4f-866b-89cea98c1474\\":\\"ESA\\",\\"4b904608-dc4a-4226-b631-2d167d134c20\\":\\"NIST-FIPS-190\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"1d04f0b3-1353-44b6-93a5-6bf484148ab3\\":\\"IA-5(11)\\",\\"9c23d21f-d2dc-4f4f-866b-89cea98c1474\\":\\"GASF\\",\\"4b904608-dc4a-4226-b631-2d167d134c20\\":\\"Section 4\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The identity of a human user can be proven by requiring the user to demonstrate possession of a physical object which is unique to that user, or to a group of users. Objects used for this it purpose are known as authentication tokens. Since the uniqueness of the information stored on an authentication token is responsible for proving the identity of its bearer to the host system, the information must be protected against duplication or theft. Advanced tokens usually contain a microprocessor and semiconductor memory, and support sophisticated authentication protocols which provide a high level of security.\\n\\nFrom a security standpoint, the strength of token based authentication lies in the fact that the device containing the information which verifies the identity of the user is portable. Therefore, the authentication information can be kept in the user\'s possession. The greatest threat to the security of this type of system is the possibility that an attacker could steal a valid token in order to pose as an authorized user. A sophisticated attacker might also be able to counterfeit a token. These threats can be reduced by requiring the user to submit a password or PIN when the token is used for authentication. There should be a limit to the number of consecutive incorrect PIN submissions. Without the password, a stolen or counterfeited token would not allow an attacker to gain access to the system. This can significantly increase the level of assurance since a user\'s identity is verified based on something the user knows in addition to possession of the token. Compromise of one user\'s token should only compromise that user, not the entire system. Use of tokens with cryptographic capabilities can contribute greatly to the security of an authentication system. In addition, the use of passwords or PINs in combination with authentication tokens is recommended for applications where this approach is practical.\\n\\nThe type of authentication token selected for a particular application will depend on a number of factors."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0349",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Digital signature based authentication (PKI)",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use PKI-based authentication and validate certificates by constructing a certification path with status information to an accepted trust anchor",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"b5eee7db-52af-4163-90d0-20a95051ab0e\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"b5eee7db-52af-4163-90d0-20a95051ab0e\\":\\"IA-5(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Devices requiring unique device-to-device identification and authentication may be defined by type, by device, or by a combination of type/device. Information systems typically use either shared known information (e.g., Media Access Control [MAC] or Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol [TCP/IP] addresses) for device identification or organizational authentication solutions (e.g., IEEE 802.1x and Extensible Authentication Protocol [EAP], Radius server with EAP-Transport Layer Security [TLS] authentication, Kerberos) to identify/authenticate devices on local and/or wide area networks.\\n\\nA local connection is any connection with a device communicating without the use of a network. A network connection is any connection with a device that communicates through a network (e.g., local area or wide area network, Internet). A remote connection is any connection with a device communicating through an external network (e.g., the Internet)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0178",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Enforce user deactivation after failed attempts",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "When the [number of unsuccessful authentication attempts] has been reached or exceeded, the system shall disable the access to the user for a certain time. This time shall be configurable.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"acbf0298-6ac3-459d-ae73-d3cf673f898a\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\",\\"71f95adf-ef1c-49eb-a5ef-94a6fceebe15\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"acbf0298-6ac3-459d-ae73-d3cf673f898a\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0040\\",\\"71f95adf-ef1c-49eb-a5ef-94a6fceebe15\\":\\"AC-7\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This is prevents an attacker to scan all possible passwords for breaking the access control mechanism. They are mandatory to protect from attacks driven by people around authorised user.\\nThis control applies regardless of whether the logon occurs via a local or network connection. Due to the potential for denial of service, automatic lockouts initiated by information systems are usually temporary and automatically release after a predetermined time period established by organizations. If a delay algorithm is selected, organizations may choose to employ different algorithms for different information system components based on the capabilities of those components. Responses to unsuccessful login attempts may be implemented at both the operating system and the application levels."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0220",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Ensure strength of secrets",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "When authentication mechanisms are based on secrets, it shall be ensured that the secrets are of appropriate strength.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"3e56bc69-763d-434b-8fae-725f9af3b522\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"3e56bc69-763d-434b-8fae-725f9af3b522\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_AUTH_0130\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The authentication process may rely on a wide range of mechanisms, some of them requiring additional data only known by the user himself.\\nThis personal data are called secrets; it could be dongle, password, etc.\\nNB.: Secrets are not mandatory. Biometric data (eyes prints or fingerprints) could now be used to recognised users."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "09A04",\n          "index": "4",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Access filtering and management of associations ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "09A04-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does any access to the system require the use of an identifier recognized by the system?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Information access restriction\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.2; 11.6.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A04-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a direct or indirect correspondence between any identifier and a real physical person?\\r\\nIn the case where an application calls another one or calls a system, it may be that the application does not transfer to the target system the identifier which originally made the request. However, the link between that call and the original user identifier must remain traceable after the fact.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Information access restriction\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.2; 11.6.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A04-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have all generic or by-default accounts and passwords been changed or deleted?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A04-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the acceptance of the account identified by the system systematically followed by authentication control?\\r\\nSystematic authentication requires that the process be implemented for all subsystems (remote processing monitor, database management system, batch processes, etc. ), for all application requests, for all access routes and for all ports, including ports reserved for remote maintenance.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A04-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "May the authentication process be repeated during an open session for transactions considered to be sensitive?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.6"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A04-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there an automatic invalidation of the user identifier in the absence of traffic after a defined delay, which requires user re-identification and re-authentication?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Secure log-on procedures\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.5.5"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A04-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are there application access controls which limit the view and access to very sensitive information?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.4.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"System and application access\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.4.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Information access restriction\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.6.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A04-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a systematic control of the profile and connection context of the requester and of their appropriateness for the access requested?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A04-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the process of definition and management of access filtering rules under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the list of persons able to change the filtering security parameters be extremely limited, and that there be a reinforced access control in order to be able to effect such modification and that any modification be logged an audited.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A04-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes that guarantee access filtering under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of access control procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect change attempts and the processes which respond to these change attempts).",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0353",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Map the authenticated identity to the account",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall map the authenticated identity to the account of the individual.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"ac60c56b-0a65-41ae-9e41-150be664da2e\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"ac60c56b-0a65-41ae-9e41-150be664da2e\\":\\"IA-5(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0130",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Automatically lock session after inactivity",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The information system shall prevent further access to the system by initiating a session lock after a�[period of inactivity].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"88260c9d-3c8a-4d60-9d4d-9abf29fc15c6\\":\\"NIST\\",\\"b458b2f7-c61f-4edc-b206-121878c2a35b\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\",\\"711a1452-d532-4496-aa98-0a5b815f5e1e\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"88260c9d-3c8a-4d60-9d4d-9abf29fc15c6\\":\\"AC-11\\",\\"b458b2f7-c61f-4edc-b206-121878c2a35b\\":\\"A.11.5.5\\",\\"711a1452-d532-4496-aa98-0a5b815f5e1e\\":\\"TCA_SYS_ACC_0040\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Session locks are temporary actions taken when users stop work and move away from the immediate vicinity of information systems but do not want to log out because of the temporary nature of their absences. Session locks are implemented where session activities can be determined. This is typically at the operating system level, but can also be at the application level. Session locks are not an acceptable substitute for logging out of information systems, for example, if organizations require users to log out at the end of workdays."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0271",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "E-commerce",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The security protection of the data involved in electronic transaction shall be ensured. Mechanisms to protect against malicious activities, contracts dispute or repudiation, and all other confidentiality and integrity flaws shall be implemented.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"ec13cef6-2383-4ed7-81a9-ac18f44ca45e\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"ec13cef6-2383-4ed7-81a9-ac18f44ca45e\\":\\"A.10.9.1\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0391",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use human identification challenges",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use challenge-response tests to idendify whether or not the user is human.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"5611e9d8-c5fc-4bfa-9459-e819b347ca4e\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"5611e9d8-c5fc-4bfa-9459-e819b347ca4e\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This applies mostly for services available to web users. Challenge-response systems, widely known as CAPTCHAs (Completely Automated Public Turing test to tell Computers and Humans Apart), permit to restrict the use of automatic scripts for specific features (e.g. browsing, registering)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0222",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Re-authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall re-authenticate the user under [specific conditions].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"8bc9f6a5-d728-4138-8cc5-6d9520fd94c0\\":\\"CC\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"8bc9f6a5-d728-4138-8cc5-6d9520fd94c0\\":\\"12.4\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0383",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prevent display of default banner",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prevent the display of applications\' and servers\' default banner.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"0329ae85-3eb9-4a40-8063-a45b2e1b6fa1\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"0329ae85-3eb9-4a40-8063-a45b2e1b6fa1\\":\\"GASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Most default banners reveal relevant information on the server and application\\nIndeed, one of the first tasks when conducting an application penetration test is to try to identify the version of the server and the application to pentest. The reason for that is that it allows the tester to discover all the well-known vulnerabilities that are affecting the server and the application.\\nThis process is called application fingerprinting."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "09A05",\n          "index": "5",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Authentication of the application for access to sensitive applications",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "09A05-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a possibility to declare applications as sensitive and, as such, requiring an authentication of the application accessed?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A05-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a mechanism of authentication of the application called before access to a sensitive application from the internal network?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A05-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the authentication mechanism of the accessed sensitive applications provide a recognized strong level of security?\\r\\nNotably the usage of a simple password will always be a weakness. The only methods recognized as strong, that is observable without divulging information, are those based on cryptographic algorithms.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A05-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Do the security equipment that retain credentials (e.g. passwords, calling number, etc.) use mechanisms which guarantee their impregnability and authenticity?\\r\\nPasswords must be stored encrypted and a preliminary control of the user must be made before usage.\\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A05-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the transmission of credentials (e.g. passwords, calling address, etc.) between calling user equipment and authentication systems use mechanisms which guarantee their impregnability and authenticity?\\r\\nTransmission of a password must be encrypted or use an algorithm which introduces a variable at each transmission. \\r\\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A05-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the revoked keys management procedure guarantee that the control systems take into consideration in real time any revocation of keys?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A05-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the revoked keys management procedure guarantee that the control systems systematically test that the keys used have not been revoked?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09A05-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes that guarantee the authentication of the accessed entities under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there is an audit at least once a year of the authentication procedures and processes.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0194",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Do not transmit passwords in clear text",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Passwords shall never be transmitted in clear text and their encryption shall be done using appropriate algorithms.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"dd60fb91-c654-4336-bae4-cca490e93ab5\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"dd60fb91-c654-4336-bae4-cca490e93ab5\\":\\"IA-5(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This does not apply when passwords are used to unlock hardware authenticators (e.g., Personal 