This control enhancement ensures that there is predictable behaviour in the face of invalid inputs by specifying information system responses that facilitate transitioning the system to known states without adverse, unintended side effects."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "09B05",\n          "index": "5",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Continuous (plausibility, ..) checks on data processing ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "09B05-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have the checks that should be made to verify consistency of the data after processing by the application been analyzed with the users (test variables, ratios, evolution and comparison before and after processing, etc.), and have the corresponding checks been implemented in the applications?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "12.2.1; 12.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09B05-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the parameters for these checks recorded in tables separated from the application code and easily verifiable?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09B05-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes insuring continuous checking of the data processing under strict control?\\r\\nStrict control requires that the corresponding software is validated and is subject to a regular integrity check (sealing)  and that there is an audit at least once a year of the control process and procedures (including procedures for detecting attempts at modification and for reacting to these attempts).",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09B05-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the check parameters under strict control?\\r\\nStrict control requires that the list of people authorized to change the control parameters is very limited, that strong access control is applied to all modifications, and that the modifications are logged and audited. ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09B05-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the checks that exist integrated into an operational procedure that signals and handles any errors? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0117",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Output validation",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Any output from a software shall be validated and sanitized to ensure that further operations performed on this data (e.g. storage) is correct, safe and appropriate.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"d5b9fb50-28b9-4fb9-97b2-262e9c0fa644\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\",\\"2edcf9a1-fac6-42c8-8d26-799f36409125\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"d5b9fb50-28b9-4fb9-97b2-262e9c0fa644\\":\\"A.12.2.4\\",\\"2edcf9a1-fac6-42c8-8d26-799f36409125\\":\\"SI-15\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This requirement means that data shall be verified before being sent out to minimize security breaches, e.g.. a string input through a MMI and sent to a shell.\\nThis requirement is especially important to counter security breaches of third party programs. This reduces the use of these programs to known and tested vulnerabilities."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0119",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Ensure a predictable behaviour on invalid inputs/outputs",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall behave in a predictable and documented manner that reflects organisational and system objectives when invalid inputs/outputs are received/sent.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"4bf93864-5dd7-4a27-9c93-1cc5fb88b98c\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"4bf93864-5dd7-4a27-9c93-1cc5fb88b98c\\":\\"SI-10(3)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "A common vulnerability in organisational information systems is unpredictable behaviour when invalid inputs are received. This control enhancement ensures that there is predictable behaviour in the face of invalid inputs by specifying information system responses that facilitate transitioning the system to known states without adverse, unintended side effects."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n        