n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09G01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the anomaly diagnostic system trigger an alarm in real time to a permanent surveillance team able or by direct call and able to react without delay?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "16.1.4",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A16\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Information security incident management\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A16.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Management of information security incidents and improvements\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"16.1.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Assessment of and decision on information security events\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09G01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "For each case of alert has the expected response from the intervention team been defined and is the availability of the intervention team sufficient to face this expectation?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "16.1.4",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A16\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Information security incident management\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A16.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Management of information security incidents and improvements\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"16.1.4\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Assessment of and decision on information security events\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09G01-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the parameters defining the elements to record and the diagnostic analysis effected on these elements strictly protected (restricted access rights and strict authentication ) against illicit modification?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09G01-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Does the stopping of the recording and record processing system trigger an alarm with the surveillance team?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09G01-11",\n              "index": "11",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the procedures for recording, processing and diagnostic analysis and the availability of the intervention team regularly audited?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0092",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Take action on audit processing failures",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall be able to take the [appropriate action] when an audit processing failure is detected.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"64d4d890-6df1-4492-84d5-5f59776950a2\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"64d4d890-6df1-4492-84d5-5f59776950a2\\":\\"AU-5\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The followings are examples of action: shut down information system, overwrite oldest audit records, stop generating audit records.\\nOrganisations may choose to define additional actions for different audit processing failures (e.g., by type, by location, by severity, or a combination of such factors). This applies to each audit data storage repository (i.e., distinct information system component where audit records are stored), the total audit storage capacity of organizations (i.e., all audit data storage repositories combined) or both."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        }\n      ],\n      "gasf": [],\n      "answers": {\n        "MEHARI_W": "",\n        "MEHARI_Min": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n        "MEHARI_Max": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n      },\n      "referenceObject": null,\n      "identifier": null,\n      "objType": "Audit",\n      "lockedBy": null\n    },\n    {\n      "category": "09H",\n      "index": "9",\n      "type": "CATEGORY",\n      "value": "Security of application services and transactions",\n      "children": [\n        {\n          "category": "09H01",\n          "index": "1",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Securing application services on public networks\\r\\nInformation involved in application services passing over public networks should be protected from fraudulent activity, contract dispute and unauthorized disclosure and modification",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the migration of existing services from private to public networks organized with the associated parties ?\\r\\nAttention to the risk owners and all users should be prominent and the management requirements issues central to the decision",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Securing application services on public networks\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have the security requirements specific to making information available on public networks been analyzed and thus defined the necessary protections and assurance?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Information security requirements analysis and specification\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.9.1"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have the classification levels for the information and services assets received a special attention?\\r\\nThe value of Personally Identifiable Information and strategic elements for the organization should be carefully established (see worksheets T1 to T3)",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Securing application services on public networks\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have Service level agreements for the permanence and continuity of the service been negotiated with the service providers ?\\r\\nThis is very important in the case of services obtained over the cloud and appropriate penalties should be clearly understood by the organization (e.g. in the case of interruption by the provider (error, accident, strike, bankruptcy, takeover, ...)) including the capacity to recover the proprietary data ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the protection and verification of transactions appropriately managed?\\r\\nIncluding payment information provided by the customer, integrity, confidentiality, protection against replay, confirmation of receipt, non-repudiation, etc. to guard against fraud.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Securing application services on public networks\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are Service level agreements in place concerning the confidentiality of the information treated and/or stored by the service provider?\\r\\nMeans to control the agreements and to react rapidly should be guaranteed to the organization.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Information security requirements analysis and specification\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have protections to the security risks associated to web access been integrated to the application?\\r\\nOWASP references 10 important threats like Injection flaws, cross site scripting and request forgery, broken sessions, insecure direct object references and cryptographic storage, security misconfiguration, failure to restrict URL access, insufficient transport layer protection, unvalidated redirects and forwards)",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-08",\n              "index": "8",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Have the likelihood of attacks and threats been specifically analyzed for the application services?\\r\\nCareful attention to  the level of the natural exposure settings in the worksheet Expo is required, firstly cyber attacks",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Securing application services on public networks\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-09",\n              "index": "9",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the authentication, control of rights and logging mechanisms specifically enforced for administrative operations?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.1",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.1\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Information security requirements analysis and specification\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-10",\n              "index": "10",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the mutual levels of confidence (of each other`s identity, authorization, level of trust required in the integrity  and confidentiality of data exchanged) considered in regard of the requirements?\\r\\nThe quality of the security services 09A to 09G above should be appropriate with the requirements of the application service.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Securing application services on public networks\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H01-11",\n              "index": "11",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular review, at least once a year, of the application services and corrective solutions envisaged?\\r\\nThis review shall also consider shadow applications and data on public networks",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0271",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "E-commerce",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The security protection of the data involved in electronic transaction shall be ensured. Mechanisms to protect against malicious activities, contracts dispute or repudiation, and all other confidentiality and integrity flaws shall be implemented.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"ec13cef6-2383-4ed7-81a9-ac18f44ca45e\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"ec13cef6-2383-4ed7-81a9-ac18f44ca45e\\":\\"A.10.9.1\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0105",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Protect information during pre/post transmission handling",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall maintain the confidentiality and integrity of information during preparation for transmission and during reception.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"88cbbda5-6f4f-4234-9880-26f5584fa1b7\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"88cbbda5-6f4f-4234-9880-26f5584fa1b7\\":\\"SC-8(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Information can be either unintentionally or maliciously disclosed or modified during preparation for transmission or during reception including, for example, during aggregation, at protocol transformation points, and during packing/unpacking. These unauthorized disclosures or modifications compromise the confidentiality or integrity of the information."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0272",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "On-line transactions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Online dealings shall be protected against information security problems and incidents. Examples of suche incidents are incomplete transmission and all unauthorized message alteration, disclosure, duplication or replay.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"cdf59867-ff54-4312-8eca-ef82f9b8b2b5\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"cdf59867-ff54-4312-8eca-ef82f9b8b2b5\\":\\"A.10.9.2\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0258",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prevent display of management-related functionalities to non-privileged users",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prevent the presentation of information system management-related functionality at an interface for non-privileged users.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"04da66df-bda0-46bc-a96c-c81933d27273\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"04da66df-bda0-46bc-a96c-c81933d27273\\":\\"SC-2(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This ensures that administration options (e.g., administrator privileges) are not available to general users (including prohibiting the use of the grey-out option commonly used to eliminate accessibility to such information). Such restrictions include, for example, not presenting administration options until users establish sessions with administrator privileges."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0273",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Protect integrity of information published through available system",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The integrity of publicly available information system shall be protected to prevent any integrity modification.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"c69fee16-5b83-41f8-bd15-295cc0c68f59\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"c69fee16-5b83-41f8-bd15-295cc0c68f59\\":\\"A.10.9.3\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "09H02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Protecting application services transactions",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "09H02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are specific security protection requirements defined and used for critical transactions attached to the application?\\r\\nCompliance with legal and regulatory requirements is imperative.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protecting application services transactions\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the non disclosure of critical transactions protected by using strong cryptographic controls?\\r\\nSecret authentication information of all parties should be valid and verified, communication paths between them are encrypted, protocols used are secured, storage of the transaction details are located in a protected environment.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protecting application services transactions\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the integrity of critical transactions protected by using electronic signatures?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protecting application services transactions\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the service of a trusted authority protected throughout the entire end-to-end certificate/signature management process?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "14.1.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A14\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"System acquisition, development and maintenance\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A14.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Security requirements of information systems\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"14.1.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Protecting application services transactions\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H02-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are administrators and users trained on their operations, rights and responsibilities and aware of the risks with networked applications?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H02-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular review, at least once a year, of the service transactions and corrective solutions envisaged?\\r\\nThis review shall also consider new threats and vulnerabilities on the applications and data on public networks",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0128",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Only allow certificate authorities for verification of protected sessions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall only allow the installation of [certificate authorities] for verification of the establishment of protected sessions.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"c24e4001-9332-47eb-b03f-63bdd49a9833\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"c24e4001-9332-47eb-b03f-63bdd49a9833\\":\\"SC-23(5)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Reliance on certificate authorities (CAs) for the establishment of secure sessions includes, for example, the use of Secure Socket Layer (SSL) and/or Transport Layer Security (TLS) certificates. These certificates, after verification by the respective certificate authorities, facilitate the establishment of protected sessions between web clients and web servers."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0352",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Validate certification paths",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall validate certificates by constructing a certification path with status information to an accepted trust anchor.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"1dfba2de-063f-4ac7-b4f6-75b76353754c\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"1dfba2de-063f-4ac7-b4f6-75b76353754c\\":\\"IA-5(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Status information for certification paths includes, for example, certificate revocation lists or certificate status protocol responses."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0271",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "E-commerce",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The security protection of the data involved in electronic transaction shall be ensured. Mechanisms to protect against malicious activities, contracts dispute or repudiation, and all other confidentiality and integrity flaws shall be implemented.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"ec13cef6-2383-4ed7-81a9-ac18f44ca45e\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"ec13cef6-2383-4ed7-81a9-ac18f44ca45e\\":\\"A.10.9.1\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0349",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Digital signature based authentication (PKI)",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall use PKI-based authentication and validate certificates by constructing a certification path with status information to an accepted trust anchor",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"b5eee7db-52af-4163-90d0-20a95051ab0e\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"b5eee7db-52af-4163-90d0-20a95051ab0e\\":\\"IA-5(2)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "Devices requiring unique device-to-device identification and authentication may be defined by type, by device, or by a combination of type/device. Information systems typically use either shared known information (e.g., Media Access Control [MAC] or Transmission Control Protocol/Internet Protocol [TCP/IP] addresses) for device identification or organizational authentication solutions (e.g., IEEE 802.1x and Extensible Authentication Protocol [EAP], Radius server with EAP-Transport Layer Security [TLS] authentication, Kerberos) to identify/authenticate devices on local and/or wide area networks.\\n\\nA local connection is any connection with a device communicating without the use of a network. A network connection is any connection with a device that communicates through a network (e.g., local area or wide area network, Internet). A remote connection is any connection with a device communicating through an external network (e.g., the Internet)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0369",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Avoid information leakage of stored information",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Unauthorised information disclosure shall be prevented.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"4b911833-8300-440a-9485-68b101926681\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"4b911833-8300-440a-9485-68b101926681\\":\\"A.12.5.4\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0272",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "On-line transactions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Online dealings shall be protected against information security problems and incidents. Examples of suche incidents are incomplete transmission and all unauthorized message alteration, disclosure, duplication or replay.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"cdf59867-ff54-4312-8eca-ef82f9b8b2b5\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"cdf59867-ff54-4312-8eca-ef82f9b8b2b5\\":\\"A.10.9.2\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "09H03",\n          "index": "3",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Electronic messaging",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "09H03-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are there policies for the use of the various types of electronic messaging services, based on business security requirements?\\r\\nExamples: email, social networking, electronic data interchange, instant messaging, file sharing ...",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H03-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is an approval and authorization process, based on the policies, in place prior to using these services?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H03-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are stronger levels of authentication established for controlling access from publicly accessible networks?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H03-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the exchanges requiring protection commensurate with the classification scheme adopted by the organization?\\r\\nEncryption, signature,authorized access, modification, denial of service, non repudiation.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "09H03-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are administrators and users trained on the operations, rights and responsibilities and aware of the risks with electronic messaging?\\r\\nTraining  sessions and awareness messages should be regularly organized.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0271",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "E-commerce",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The security protection of the data involved in electronic transaction shall be ensured. Mechanisms to protect against malicious activities, contracts dispute or repudiation, and all other confidentiality and integrity flaws shall be implemented.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "3",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"ec13cef6-2383-4ed7-81a9-ac18f44ca45e\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"ec13cef6-2383-4ed7-81a9-ac18f44ca45e\\":\\"A.10.9.1\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0106",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Check XML messages",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "All XML messages shall be validated via XML Schema validation.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"c32e8b01-270d-4245-a5ca-6dfde02a9119\\":\\"ESA\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"c32e8b01-270d-4245-a5ca-6dfde02a9119\\":\\"ASF\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0272",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "On-line transactions",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "Online dealings shall be protected against information security problems and incidents. Examples of suche incidents are incomplete transmission and all unauthorized message alteration, disclosure, duplication or replay.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"cdf59867-ff54-4312-8eca-ef82f9b8b2b5\\":\\"ISO-27001:2005\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"cdf59867-ff54-4312-8eca-ef82f9b8b2b5\\":\\"A.10.9.2\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "-"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        }\n      ],\n      "gasf": [],\n      "answers": {\n        "MEHARI_W": "",\n        "MEHARI_Min": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n        "MEHARI_Max": "",\n        "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n      },\n      "referenceObject": null,\n      "identifier": null,\n      "objType": "Audit",\n      "lockedBy": null\n    }\n  ],\n  "identifier": null,\n  "objType": "Audit",\n  "lockedBy": null\n}'),
	(1514, '9', 'Application access control ', 'CATEGORY', '09A', '09', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1515, '1', 'Management of application data access profiles ', 'CATEGORY', '09A01', '09A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1516, '1', 'Has a management policy for access rights to data and information been established, built from an analysis of the security requirements based on the business stakes?', 'QUESTION', '09A01-01', '09A01', '2', '', '', 'E1', '9.1.1', '11.1.1', NULL),
	(1517, '2', 'Is access to applications and associated data defined in terms of job profiles which regroup roles or functions within the organization (a profile defines access rights available  to holders of the profile)?\r\nNote: in certain circumstances the notion of profile may be replaced by the notion of group.', 'QUESTION', '09A01-02', '09A01', '4', '2', '', 'E1', '9.2.3; 9.2.5; 9.4.1', '11.2.2; 11.6.1', NULL),
	(1518, '3', 'Is it possible to adjust the access rights (that establish rights attributed to a given profile), variable parameters based on the connection context such as the origin of the request or network paths used, or depending on protection means used (protocol, encryption, etc) and on the classification of the resources accessed?', 'QUESTION', '09A01-03', '09A01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1519, '4', 'Do the access profiles also allow definition of working time limits and periods in the working calendar (daily hours, weekends, holidays etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '09A01-04', '09A01', '2', '', '', 'E3', '9.4.2', '11.5.6', NULL),
	(1520, '5', 'Have these profiles and the access rights attributed to the different profiles been approved by the information owners and/or the Information Security Officer?', 'QUESTION', '09A01-05', '09A01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1521, '6', 'Are the processes of definition and management of rights attributed to profiles under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the list of people allowed to change rights attributed to profiles be strictly limited and that the implementation of these rights (e.g. into tables) be strictly secure and that there exist a reinforced access control for any modification of these rights and that any modification be logged and audited.', 'QUESTION', '09A01-06', '09A01', '4', '2', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1522, '7', 'Is it possible to review at any time the list of profiles and the rights attributed to each profile?', 'QUESTION', '09A01-07', '09A01', '2', '2', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1523, '8', 'Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of the totality of rights attributed to each profile and the profile management procedures?', 'QUESTION', '09A01-08', '09A01', '4', '2', '', 'C1', '9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1524, '2', 'Management of access authorizations to application data (granting, delegation, revocation) ', 'CATEGORY', '09A02', '09A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1525, '1', 'Does the procedure of granting access authorization to applications require the formal authorization of line management  (at a sufficiently senior level)?', 'QUESTION', '09A02-01', '09A02', '4', '2', '', 'E1', '9.4.1', '11.6.1', NULL),
	(1526, '2', 'Are authorizations granted to named individuals and only as a function of their profile?', 'QUESTION', '09A02-02', '09A02', '2', '', '', 'E1', '', '11.6.1', NULL),
	(1527, '3', 'Is the procedure for granting (or modification or revocation) of access rights (directly or via a profile) strictly controlled?\r\nA strict control requires a formal recognition of the signature (electronic or otherwise) of the requester, that the implementation of the profile attributed to users in the form of tables is highly secure and that there be a reinforced access control over the modification of such records and that any modification of records be logged and audited.', 'QUESTION', '09A02-03', '09A02', '4', '2', '3', 'E2', '9.2.3', '11.2.2', NULL),
	(1528, '4', 'Is there a systematic process of updating the table of access rights at the time of departure of personnel (internal or external personnel)?', 'QUESTION', '09A02-04', '09A02', '4', '', '', 'E2', '9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1529, '5', 'Is there a systematic process of updating the table of access rights at the time of change of function?', 'QUESTION', '09A02-05', '09A02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1530, '6', 'Is there a strictly controlled process (see below) which allows rights to be delegated, in part or in whole, to a person of choice for a determined period (in case of absence)?\r\nIn this case, the delegated rights must no longer be available to the person who has delegated them during this time. The latter however, must have the possibility of taking them back, by which process he or she effectively ends the delegation.', 'QUESTION', '09A02-06', '09A02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1531, '7', 'Is it possible to control at any time, for all users, the rights, authorizations and privileges in force?', 'QUESTION', '09A02-07', '09A02', '2', '', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1532, '8', 'Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of the profiles and authorizations granted to all personnel and the procedures for management of attributed profiles?', 'QUESTION', '09A02-08', '09A02', '1', '2', '', 'C1', '9.2.5', '11.2.4', NULL),
	(1533, '3', 'Authentication of the access requester', 'CATEGORY', '09A03', '09A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1534, '1', 'Does the process of distribution or modification of the user credentials guarantee that only the holder of the identifier has access (initial communication is confidential, password change is under the exclusive control of the user, etc.)?  ', 'QUESTION', '09A03-01', '09A03', '2', '1', '', 'E1', ' 9.4.3', '11.5.3', NULL),
	(1535, '2', 'Does the process of creation or modification of a user credentials respect a set of rules which ensures its intrinsic validity?\r\nIn the case of passwords: sufficient length (8 characters or more), obligatory mixture of types of characters, frequent change (less than once a month), impossibility of reusing an old password, non-trivial word test using a dictionary, banning of standard systems, first names, anagrams of user name, dates etc.\r\nIn the case of certificates or use made of cryptographic mechanisms for authentication: a generation process evaluated or publicly recognized, encryption keys of a sufficient length etc.', 'QUESTION', '09A03-02', '09A03', '4', '2', '', 'E2', ' 9.4.3', '11.2.3; 11.5.3', NULL),
	(1536, '3', 'Does the presentation of his credentials by the user guarantee their inviolability?\r\nTyping a password will always be a weak point. The only processes whose observation does not divulge information consist either of introducing an object containing a secret (smart card), or using a code which changes at every moment (token card) or using a means of which contains some biometric characteristic.', 'QUESTION', '09A03-03', '09A03', '4', '2', '', 'E3', ' 9.4.3', '11.5.3', NULL),
	(1537, '4', 'Is there a guarantee that the credentials, used for authentication, will remain inviolable and authentic while kept or presented by the user or by the user agent?\r\nPasswords must be stored encrypted and a preliminary access control must be made before usage. \r\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic processing, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a reference organization.', 'QUESTION', '09A03-04', '09A03', '2', '2', '3', 'E2', ' 9.4.3', '11.5.3', NULL),
	(1538, '5', 'Is there a guarantee that the credentials, used for authentication, will remain inviolable and authentic while transmitted between the user and the target systems?\r\nTransmission of a password must be encrypted or use an algorithm which introduces a variable at each transmission. \r\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic processing, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a reference organization.', 'QUESTION', '09A03-05', '09A03', '2', '2', '3', 'E3', ' 9.4.3', '11.5.3', NULL),
	(1539, '6', 'In the case of multiple incorrect authentication attempts, is there a process which automatically invalidates the user identifier, even the user workstation itself, or a slowing of the authentication process (aimed at preventing connection from an automatic routine)?', 'QUESTION', '09A03-06', '09A03', '4', '2', '', 'E2', ' 9.4.3', '11.5.3', NULL),
	(1540, '7', 'Does the procedure for the replacement of lost or mislaid user authentication means (password, token card) allow for the instant deactivation of the user account?', 'QUESTION', '09A03-07', '09A03', '2', '2', '', 'E2', ' 9.4.3', '11.5.3', NULL),
	(1541, '8', 'Does the procedure for the replacement of lost or mislaid user authentication means (password, token card) allow for an effective control of the requester`s identity?', 'QUESTION', '09A03-08', '09A03', '2', '2', '', 'E3', ' 9.4.3', '11.5.3', NULL),
	(1542, '9', 'Are authentication parameters under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that people able to change the definition rules of credentials, the credentials themselves, rules of surveillance of connection attempts etc., be strictly limited and that there exists a reinforced access control to effect these modifications, that these modifications be logged and audited and that a general audit be run at least once a year of all authentication parameters.', 'QUESTION', '09A03-09', '09A03', '4', '2', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1543, '10', 'Are the processes that guarantee authentication under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of authentication procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect violations attempts and the processes which respond to these violation attempts).', 'QUESTION', '09A03-10', '09A03', '4', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1544, '4', 'Access filtering and management of associations ', 'CATEGORY', '09A04', '09A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1545, '1', 'Does any access to the system require the use of an identifier recognized by the system?', 'QUESTION', '09A04-01', '09A04', '1', '2', '', 'E1', '9.4.1', '11.5.2; 11.6.1', NULL),
	(1546, '2', 'Is there a direct or indirect correspondence between any identifier and a real physical person?\r\nIn the case where an application calls another one or calls a system, it may be that the application does not transfer to the target system the identifier which originally made the request. However, the link between that call and the original user identifier must remain traceable after the fact.', 'QUESTION', '09A04-02', '09A04', '4', '2', '', 'E1', '9.4.1', '11.5.2; 11.6.1', NULL),
	(1547, '3', 'Have all generic or by-default accounts and passwords been changed or deleted?', 'QUESTION', '09A04-03', '09A04', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '11.5.2', NULL),
	(1548, '4', 'Is the acceptance of the account identified by the system systematically followed by authentication control?\r\nSystematic authentication requires that the process be implemented for all subsystems (remote processing monitor, database management system, batch processes, etc. ), for all application requests, for all access routes and for all ports, including ports reserved for remote maintenance.', 'QUESTION', '09A04-04', '09A04', '2', '2', '', 'E2', '', '11.5.2', NULL),
	(1549, '5', 'May the authentication process be repeated during an open session for transactions considered to be sensitive?', 'QUESTION', '09A04-05', '09A04', '4', '', '', 'E3', '9.4.2', '11.5.6', NULL),
	(1550, '6', 'Is there an automatic invalidation of the user identifier in the absence of traffic after a defined delay, which requires user re-identification and re-authentication?', 'QUESTION', '09A04-06', '09A04', '4', '', '', 'E3', '9.4.2', '11.5.5', NULL),
	(1551, '7', 'Are there application access controls which limit the view and access to very sensitive information?', 'QUESTION', '09A04-07', '09A04', '4', '', '', 'E3', '9.4.1', '11.6.1', NULL),
	(1552, '8', 'Is there a systematic control of the profile and connection context of the requester and of their appropriateness for the access requested?', 'QUESTION', '09A04-08', '09A04', '4', '2', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(1553, '9', 'Is the process of definition and management of access filtering rules under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the list of persons able to change the filtering security parameters be extremely limited, and that there be a reinforced access control in order to be able to effect such modification and that any modification be logged an audited.', 'QUESTION', '09A04-09', '09A04', '4', '2', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(1554, '10', 'Are the processes that guarantee access filtering under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there be an audit at least once a year of access control procedures and processes (including the processes which aim to detect change attempts and the processes which respond to these change attempts).', 'QUESTION', '09A04-10', '09A04', '4', '3', '', 'R2', '', '', NULL),
	(1555, '5', 'Authentication of the application for access to sensitive applications', 'CATEGORY', '09A05', '09A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(1556, '1', 'Is there a possibility to declare applications as sensitive and, as such, requiring an authentication of the application accessed?', 'QUESTION', '09A05-01', '09A05', '4', '1', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1557, '2', 'Is there a mechanism of authentication of the application called before access to a sensitive application from the internal network?', 'QUESTION', '09A05-02', '09A05', '4', '1', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1558, '3', 'Does the authentication mechanism of the accessed sensitive applications provide a recognized strong level of security?\r\nNotably the usage of a simple password will always be a weakness. The only methods recognized as strong, that is observable without divulging information, are those based on cryptographic algorithms.', 'QUESTION', '09A05-03', '09A05', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1559, '4', 'Do the security equipment that retain credentials (e.g. passwords, calling number, etc.) use mechanisms which guarantee their impregnability and authenticity?\r\nPasswords must be stored encrypted and a preliminary control of the user must be made before usage.\r\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.', 'QUESTION', '09A05-04', '09A05', '4', '3', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1560, '5', 'Does the transmission of credentials (e.g. passwords, calling address, etc.) between calling user equipment and authentication systems use mechanisms which guarantee their impregnability and authenticity?\r\nTransmission of a password must be encrypted or use an algorithm which introduces a variable at each transmission. \r\nIn the case of authentication using cryptographic procedures, the mechanism must provide solid guarantees validated by a recognized organization.', 'QUESTION', '09A05-05', '09A05', '4', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1561, '6', 'Does the revoked keys management procedure guarantee that the control systems take into consideration in real time any revocation of keys?', 'QUESTION', '09A05-06', '09A05', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(1562, '7', 'Does the revoked keys management procedure guarantee that the control systems systematically test that the keys used have not been revoked?', 'QUESTION', '09A05-07', '09A05', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(1563, '8', 'Are the processes that guarantee the authentication of the accessed entities under strict control?\r\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there is an audit at least once a year of the authentication procedures and processes.', 'QUESTION', '09A05-08', '09A05', '4', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
