ment (or the manager responsible for external service providers) at a sufficiently high level?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "6.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A6\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Organization of information security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A6.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Internal organization\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"6.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation of duties\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.1.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "11E01-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the process of attributing special rights allocated only in relation to the profile of the holder?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "6.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A6\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Organization of information security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A6.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Internal organization\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"6.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation of duties\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "10.1.3"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "11E01-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the process of granting (modification or revocation) of special rights to an individual strictly controlled?\\r\\nA strict control requires a formal recognition of the signature (electronic or not) of the requester, that there be a tight control of access in order to attribute or modify such rights and that any modification of special rights be logged and audited.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.3; 9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.3\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Management of privileged access rights\\"},{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.2"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "11E01-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a systematic process of removal of special rights at the time of departure or role change of user support operations staff?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "11E01-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of all special rights attributed ?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "1",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "9.2.5",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A9\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Access control\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A9.2\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"User access management\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"9.2.5\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Review of user access rights\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": "11.2.4"\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0258",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Prevent display of management-related functionalities to non-privileged users",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall prevent the presentation of information system management-related functionality at an interface for non-privileged users.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"04da66df-bda0-46bc-a96c-c81933d27273\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"04da66df-bda0-46bc-a96c-c81933d27273\\":\\"SC-2(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "This ensures that administration options (e.g., administrator privileges) are not available to general users (including prohibiting the use of the grey-out option commonly used to eliminate accessibility to such information). Such restrictions include, for example, not presenting administration options until users establish sessions with administrator privileges."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "11E02",\n          "index": "2",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Authentication and control of the access rights of administrators and operational personnel ",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "11E02-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the authentication of the administrator required before taking control of a user workstation? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "4",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "6.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A6\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Organization of information security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A6.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Internal organization\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"6.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation of duties\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "11E02-02",\n              "index": "2",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is the authentication protocol used for administrators or holders of special rights considered to be secure?\\r\\nAn authentication protocol is considered secure if it is not susceptible to being broken by a listening device on the network or rendered inoperable by specialists tools (in particular password crack tools). Such security usually uses cryptographic methods.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "4",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "6.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A6\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Organization of information security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A6.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Internal organization\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"6.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation of duties\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "11E02-03",\n              "index": "3",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the rules, for instance in the case of passwords, considered to be very strict?\\r\\nStrict rules impose the use of tested non-trivial passwords, using a mixture of different types of characters and of a reasonable length (ten characters). It is desirable that these rules have been approved by the Information Security Officer",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "6.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A6\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Organization of information security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A6.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Internal organization\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"6.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation of duties\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "11E02-04",\n              "index": "4",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a consistent control of the administrator`s rights, of its context, and of the suitability of this context with the requested access, as per formal rules of access control?",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "6.1.2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A6\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Organization of information security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A6.1\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Internal organization\\",\\"ControlId\\":\\"6.1.2\\",\\"Control\\":\\"Segregation of duties\\"}]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "11E02-05",\n              "index": "5",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are authentication parameters under strict control?\\r\\nA strict control requires that the list of people able to change authentication rules, the credentials themselves and the surveillance rules of connection attempts be strictly limited, that there be a reinforced access control in order to be able to modify these rights and that any modification of these rights be logged and audited and that there be a general audit at least once a year of all authentication parameters.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "2",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "11E02-06",\n              "index": "6",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Are the processes that guarantee authentication under strict control? \\r\\nA strict control requires that the software used has been validated and undergoes a regular test for integrity (seal) and that there is an audit at least once a year of the authentication procedures and processes.",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "11E02-07",\n              "index": "7",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Is there a regular audit of the procedures of  the security parameters attached to protecting profiles and rights? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "4",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n                "MEHARI_Max": "3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "gasf": [\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0354",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Use cryptographic bidirectional authentication",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The system shall authenticate devices before establishing local/remote/network connection using a cryptographically based bidirectional authentication.",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"808dfd05-b6f6-47c3-a866-2d00d46b7928\\":\\"NIST-SP800-53_rev4\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"808dfd05-b6f6-47c3-a866-2d00d46b7928\\":\\"IA-3(1)\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "A local connection is any connection with a device communicating without the use of a network. A network connection is any connection with a device that communicates through a network (e.g., local area or wide area network, Internet). A remote connection is any connection with a device communicating through an external network (e.g., the Internet). Bidirectional authentication provides stronger safeguards to validate the identity of other devices for connections that are of greater risk (e.g., remote connections)."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            },\n            {\n              "category": "GASF_0030",\n              "index": "01",\n              "type": "GASF",\n              "value": "Delete inactive accounts",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "Description": "The contractor shall include the deletion of inactive accounts in the user account management documentation in the [host document].",\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_R_V5": "{\\"2009\\":{\\"de51f0bb-ad01-47e3-b8a7-a5cd3a22ffd6\\":\\"INDAS0607F074.1_TN2_SRS\\"},\\"2010\\":{\\"de51f0bb-ad01-47e3-b8a7-a5cd3a22ffd6\\":\\"TCA_IDENT_0020\\"}}",\n                "MEHARI_R_V4": "The old and inactive accounts should be deleted.\\nThis prevents illicit use of accounts by other users."\n              },\n              "referenceObject": null,\n              "identifier": null,\n              "objType": "Audit",\n              "lockedBy": null\n            }\n          ],\n          "answers": {\n            "MEHARI_W": "",\n            "MEHARI_Min": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[]",\n            "MEHARI_Max": "",\n            "MEHARI_ISO5": ""\n          },\n          "referenceObject": null,\n          "identifier": null,\n          "objType": "Audit",\n          "lockedBy": null\n        },\n        {\n          "category": "11E03",\n          "index": "3",\n          "type": "CATEGORY",\n          "value": "Surveillance of system administrators` actions over the users` workstations",\n          "children": [\n            {\n              "category": "11E03-01",\n              "index": "1",\n              "type": "QUESTION",\n              "value": "Has a detailed analysis been carried out of the events and operations carried out with administrative rights on the users` workstations which may potentially have an impact on system security? ",\n              "children": [],\n              "gasf": [],\n              "answers": {\n                "MEHARI_W": "2",\n                "MEHARI_Min": "",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13": "12.4.3",\n                "MEHARI_ISO13_info": "[{\\"ClauseId\\":\\"A12\\",\\"Clause\\":\\"Operations security\\",\\"ObjectiveId\\":\\"A12.4\\",\\"Objective\\":\\"Logging and monitoring\\"