	(2020, '12', 'Security of operational procedures ', 'CATEGORY', '12A', '12', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2021, '1', 'Consideration of security in relation with operational personnel (permanent and temporary staff)', 'CATEGORY', '12A01', '12A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2022, '1', 'Is there a security policy, specifically aimed at operations personnel, related to telecommunications?\r\nThis policy should cover the requirements for the protection of information as well as the protection of physical assets and processes and mention the forbidden behaviors', 'QUESTION', '12A01-01', '12A01', '4', '', '', 'E1', '11.2.1', '9.2.1', NULL),
	(2023, '2', 'Is telecommunication operations personnel required to sign contract clauses of adherence to that security policy (no matter their status: permanent or temporary staff, students, etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '12A01-02', '12A01', '4', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2024, '3', 'Do these clauses make clear that the personnel has an obligation not to tolerate any action contrary to security from other people?', 'QUESTION', '12A01-03', '12A01', '4', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(2025, '4', 'Does the signature of these clauses represent a formal commitment?\r\nIn order to achieve a formal commitment, the personnel should explicitly state that his/her signature implies having understood and accepted the security policy', 'QUESTION', '12A01-04', '12A01', '4', '3', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2026, '5', 'Are these same clauses obligatory for contractors working on systems operations?\r\nPractically, the contractors should ensure that their personnel sign individually and explicitly under the same conditions than internal staff. ', 'QUESTION', '12A01-05', '12A01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2027, '6', 'Is there a mandatory and well adapted training course aimed at systems operation personnel?', 'QUESTION', '12A01-06', '12A01', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2028, '7', 'Are the security policy compliance agreements, signed by personnel, securely kept (at least in a locked cupboard )?  ', 'QUESTION', '12A01-07', '12A01', '2', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(2029, '8', 'Are the security policy compliance agreements, signed by external contractors, securely kept (at least in a locked cupboard )?  ', 'QUESTION', '12A01-08', '12A01', '2', '3', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(2030, '9', 'Is there a regular audit, at least once a year, of the effective application of the signature procedure by  operational personnel (directly employed by the company or indirectly through a service company)?  ', 'QUESTION', '12A01-09', '12A01', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(2031, '2', 'Control of the implementation of new equipment or upgrade of existing systems\r\nEquipment for classical telephony: PABX, ..\r\nWith VoIP: call server, gateway converter to classical telephony, routers, switches\r\nEquipment dedicated to users: telephone terminal, fax machines (often combined with printing, scanning and photocopy capabilities, ...), tele and videoconferencing, ..\r\nThese systems may provide configuration, management, directory, billing and storage (answering machine, voice mail) services, ..', 'CATEGORY', '12A02', '12A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2032, '1', 'Are the decisions to change or update equipment and systems significantly subject to a control procedure (registration, planning, formal approval, communication to all concerned individuals, etc.)?\r\nThe possible separation (physical or logical, using VLAN) of data and voice flows shall be analyzed when moving to VoIP and revised based on the observed load changes, the same applies to interconnection capabilities between the two networks ', 'QUESTION', '12A02-01', '12A02', '4', '', '', 'E1', '12.1.2; 12.1.3', '10.1.2; 10.3.1', NULL),
	(2033, '2', 'Are the change decisions based on an analysis of the capacity of the new equipment and systems to ensure the required load and take into account the evolution of foreseeable requests?', 'QUESTION', '12A02-02', '12A02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.3', '10.3.1', NULL),
	(2034, '3', 'Do the installations take into account physical protection?\r\nProtected access, no direct external view on equipment, no multiple physical threats, continuity of power supply, weather conditions, protection against thunderbolts, protection against dust, etc.', 'QUESTION', '12A02-03', '12A02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '11.2.1', '9.2.1', NULL),
	(2035, '4', 'Is any new or modified functionality linked to a new system or new version of a system, systematically documented before moving into production?', 'QUESTION', '12A02-04', '12A02', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2036, '5', 'Is such new functionality (or change in functionality), linked to a new system or new version of a system, formally and systematically reviewed in conjunction with the IT security function?', 'QUESTION', '12A02-05', '12A02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '14.2.9', '10.3.2', NULL),
	(2037, '6', 'Does this review include an analysis of the risks that may  result from the changes? ', 'QUESTION', '12A02-06', '12A02', '2', '2', '', 'E2', '14.2.9', '10.3.2', NULL),
	(2038, '7', 'Have telecommunication  operations staff received formal appropriate training in risk analysis?\r\nThis should include service continuity as well as confidentiality and integrity of the data and the transmissions', 'QUESTION', '12A02-07', '12A02', '1', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(2039, '8', 'May the operation staff obtain an appropriate support specially competent on risk analysis? ', 'QUESTION', '12A02-08', '12A02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(2040, '9', 'Are the security measures, determined to counter the new identified risks, formally reviewed before implementation?', 'QUESTION', '12A02-09', '12A02', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '14.2.9', '10.3.2', NULL),
	(2041, '10', 'Are security parameters and configuration rules (deletion of generic accounts, changing of any default passwords, blocking of unauthorized communications ports, setting of access rights and authentication parameters, etc.) listed in detail and regularly updated?', 'QUESTION', '12A02-10', '12A02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '14.2.9', '10.3.2; 11.4.4', NULL),
	(2042, '11', 'Are the security parameters and configuration rules controlled prior to any start of production of a new version? ', 'QUESTION', '12A02-11', '12A02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '14.2.9', '10.3.2; 11.4.4', NULL),
	(2043, '12', 'Has the eventual impact of the systems` changes regarding the continuity plans been considered?', 'QUESTION', '12A02-12', '12A02', '2', '', '', 'E2', '14.2.9', '10.3.2', NULL),
	(2044, '13', 'Are any exemptions from the prerequisite risk analysis and control of security parameters subject to strict procedures, including a signature from senior management?', 'QUESTION', '12A02-13', '12A02', '4', '', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(2045, '14', 'Can the start of production of new systems and applications be only carried out by  operations personnel?', 'QUESTION', '12A02-14', '12A02', '2', '2', '', 'E3', '12.5.1', '6.1.4; 12.4.1', NULL),
	(2046, '15', 'Is the start of  production of new versions of systems or applications possible by the use of a defined validation and authorization process? ', 'QUESTION', '12A02-15', '12A02', '2', '2', '', 'E3', '12.5.1', '6.1.4; 12.4.1', NULL),
	(2047, '16', 'Are the start of production control procedures regularly audited?', 'QUESTION', '12A02-16', '12A02', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(2048, '3', 'Control of maintenance operations ', 'CATEGORY', '12A03', '12A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2049, '1', 'Is a trace of all maintenance operations kept?', 'QUESTION', '12A03-01', '12A03', '1', '', '', 'E2', '11.2.4', '9.2.4', NULL),
	(2050, '2', 'Are all maintenance operations required to terminate with a systematic control of physical or recorded configurations and security parameters (as defined at time of start of production)? ', 'QUESTION', '12A03-02', '12A03', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2051, '3', 'Are all maintenance operations required to terminate with a systematic control of the recording parameters for security events and the life span of records?', 'QUESTION', '12A03-03', '12A03', '4', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(2052, '4', 'Are all maintenance operations required to terminate with a systematic control of system administration parameters (required profile, authentication type, removal of standard logins etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '12A03-04', '12A03', '4', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(2053, '5', 'Is a formal dispensation, signed by a responsible manager, required if the above mentioned procedures are not observed? ', 'QUESTION', '12A03-05', '12A03', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(2054, '6', 'Is the effective implementation of these controls regularly audited?', 'QUESTION', '12A03-06', '12A03', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(2055, '4', 'Control of Remote Maintenance ', 'CATEGORY', '12A04', '12A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2056, '1', 'In the case of remote maintenance, is the remote maintenance desk`s access subject to a secure authentication procedure?', 'QUESTION', '12A04-01', '12A04', '2', '', '2', 'E2', '', '11.4.4', NULL),
	(2057, '2', 'In the case of remote maintenance, are maintenance staff subject to a secure authentication procedure?', 'QUESTION', '12A04-02', '12A04', '4', '', '2', 'E2', '', '11.4.4', NULL),
	(2058, '3', 'Is there a set of procedures covering the granting and revocation of access rights for remote maintenance operatives and the granting of rights in urgent situations?', 'QUESTION', '12A04-03', '12A04', '2', '', '', 'E3', '', '11.4.4', NULL),
	(2059, '4', 'Does the usage of the remote maintenance line require the prior agreement (for each usage) of telecommunication operations personnel (upon request by the manufacturer or editor specifying the nature, date and time of the intervention)?', 'QUESTION', '12A04-04', '12A04', '4', '3', '', 'E3', '', '11.4.4', NULL),
	(2060, '5', 'Is the usage of the remote maintenance line under strict control?\r\nA strict control supposes that each use of the line, the name of the maintenance operative and the actions carried out is registered, and that there be a subsequent audit of the appropriateness of the actions and their conformity with the rules laid down by maintenance managers.', 'QUESTION', '12A04-05', '12A04', '4', '3', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2061, '6', 'Are control procedures for remote maintenance regularly audited?', 'QUESTION', '12A04-06', '12A04', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(2062, '5', 'Management of Operating Procedures for Telecommunication Operation ', 'CATEGORY', '12A05', '12A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2063, '1', 'Do the operating procedures result from the study of the overall cases to be covered by said procedure (normal operating cases and incidents)?', 'QUESTION', '12A05-01', '12A05', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.1', '10.1.1', NULL),
	(2064, '2', 'Are the operating procedures documented and kept up to date?', 'QUESTION', '12A05-02', '12A05', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.1', '10.1.1', NULL),
	(2065, '3', 'Are the operating procedures readily available upon request by any accredited individual?', 'QUESTION', '12A05-03', '12A05', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.1', '10.1.1', NULL),
	(2066, '4', 'Is the telecommunications operation Management required to approve changes to procedures?', 'QUESTION', '12A05-04', '12A05', '4', '', '', 'E2', '12.1.1', '10.1.1', NULL),
	(2067, '5', 'Are these procedures protected from unauthorized alterations?', 'QUESTION', '12A05-05', '12A05', '2', '', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(2068, '6', 'Are the operating procedures audited regularly for authenticity and relevance?', 'QUESTION', '12A05-06', '12A05', '2', '', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(2069, '6', 'Management of service providers relating to telecommunication', 'CATEGORY', '12A06', '12A', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2070, '1', 'Is it regularly ensured that the security services allocated to suppliers or providers are efficiently implemented and maintained by them?', 'QUESTION', '12A06-01', '12A06', '4', '', '', 'C1', '', '10.2.1', NULL),
	(2071, '2', 'Is it ensured that the telecommunications service suppliers or providers  have efficiently prepared the appropriate arrangements to ensure that the services are provided as agreed?', 'QUESTION', '12A06-02', '12A06', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '10.2.1', NULL),
	(2072, '3', 'Is the respect of the security provisions by the suppliers or providers regularly reviewed?', 'QUESTION', '12A06-03', '12A06', '4', '', '', 'E1', '15.2.1', '10.2.2', NULL),
	(2073, '4', 'Is it ensured that the suppliers and providers report and document any security incident concerning information or networks?', 'QUESTION', '12A06-04', '12A06', '4', '', '', 'E2', '15.2.1', '10.2.2', NULL),
	(2074, '5', 'Is there a regular review of these incidents or malfunctions with the concerned suppliers and providers?', 'QUESTION', '12A06-05', '12A06', '2', '', '', 'E2', '15.2.1', '10.2.2', NULL),
	(2075, '6', 'Are any changes in the contract relationship (obligations, service levels, etc.) analyzed for resulting potential risks?', 'QUESTION', '12A06-06', '12A06', '2', '', '', 'E3', '15.2.2', '10.2.3', NULL),
	(2076, '12', 'Control of hardware and software configurations', 'CATEGORY', '12B', '12', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2077, '1', 'Network equipment customizing and compliance control of configurations', 'CATEGORY', '12B01', '12B', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2078, '1', 'Is an exact inventory of the equipment kept up to date by the concerned responsible persons?\r\nOf key importance with VoIP for the move of terminal equipment and their configuration (including configured emergency call numbers) ', 'QUESTION', '12B01-01', '12B01', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2079, '2', 'Is there a document (or a set of documents ) or an operational procedure which describes all security parameters for the equipment and systems?\r\nSuch a document should be derived from the security policy and describe all the filtering rules decided. It should also mention the reference to the system versions so as to check the status of the updates.', 'QUESTION', '12B01-02', '12B01', '4', '2', '', 'E1', '', '', NULL),
	(2080, '3', 'Does this document require that all generic or by default accounts be deleted and their list established? ', 'QUESTION', '12B01-03', '12B01', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '11.4.4', NULL),
	(2081, '4', 'Are the system versions, fixes and parameters updated regularly in line with latest information?\r\nThis should be done in cooperation with expert authorities (specialized audits, subscription to a service center, regular consultation with CERTs, etc.) ', 'QUESTION', '12B01-04', '12B01', '2', '3', '', 'E2', '12.6.1', '10.7.4; 12.6.1', NULL),
	(2082, '5', 'Does the resulting document or procedure impose a synchronization feature, based on a reliable time reference?', 'QUESTION', '12B01-05', '12B01', '4', '', '', 'E3', '12.4.4', '10.10.6', NULL),
	(2083, '6', 'Are these reference documents protected, by secure methods, against untimely or illicit alteration (sealing)?  ', 'QUESTION', '12B01-06', '12B01', '2', '3', '', 'R1', '', '10.7.4', NULL),
	(2084, '7', 'Is the integrity of system configurations checked, regularly (at least weekly) if not at each system start-up, against the configuration theoretically expected?', 'QUESTION', '12B01-07', '12B01', '4', '2', '', 'E3', '18.2.3', '15.2.2', NULL),
	(2085, '8', 'Are regular audits carried out of the  compliance to the specifications for security parameters?', 'QUESTION', '12B01-08', '12B01', '2', '', '', 'R1', '18.2.3', '15.2.2', NULL),
	(2086, '9', 'Are regular audits carried out of the exception and escalation procedures in the case of difficulty or installation problems?', 'QUESTION', '12B01-09', '12B01', '2', '', '', 'R1', '18.2.3', '15.2.2', NULL),
	(2087, '10', 'Are the development and test environments separated from the operational environments?', 'QUESTION', '12B01-10', '12B01', '1', '', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(2088, '11', 'Is it possible to control, each time it is needed, the compliance of the architecture and of the configurations of the equipment? ', 'QUESTION', '12B01-11', '12B01', '2', '2', '', 'R2', '', '', NULL),
	(2089, '2', 'Conformity control of operational software to a reference version ', 'CATEGORY', '12B02', '12B', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2090, '1', 'Do the telecommunications operations manage a reference version for each equipment or system in operation (source and executable code)? ', 'QUESTION', '12B02-01', '12B02', '4', '2', '', 'E1', '', '', NULL),
	(2091, '2', 'Is this reference version protected against all possible illicit or untimely modification (signed media kept by a senior manager, electronic sealing, etc.)?  ', 'QUESTION', '12B02-02', '12B02', '2', '', '', 'R1', '', '', NULL),
	(2092, '3', 'Is this protection considered to be inviolable (sealing by cryptographic algorithm approved by the Information Security Officer)?  ', 'QUESTION', '12B02-03', '12B02', '4', '', '', 'R2', '', '', NULL),
	(2093, '4', 'Is the protective seal controlled automatically (otherwise it may be an authoritative signature) at each new installation?', 'QUESTION', '12B02-04', '12B02', '4', '', '', 'R2', '', '', NULL),
	(2094, '5', 'Is a check made of the proof of origin and integrity of received maintenance module or a new version, from the editor or the manufacturer (for operating systems)?  ', 'QUESTION', '12B02-05', '12B02', '4', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2095, '6', 'Are the sealing and sealing control tools protected against any unauthorized usage?', 'QUESTION', '12B02-06', '12B02', '4', '', '', 'R2', '', '', NULL),
	(2096, '7', 'Does the inhibition of the automatic control of seals trigger an alarm to a manager?', 'QUESTION', '12B02-07', '12B02', '4', '', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
