	(2117, '3', 'Backup of software configurations (system, services and configuration parameters) ', 'CATEGORY', '12C03', '12C', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2118, '1', 'Has a backup plan been established which covers all programs and defines all objects to save and the frequency of backups?', 'QUESTION', '12C03-01', '12C03', '4', '', '', 'E1', '12.3.1', '10.5.1', NULL),
	(2119, '2', 'Does the plan also cover configuration parameters of the telecommunication equipment to save?', 'QUESTION', '12C03-02', '12C03', '4', '3', '', 'E2', '12.3.1', '10.5.1', NULL),
	(2120, '3', 'Is the plan implemented by automatic production routines?', 'QUESTION', '12C03-03', '12C03', '2', '3', '', 'E2', '12.3.1', '10.5.1', NULL),
	(2121, '4', 'Are there regular tests that the backup copies of configurations enable the effective restoration of the production environment at any time?\r\nThese tests should consider all the backups (including documentation and parameters files) of legitimate elements.', 'QUESTION', '12C03-04', '12C03', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '12.3.1; 17.1.2; 17.1.3', '10.5.1; 14.1.5', NULL),
	(2122, '5', 'Are the production routines which ensure backups protected, against illicit or undue modification, by secure mechanisms?\r\nSuch mechanisms might be electronic seal or any equivalent modification detection system.', 'QUESTION', '12C03-05', '12C03', '4', '3', '', 'R1', '12.3.1', '10.5.1', NULL),
	(2123, '6', 'Are regular tests made of the readability of backups?', 'QUESTION', '12C03-06', '12C03', '2', '3', '', 'R2', '12.3.1', '10.5.1', NULL),
	(2124, '7', 'Are all software backup plans and procedures subject to regular audit?', 'QUESTION', '12C03-07', '12C03', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(2125, '4', 'Disaster Recovery Plans', 'CATEGORY', '12C04', '12C', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2126, '1', 'Have all the scenarios which may impact the telecommunications infrastructure and services been considered and, for each scenario, the consequences in terms of service unavailability for users?\r\nVoIP creates additional requirements for power supply continuity and ability to reconfigure of terminal equipment ', 'QUESTION', '12C04-01', '12C04', '4', '', '', 'E1', '17.1.2', '14.1.3', NULL),
	(2127, '2', 'For each scenario, and in agreement with the users, have a list and schedule of service resume been defined?\r\nLoss of information, means to reconstruct them and temporary operational procedures must be considered.', 'QUESTION', '12C04-02', '12C04', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '17.1.2', '14.1.3', NULL),
	(2128, '3', 'Has an activity recovery solution been defined and implemented to resolve each scenario identified above, in accordance with user requirements?', 'QUESTION', '12C04-03', '12C04', '4', '', '2', 'E1', '17.1.2', '14.1.3', NULL),
	(2129, '4', 'Are the technical, organizational and human resources sufficient to address the organization`s requirements for IT continuity?\r\nThis means being able to correct personnel deficiencies', 'QUESTION', '12C04-04', '12C04', '4', '', '', 'E2', '17.1.2', '14.1.3', NULL),
	(2130, '5', 'Are the technical, organizational and human resources educated to address the organization`s requirements for continuity?\r\nThis implies to train appropriately all concerned staff.', 'QUESTION', '12C04-05', '12C04', '4', '', '', 'E2', '17.1.2', '14.1.3', NULL),
	(2131, '6', 'Are all these solutions described in detail in Disaster Recovery Plans including the conditions for triggering the plan, the actions to execute, the priorities, the actors to mobilize and their contact details? ', 'QUESTION', '12C04-06', '12C04', '4', '', '', 'E1', '17.1.2', '14.1.3', NULL),
	(2132, '7', 'Are these plans tested at least once a year?', 'QUESTION', '12C04-07', '12C04', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '17.1.2; 17.1.3', '14.1.5', NULL),
	(2133, '8', 'Are above tests able to guarantee that the staff capacity and the recovery systems can cope, under full operational load, the minimum service levels required by users?\r\nThe tests required to obtain this guarantee are preferably full scale tests of each variant of scenario, involving all users. The results of the tests have to be registered and analyzed in order to improve the capability of the organization to answer to the situations considered. ', 'QUESTION', '12C04-08', '12C04', '4', '3', '', 'E2', '17.1.2; 17.1.3', '14.1.5', NULL),
	(2134, '9', 'If the recovery solutions include delivery of hardware components (which cannot be triggered during tests), is there a contractual commitment by the manufacturer or any relevant third party (leaser, broker, distributor) to deliver the replacement hardware within fixed and anticipated time limits as stated in the recovery plan?', 'QUESTION', '12C04-09', '12C04', '4', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2135, '10', 'Has the unavailability or failure of the recovery facility been considered and has a replacement solution been defined and validated (second level recovery)?', 'QUESTION', '12C04-10', '12C04', '2', '3', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2136, '11', 'Has this (second level  recovery) solution been validated?', 'QUESTION', '12C04-11', '12C04', '2', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(2137, '12', 'Is the recovery solution usable for an unlimited duration and, if not, has a follow on replacement solution been established?', 'QUESTION', '12C04-12', '12C04', '2', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(2138, '13', 'Are the existence, the pertinence and the updates of the services Recovery Plans regularly controlled?', 'QUESTION', '12C04-13', '12C04', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(2139, '14', 'Is the updating of the above procedures within the recovery plan subject to regular audit?', 'QUESTION', '12C04-14', '12C04', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
	(2140, '5', 'Management of critical systems (regarding maintenance continuity) ', 'CATEGORY', '12C05', '12C', '', '', '', '', '', '', NULL),
	(2141, '1', 'Have the consequences of the disappearance of a supplier been analyzed (in the case of failure, a bug or change requirement) and has a list of critical systems been established? \r\nThis is valid for hardware, software or service providers', 'QUESTION', '12C05-01', '12C05', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2142, '2', 'For all critical systems, has a corrective solution been analyzed to cope with the failure or disappearance of a supplier (consignment of maintenance documentation or source code with a trusted third party, hardware replacement by standard market solutions etc.)?', 'QUESTION', '12C05-02', '12C05', '2', '', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2143, '3', 'Is there a guarantee that the corrective solutions could be made operational within time delays compatible with the continuity of the business and accepted by the users?', 'QUESTION', '12C05-03', '12C05', '2', '2', '', 'E2', '', '', NULL),
	(2144, '4', 'Have variants to the primary solution been considered in case it might encounter unforeseen difficulties?', 'QUESTION', '12C05-04', '12C05', '2', '3', '', 'E3', '', '', NULL),
	(2145, '5', 'Is there a regular review of critical systems and corrective solutions envisaged?', 'QUESTION', '12C05-05', '12C05', '2', '3', '', 'C1', '', '', NULL),
